					We drowned those who rejected Our revelations. They were blind people.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					And to Aad, their brother Hud. He said, "my people! Worship God; you have no
					god other than Him. Will you not take heed?"
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					The elite of his people who disbelieved said, "We see foolishness in you, and
					we think that you are a liar."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					He said, "my people! There is no foolishness in me, but I am a messenger from
					the Lord of the Worlds.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					"I convey to you the messages of my Lord, and I am a trustworthy adviser to
					you."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					"Are you surprised that a reminder has come to you from your Lord, through a
					man from among you, to warn you? Remember how He made you successors after the
					people of Noah, and increased you greatly in stature. And remember God's
					blessings, so that you may prosper."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					They said, "Did you come to us to make us worship God alone, and abandon what
					our ancestors used to worship? Then bring us what you threaten us with, if you
					are truthful."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					He said, "Condemnation and wrath have befallen you from your Lord. Are you
					arguing with me over names, which you and your ancestors invented, for which
					God sent down no authority? Just wait; I am waiting with you."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					So We saved him and those with him, by mercy from Us, and We cut off the roots
					of those who rejected Our revelations and were not believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					And to Thamood, their brother Saleh. He said, "my people! Worship God; you have
					no god other than Him. Clarification has come to you from your Lord. This
					she-camel of God is a sign for you. So leave her to graze on God's earth, and
					do her no harm, lest a painful penalty seizes you."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					"And remember how He made you successors after Aad, and settled you in the
					land. You make for yourselves mansions on its plains, and carve out dwellings
					in the mountains. So remember God's benefits, and do not roam the earth
					corruptingly."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					The elite of his people, who were arrogant, said to the common people who had
					believed, "Do you know that Saleh is sent from his Lord?" They said, "We are
					believers in what he was sent with."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					Those who were arrogant said, "We reject what you believe in."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					So they hamstrung the she-camel, and defied the command of their Lord, and
					said, "Saleh, bring upon us what you threaten us with, if you are one of the
					messengers."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					Whereupon the quake overtook them, and they became lifeless bodies in their
					homes.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					Then he turned away from them, and said, "my people, I have delivered to you
					the message of my Lord, and I have advised you, but you do not like those who
					give advice."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And Lot, when he said to his people, "Do you commit lewdness no people anywhere
					have ever committed before you?"
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					"You lust after men rather than women. You are an excessive people."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					And his people's only answer was to say, "Expel them from your town; they are
					purist people."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					But We saved him and his family, except for his wife; she was of those who
					lagged behind.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					And We rained down on them a rain; note the consequences for the sinners.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					And to Median, their brother Shuaib. He said, "my people, worship God; you have
					no god other than Him. A clear proof has come to you from your Lord. Give full
					measure and weight, and do not cheat people out of their rights, and do not
					corrupt the land once it has been set right. This is better for you, if you are
					believers."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					"And do not lurk on every path, making threats and turning away from the path
					of God those who believe in Him, seeking to distort it. And remember how you
					were few, and how He made you numerous. So note the consequences for the
					corrupters."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 87
			-
				-
