					religion." He said, "Even if we are unwilling?"
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					"We would be fabricating falsehood against God, if we were to return to your
					religion, after God has saved us from it. It is not for us to return to it,
					unless God, our Lord, wills. Our Lord embraces all things in knowledge. In God
					we place our trust. Our Lord, decide between us and our people in truth, for
					You are the Best of Deciders."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					The elite of his people who disbelieved said, "If you follow Shuaib, you will
					be losers."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					Thereupon, the quake struck them; and they became lifeless bodies in their
					homes.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					Those who rejected Shuaib-as if they never prospered therein. Those who
					rejected Shuaib-it was they who were the losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					So he turned away from them, and said, "my people, I have delivered to you the
					messages of my Lord, and I have advised you, so why should I grieve over a
					disbelieving people?"
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					We did not send any prophet to any town but We afflicted its people with misery
					and adversity, so that they may humble themselves.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					Then We substituted prosperity in place of hardship. Until they increased in
					number, and said, "Adversity and prosperity has touched our ancestors." Then We
					seized them suddenly, while they were unaware.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Had the people of the towns believed and turned righteous, We would have opened
					for them the blessings of the heaven and the earth; but they rejected the
					truth, so We seized them by what they were doing.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					Do the people of the towns feel secure that Our might will not come upon them
					by night, while they sleep?
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					Do the people of the towns feel secure that Our might will not come upon them
					by day, while they play?
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					Do they feel safe from God's plan? None feel safe from God's plan except the
					losing people.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					Is it not guidance for those who inherit the land after its inhabitants, that
					if We willed, We could strike them for their sins? And seal up their hearts, so
					that they would not hear?
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					These towns-We narrate to you some of their tales. Their messengers came to
					them with the clear signs, but they would not believe in what they had rejected
					previously. Thus God seals the hearts of the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					We found most of them untrue to their covenants; We found most of them corrupt.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					Then, after them, We sent Moses with Our miracles to Pharaoh and his
					establishment, but they denounced them. So consider the end of the evildoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					Moses said, "Pharaoh, I am a messenger from the Lord of the Worlds."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					"It is only proper that I should not say about God anything other than the
					truth. I have come to you with clear evidence from your Lord, so let the
					Children of Israel go with me."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					He said, "If you brought a miracle, then present it, if you are truthful."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					So he threw his staff, and it was an apparent serpent.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					And He pulled out his hand, and it was white to the onlookers.
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					The notables among Pharaoh's people said, "This is really a skilled magician."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					"He wants to evict you from your land, so what do you recommend?"
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					They said, "Put him off, and his brother, and send heralds to the cities."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 112
			-
				-
					"And let them bring you every skillful magician."
				-
			-
				Surah 7 - The Heights: Ayah 113
			-
				-
					The magicians came to Pharaoh, and said, "Surely there is a reward for us, if
