					battle, or to join another group, has incurred wrath from God, and his abode is
					Hell-what a miserable destination!
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					It was not you who killed them, but it was God who killed them. And it was not
					you who launched when you launched, but it was God who launched. That He may
					bestow upon the believers an excellent reward. God is Hearing and Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Such is the case. God will undermine the strategy of the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					If you desire a verdict, the verdict has come to you. And if you desist, it
					would be best for you. And if you return, We will return; and your troops,
					however numerous, will not benefit you. God is with the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Obey God and His Messenger, and do not turn away from him
					when you hear.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And be not like those who say, "We hear," when they do not hear.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					The worst of animals to God are the deaf and dumb-those who do not reason.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Had God recognized any good in them, He would have made them hear; and had He
					made them hear, they would have turned away defiantly.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Respond to God and to the Messenger when He calls you to
					what will revive you. And know that God stands between a man and his heart, and
					that to Him you will be gathered.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					And beware of discord which does not afflict the wrongdoers among you
					exclusively; and know that God is severe in retribution.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And remember when you were few, oppressed in the land, fearing that people may
					capture you; but He sheltered you, and supported you with His victory, and
					provided you with good things-so that you may be thankful.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not betray God and the Messenger, nor betray your trusts,
					while you know.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And know that your possessions and your children are a test, and that God
					possesses an immense reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					O you who believe! If you remain conscious of God, He will give you a
					criterion, and will remit from you your sins, and will forgive you. God is
					possessor of infinite grace.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					When the disbelievers plotted against you, to imprison you, or kill you, or
					expel you. They planned, and God planned, but God is the Best of planners.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					And when Our revelations are recited to them, they say, "We have heard. Had we
					wanted, we could have said the like of this; these are nothing but myths of the
					ancients."
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And they said, "Our God, if this is the truth from You, then rain down on us
					stones from the sky, or visit us with a painful affliction."
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					But God would not punish them while you are amongst them. And God would not
					punish them as long as they seek forgiveness.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Yet why should God not punish them, when they are turning others away from the
					Sacred Mosque, although they are not its custodians? Its rightful custodians
					are the pious; but most of them do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Their prayer at the House was nothing but whistling and clapping-so taste the
					punishment for your blasphemy.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve spend their wealth to repel from God's path. They will
					spend it, then it will become a source of sorrow for them, and then they will
					be defeated. Those who disbelieve will be herded into Hell.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					That God may distinguish the bad from the good, and heap the bad on top of one
					another, and pile them together, and throw them in Hell. These are the losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Say to those who disbelieve: if they desist, their past will be forgiven. But
					if they persist-the practice of the ancients has passed away.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Fight them until there is no more persecution, and religion becomes exclusively
					for God. But if they desist-God is Seeing of what they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					And if they turn away, know that God is your Protector. The Best Protector, and
					the Best Supporter.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					And know that whatever spoils you gain, to God belongs its fifth, and to the
					Messenger, and the relatives, and the orphans, and the poor, and to the
					wayfarer, provided you believe in God and in what We revealed to Our servant on
					the Day of Distinction, the day when the two armies met. God is Capable of
					everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Recall when you were on the nearer bank, and they were on the further bank, and
					the caravan was below you. Had you planned for this meeting, you would have
					disagreed on the timing, but God was to carry out a predetermined matter, so
					that those who perish would perish by clear evidence, and those who survive
					would survive by clear evidence. God is Hearing and Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					God made them appear in your dream as few. Had He made them appear as many, you
					would have lost heart, and disputed in the matter. But God saved the situation.
					He knows what the hearts contain.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					When you met, He made them appear as few in your eyes, and made you appear
					fewer in their eyes, so that God may conclude a predetermined matter. To God
					all matters revert.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					O you who believe! When you meet a force, stand firm, and remember God much, so
					that you may prevail.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					And obey God and His Messenger, and do not dispute, lest you falter and lose
					your courage. And be steadfast. God is with the steadfast.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And do not be like those who left their homes boastfully, showing off before
					the people, and barring others from the path of God. God comprehends what they
					do.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					Satan made their deeds appear good to them, and said, "You cannot be defeated
					by any people today, and I am at your side." But when the two armies came in
					sight of one another, he turned on his heels, and said, "I am innocent of you;
					I see what you do not see; I fear God; God is severe in punishment."
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					The hypocrites and those in whose hearts is sickness said, "Their religion has
					deluded these people." But whoever puts his trust in God-God is Mighty and
					Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					If only you could see, as the angels take away those who disbelieve, striking
					their faces and their backs: "Taste the agony of the Burning."
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					"That is because of what your hands have committed, and because God is not
					unjust to the servants."
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Like the behavior of the people of Pharaoh, and those before them. They
					rejected the signs of God, so God seized them for their sins. God is Powerful,
					Severe in punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					That is because God would never change a blessing He has bestowed on a people
					unless they change what is within themselves, and because God is Hearing and
					Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Such was the case with the people of Pharaoh, and those before them. They
					denied the signs of their Lord, so We annihilated them for their wrongs, and We
					drowned the people of Pharaoh-they were all evildoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					The worst of creatures in God's view are those who disbelieve. They have no
					faith.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					Those of them with whom you made a treaty, but they violate their agreement
					every time. They are not righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					If you confront them in battle, make of them a fearsome example for those who
					follow them, that they may take heed.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					If you fear treachery on the part of a people, break off with them in a like
					manner. God does not like the treacherous.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Let not the disbelievers assume that they are ahead. They will not escape.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					And prepare against them all the power you can muster, and all the cavalry you
					can mobilize, to terrify thereby God's enemies and your enemies, and others
					besides them whom you do not know, but God knows them. Whatever you spend in
					God's way will be repaid to you in full, and you will not be wronged.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					But if they incline towards peace, then incline towards it, and put your trust
					in God. He is the Hearer, the Knower.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					If they intend to deceive you-God is sufficient for you. It is He who supported
					you with His aid, and with the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					And He united their hearts. Had you spent everything on earth, you would not
					have united their hearts, but God united them together. He is Mighty and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					O prophet! Count on God, and on the believers who have followed you.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					O prophet! Rouse the believers to battle. If there are twenty steadfast among
					you, they will defeat two hundred; and if there are a hundred of you, they will
					defeat a thousand of those who disbelieve; because they are a people who do not
					understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					God has now lightened your burden, knowing that there is weakness in you. If
					there are a hundred steadfast among you, they will defeat two hundred; and if
					there are a thousand of you, they will defeat two thousand by God's leave. God
					is with the steadfast.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					It is not for a prophet to take prisoners before he has subdued the land. You
					desire the materials of this world, but God desires the Hereafter. God is
					Strong and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					Were it not for a predetermined decree from God, an awful punishment would have
					afflicted you for what you have taken.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					So consume what you have gained, legitimate and wholesome; and remain conscious
					of God. God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					O prophet! Say to those you hold prisoners, "If God finds any good in your
					hearts, He will give you better than what was taken from you, and He will
					forgive you. God is Forgiving and Merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					But if they intend to betray you, they have already betrayed God, and He has
					overpowered them. God is Knowing and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					Those who believed, and emigrated, and struggled in God's cause with their
					possessions and their persons, and those who provided shelter and support-these
					are allies of one another. As for those who believed, but did not emigrate, you
					owe them no protection, until they have emigrated. But if they ask you for help
					in religion, you must come to their aid, except against a people with whom you
					have a treaty. God is Seeing of what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					As for those who disbelieve, they are allies of one another. Unless you do
					this, there will be turmoil in the land, and much corruption.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					Those who believed, and emigrated, and struggled for God's cause, and those who
					gave shelter and support-these are the true believers. They will have
					forgiveness, and a bountiful provision.
				-
			-
				Surah 8 - The Spoils of War: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					As for those who believed afterwards, and emigrated and struggled with
					you-these belong with you. But family members are nearer to one another in the
					Book of God. God is Cognizant of everything.
