					not violate any of its terms, nor aided anyone against you. So fulfill the
					treaty with them to the end of its term. God loves the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					When the Sacred Months have passed, kill the polytheists wherever you find
					them. And capture them, and besiege them, and lie in wait for them at every
					ambush. But if they repent, and perform the prayers, and pay the alms, then let
					them go their way. God is Most Forgiving, Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And if anyone of the polytheists asks you for protection, give him protection
					so that he may hear the Word of God; then escort him to his place of safety.
					That is because they are a people who do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					How can there be a treaty with the polytheists on the part of God and His
					Messenger, except for those with whom you made a treaty at the Sacred Mosque?
					As long as they are upright with you, be upright with them. God loves the
					pious.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					How? Whenever they overcome you, they respect neither kinship nor treaty with
					you. They satisfy you with lip service, but their hearts refuse, and most of
					them are immoral.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					They traded away God's revelations for a cheap price, so they barred others
					from His path. How evil is what they did.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Towards a believer they respect neither kinship nor treaty. These are the
					transgressors.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					But if they repent, and perform the prayers, and give the obligatory charity,
					then they are your brethren in faith. We detail the revelations for a people
					who know.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					But if they violate their oaths after their pledge, and attack your religion,
					then fight the leaders of disbelief-they have no faith-so that they may desist.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					Will you not fight a people who violated their oaths, and planned to exile the
					Messenger, and initiated hostilities against you? Do you fear them? It is God
					you should fear, if you are believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Fight them. God will punish them at your hands, and humiliate them, and help
					you against them, and heal the hearts of a believing people.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					And He will remove the anger of their hearts. God redeems whomever He wills.
					God is Knowledgeable and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Or do you think that you will be left alone, without God identifying which of
					you will strive, and take no supporters apart from God, His Messenger, and the
					believers? God is well Aware of what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					It is not for the polytheists to attend God's places of worship while
					professing their disbelief. These-their works are in vain, and in the Fire they
					will abide.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					The only people to attend God's places of worship are those who believe in God
					and the Last Day, and pray regularly, and practice regular charity, and fear
					none but God. These are most likely to be guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Do you consider giving water to pilgrims and maintaining the Sacred Mosque the
					same as believing in God and the Last Day and striving in God's path? They are
					not equal in God's sight. God does not guide the unjust people.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Those who believe, and emigrate, and strive in God's path with their
					possessions and their persons, are of a higher rank with God. These are the
					winners.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Their Lord announces to them good news of mercy from Him, and acceptance, and
					gardens wherein they will have lasting bliss.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Abiding therein forever. With God is a great reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not ally yourselves with your parents and your siblings
					if they prefer disbelief to belief. Whoever of you allies himself with
					them-these are the wrongdoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Say, "If your parents, and your children, and your siblings, and your spouses,
					and your relatives, and the wealth you have acquired, and a business you worry
					about, and homes you love, are more dear to you than God, and His Messenger,
					and the struggle in His cause, then wait until God executes His judgment." God
					does not guide the sinful people.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					God has given you victory in numerous regions; but on the day of Hunayn, your
					great number impressed you, but it availed you nothing; and the land, as
					spacious as it was, narrowed for you; and you turned your backs in retreat.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Then God sent down His serenity upon His Messenger, and upon the believers; and
					He sent down troops you did not see; and He punished those who disbelieved.
					Such is the recompense of the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Then, after that, God will relent towards whomever He wills. God is Forgiving
					and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					O you who believe! The polytheists are polluted, so let them not approach the
					Sacred Mosque after this year of theirs. And if you fear poverty, God will
					enrich you from His grace, if He wills. God is Aware and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Fight those who do not believe in God, nor in the Last Day, nor forbid what God
					and His Messenger have forbidden, nor abide by the religion of truth-from among
					those who received the Scripture-until they pay the due tax, willingly or
					unwillingly.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					The Jews said, "Ezra is the son of God," and the Christians said, "The Messiah
					is the son of God." These are their statements, out of their mouths. They
					emulate the statements of those who blasphemed before. May God assail them! How
					deceived they are!
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					They have taken their rabbis and their priests as lords instead of God, as well
					as the Messiah son of Mary. Although they were commanded to worship none but
					The One God. There is no god except He. Glory be to Him; High above what they
					associate with Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					They want to extinguish God's light with their mouths, but God refuses except
					to complete His light, even though the disbelievers dislike it.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					It is He who sent His Messenger with the guidance and the religion of truth, in
					order to make it prevail over all religions, even though the idolaters dislike
					it.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Many of the rabbis and priests consume people's wealth
