			-
				-
					Nor do they spend any expenditure, small or large, nor do they cross any
					valley, but it is recorded to their credit. That God may reward them in
					accordance with the best of their deeds.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 122
			-
				-
					It is not advisable for the believers to march out altogether. Of every
					division that marches out, let a group remain behind, to gain understanding of
					the religion, and to notify their people when they have returned to them, that
					they may beware.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 123
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Fight those of the disbelievers who attack you, and let them
					find severity in you, and know that God is with the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 124
			-
				-
					Whenever a chapter is revealed, some of them say, "Which of you has this
					increased in faith?" As for those who believe: it increases them in faith, and
					they rejoice.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 125
			-
				-
					But as for those in whose hearts is sickness: it adds disgrace to their
					disgrace, and they die as unbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 126
			-
				-
					Do they not see that they are tested once or twice every year? Yet they do not
					repent, and they do not learn.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 127
			-
				-
					And whenever a chapter is revealed, they look at one another, "Does anyone see
					you?" Then they slip away. God has diverted their hearts, because they are a
					people who do not understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 128
			-
				-
					There has come to you a messenger from among yourselves, concerned over your
					suffering, anxious over you. Towards the believers, he is compassionate and
					merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 9 - The Repentance: Ayah 129
			-
				-
					If they turn away, say, "God is enough for me; there is no god except He; in
					Him I have put my trust; He is the Lord of the Sublime Throne."
				-
		-
			Surah 10 - Jonah
		-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Ra. These are the Verses of the Wise Book.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Is it a wonder to the people that We inspired a man from among them: "Warn
					mankind, and give good news to those who believe that they are on a sound
					footing with their Lord"? The disbelievers said, "This is a manifest sorcerer."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Your Lord is God, who created the heavens and the earth in six days, then
					settled over the Throne, governing all things. There is no intercessor except
					after His permission. Such is God, your Lord-so serve Him. Will you not
					reflect?
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					To Him is your return, altogether. The promise of God is true. He originates
					creation, and then He repeats it, to reward those who believe and do good deeds
					with equity. As for those who disbelieve, for them is a drink of boiling water,
					and agonizing torment, on account of their disbelief.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					It is He who made the sun radiant, and the moon a light, and determined phases
					for it-that you may know the number of years and the calculation. God did not
					create all this except with truth. He details the revelations for a people who
					know.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					In the alternation of night and day, and in what God created in the heavens and
					the earth, are signs for people who are aware.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Those who do not hope to meet Us, and are content with the worldly life, and
					are at ease in it, and those who pay no heed to Our signs.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					These-their dwelling is the Fire-on account of what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					As for those who believe and do good deeds, their Lord guides them in their
					faith. Rivers will flow beneath them in the Gardens of Bliss.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Their call therein is, "Glory be to You, our God." And their greeting therein
					is, "Peace." And the last of their call is, "Praise be to God, Lord of the
					Worlds."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					If God were to accelerate the ill for the people, as they wish to accelerate
					the good, their term would have been fulfilled. But We leave those who do not
					expect Our encounter to blunder in their excesses.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Whenever adversity touches the human being, he prays to Us-reclining on his
					side, or sitting, or standing. But when We have relieved his adversity from
					him, he goes away, as though he had never called on Us for trouble that had
					afflicted him. Thus the deeds of the transgressors appear good to them.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					We destroyed generations before you when they did wrong. Their messengers came
					to them with clear signs, but they would not believe. Thus We requite the
					sinful people.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Then We made you successors on earth after them, to see how you would behave.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					And when Our clear revelations are recited to them, those who do not hope to
					meet Us say, "Bring a Quran other than this, or change it." Say, "It is not for
					me to change it of my own accord. I only follow what is revealed to me. I fear,
					if I disobeyed my Lord, the torment of a terrible Day."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Say, "Had God willed, I would not have recited it to you, and He would not have
					made it known to you. I have lived among you for a lifetime before it. Do you
					not understand?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					Who does greater wrong than someone who fabricates lies about God, or denies
					His revelations? The guilty will never prosper.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And they worship, besides God, what neither harms them nor benefits them. And
					they say, "These are our intercessors with God." Say, "Are you informing God
					about what He does not know in the heavens or on earth?" Glorified be He, High
					above the associations they make.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Mankind was a single community; then they differed. Were it not for a prior
					decree from your Lord, the matters over which they had disputed would have been
					settled.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And they say, "If only a miracle was sent down to him from his Lord." Say, "The
					realm of the unseen belongs to God; so wait, I am waiting with you."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					When We make the people taste mercy after some adversity has touched them, they
					begin to scheme against Our revelations. Say, "God is swifter in scheming." Our
					envoys are writing down what you scheme.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					It is He who transports you across land and sea. Until, when you are on ships,
					sailing in a favorable wind, and rejoicing in it, a raging wind arrives. The
					waves surge over them from every side, and they realize that they are besieged.
					Thereupon they pray to God, professing sincere devotion to Him: "If You save us
					from this, we will be among the appreciative."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					But then, when He has saved them, they commit violations on earth, and oppose
					justice. O people! Your violations are against your own souls. It is the
					enjoyment of the present life. Then to Us is your return, and We will inform
					you of what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					The likeness of the present life is this: water that We send down from the sky
					is absorbed by the plants of the earth, from which the people and the animals
					eat. Until, when the earth puts on its fine appearance, and is beautified, and
					its inhabitants think that they have mastered it, Our command descends upon it
					by night or by day, and We turn it into stubble, as if it had not flourished
					the day before. We thus clarify the revelations for people who reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					God invites to the Home of Peace, and guides whomever He wills to a straight
					path.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					For those who have done good is goodness, and more. Neither gloom nor shame
					will come over their faces. These are the inhabitants of Paradise, abiding
					therein forever.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					As for those who have earned evil deeds: a reward of similar evil, and shame
					will cover them. They will have no defense against God-as if their faces are
					covered with dark patches of night. These are the inmates of the Fire, abiding
					therein forever.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					On the Day when We will gather them altogether, then say to those who ascribed
					partners, "To your place, you and your partners." Then We will separate between
					them, and their partners will say, "It was not us you were worshiping."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					"God is sufficient witness between us and you. We were unaware of your
					worshiping us."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					There, every soul will experience what it had done previously; and they will be
					returned to God, their True Master; and what they used to invent will fail
					them.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Say, "Who provides for you from the heaven and the earth? And who controls the
					hearing and the sight? And who produces the living from the dead, and produces
					the dead from the living? And who governs the Order?" They will say, "God."
					Say, "Will you not be careful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Such is God, your Lord-the True. What is there, beyond the truth, except
					falsehood? How are you turned away?
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Thus your Lord's Word proved true against those who disobeyed, for they do not
					believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Say, "Can any of your partners initiate creation, and then repeat it?" Say,
					"God initiates creation, and then repeats it. How are you so deluded?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Say, "Can any of your partners guide to the truth?" Say, "God guides to the
					truth. Is He who guides to the truth more worthy of being followed, or he who
					does not guide, unless he himself is guided? What is the matter with you? How
					do you judge?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Most of them follow nothing but assumptions; and assumptions avail nothing
					against the truth. God is fully aware of what they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					This Quran could not have been produced by anyone other than God. In fact, it
					is a confirmation of what preceded it, and an elaboration of the Book. There is
					no doubt about it-it is from the Lord of the Universe.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Or do they say, "He has forged it"? Say, "Then produce a single chapter like
					it, and call upon whomever you can, apart from God, if you are truthful."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					In fact, they deny what is beyond the limits of their knowledge, and whose
					explanation has not yet reached them. Thus those before them refused to
					believe. So note the consequences for the wrongdoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Among them are those who believe in it, and among them are those who do not
					believe in it. Your Lord is fully aware of the mischief-makers.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					If they accuse you of lying, say, "I have my deeds, and you have your deeds.
					You are quit of what I do, and I am quit of what you do."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					And among them are those who listen to you. But can you make the deaf hear,
					even though they do not understand?
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					And among them are those who look at you. But can you guide the blind, even
					though they do not see?
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					God does not wrong the people in the least, but the people wrong their own
					selves.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					On the Day when He rounds them up-as if they had tarried only one hour of a
					day-they will recognize one another. Those who denied the meeting with God will
					be the losers. They were not guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Whether We show you some of what We promise them, or take you, to Us is their
					return. God is witness to everything they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					Every community has a messenger. When their messenger has come, judgment will
					be passed between them with fairness, and they will not be wronged.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					And they say, "When will this promise be fulfilled, if you are truthful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					Say, "I have no power to harm or benefit myself, except as God wills. To every
					nation is an appointed time. Then, when their time arrives, they can neither
					postpone it by one hour, nor advance it.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Say, "Have you considered? If His punishment overtakes you by night or by day,
					what part of it will the guilty seek to hasten?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					"Then, when it falls, will you believe in it? Now? When before you tried to
					hasten it?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Then it will be said to those who did wrong, "Taste the torment of eternity.
					Will you be rewarded except for what you used to do?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					And they inquire of you, "Is it true?" Say, "Yes, by my Lord, it is true, and
					you cannot evade it."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Had every soul which had done wrong possessed everything on earth, it would
					offer it as a ransom. They will hide the remorse when they witness the
					suffering, and it will be judged between them equitably, and they will not be
					wronged.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					Assuredly, to God belongs everything in the heavens and the earth. Assuredly,
					the promise of God is true. But most of them do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					He gives life and causes death, and to Him you will be returned.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					O people! There has come to you advice from your Lord, and healing for what is
					in the hearts, and guidance and mercy for the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Say, "In God's grace and mercy let them rejoice. That is better than what they
					hoard."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Say, "Have you considered the sustenance God has sent down for you, some of
					which you made unlawful, and some lawful?" Say, "Did God give you permission,
					or do you fabricate lies and attribute them to God?"
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					What will they think-those who fabricate lies and attribute them to God-on the
					Day of Resurrection? God is bountiful towards the people, but most of them do
					not give thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					You do not get into any situation, nor do you recite any Quran, nor do you do
					anything, but We are watching over you as you undertake it. Not even the weight
					of an atom, on earth or in the sky, escapes your Lord, nor is there anything
					smaller or larger, but is in a clear record.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					Unquestionably, God's friends have nothing to fear, nor shall they grieve.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					Those who believe and are aware.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					For them is good news in this life, and in the Hereafter. There is no
					alteration to the words of God. That is the supreme triumph.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					And let not their sayings dishearten you. All power is God's. He is the Hearer,
					the Knower.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					Certainly, to God belongs everyone in the heavens and everyone on earth. Those
					who invoke other than God do not follow partners; they follow only assumptions,
					and they only guess.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					It is He who made the night for your rest, and the daylight for visibility.
					Surely in that are signs for people who listen.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					And they said, "God has taken a son." Be He glorified. He is the
					Self-Sufficient. His is everything in the heavens and everything on earth. Do
					you have any proof for this? Or are you saying about God what you do not know?
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					Say, "Those who fabricate lies about God will not succeed."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					Some enjoyment in this world; then to Us is their return; then We will make
					them taste the severe punishment on account of their disbelief.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					And relate to them the story of Noah, when he said to his people, "my people,
					if my presence among you and my reminding you of God's signs is too much for
					you, then in God I have put my trust. So come to a decision, you and your
					partners, and do not let the matter perplex you; then carry out your decision
					on me, and do not hold back."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					"But if you turn away, I have not asked you for any wage. My wage falls only on
					God, and I was commanded to be of those who submit."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					But they denounced him, so We saved him and those with him in the Ark, and We
					made them successors, and We drowned those who rejected Our signs. So consider
					the fate of those who were warned.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					Then, after him, We sent messengers to their people. They came to them with the
					clear proofs, but they would not believe in anything they had already rejected.
					Thus We set a seal on the hearts of the hostile.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					Then, after them, We sent Moses and Aaron with Our proofs to Pharaoh and his
					dignitaries. But they acted arrogantly. They were sinful people.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					And when the truth came to them from Us, they said, "This is clearly sorcery."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					Moses said, "Is this what you say of the truth when it has come to you? Is this
					sorcery? Sorcerers do not succeed."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					They said, "Did you come to us to divert us from what we found our ancestors
					following, and so that you become prominent in the land? We will never believe
					in you."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					Pharaoh said, "Bring me every experienced sorcerer."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And when the sorcerers came, Moses said to them, "Throw whatever you have to
					throw."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					And when they threw, Moses said, "What you produced is sorcery, and God will
					make it fail. God does not foster the efforts of the corrupt."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					"And God upholds the truth with His words, even though the sinners detest it."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					But none believed in Moses except some children of his people, for fear that
					Pharaoh and his chiefs would persecute them. Pharaoh was high and mighty in the
					land. He was a tyrant.
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					Moses said, "my people, if you have believed in God, then put your trust in
					Him, if you have submitted."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					They said, "In God we have put our trust. Our Lord, do not make us victims of
					the oppressive people."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					"And deliver us, by Your mercy, from the disbelieving people."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					And We inspired Moses and his brother, "Settle your people in Egypt, and make
					your homes places of worship, and perform the prayer, and give good news to the
					believers."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					Moses said, "Our Lord, you have given Pharaoh and his chiefs splendor and
					wealth in the worldly life. Our Lord, for them to lead away from Your path. Our
					Lord, obliterate their wealth, and harden their hearts, they will not believe
					until they see the painful torment."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					He said, "Your prayer has been answered, so go straight, and do not follow the
					path of those who do not know."
				-
			-
				Surah 10 - Jonah: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					And We delivered the Children of Israel across the sea. Pharaoh and his troops
					pursued them, defiantly and aggressively. Until, when he was about to drown, he
