					When they returned to their father, they said, "father, we were denied measure,
					but send our brother with us, and we will obtain measure. We will take care of
					him."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					He said, "Shall I trust you with him, as I trusted you with his brother before?
					God is the Best Guardian, and He is the Most Merciful of the merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					And when they opened their baggage, they found that their goods were returned
					to them. They said, "Father, what more do we want? Here are our goods, returned
					to us. We will provide for our family, and protect our brother, and have an
					additional camel-load. This is easy commerce."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					He said, "I will not send him with you, unless you give me a pledge before God
					that you will bring him back to me, unless you get trapped." And when they gave
					him their pledge, he said, "God is witness to what we say."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					And he said, "my sons, do not enter by one gate, but enter by different gates.
					I cannot avail you anything against God. The decision rests only with God. On
					Him I rely, and on Him let the reliant rely."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					And when they entered as their father had instructed them, it did not avail
					them anything against God; it was just a need in the soul of Jacob, which he
					carried out. He was a person of knowledge inasmuch as We had taught him, but
					most people do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					And when they entered into the presence of Joseph, he embraced his brother, and
					said, "I am your brother; do not be saddened by what they used to do."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					Then, when he provided them with their provisions, he placed the drinking-cup
					in his brother's saddlebag. Then an announcer called out, "people of the
					caravan, you are thieves."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					They said, as they came towards them, "What are you missing?"
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					They said, "We are missing the king's goblet. Whoever brings it will have a
					camel-load; and I personally guarantee it."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					They said, "By God, you know we did not come to cause trouble in the land, and
					we are not thieves."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					They said, "What shall be his punishment, if you are lying?"
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					They said, "His punishment, if it is found in his bag: he will belong to you.
					Thus we penalize the guilty."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					So he began with their bags, before his brother's bag. Then he pulled it out of
					his brother's bag. Thus We devised a plan for Joseph; he could not have
					detained his brother under the king's law, unless God so willed. We elevate by
					degrees whomever We will; and above every person of knowledge, there is one
					more learned.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					They said, "If he has stolen, a brother of his has stolen before." But Joseph
					kept it to himself, and did not reveal it to them. He said, "You are in a worse
					situation, and God is Aware of what you allege."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					They said, "noble prince, he has a father, a very old man, so take one of us in
					his place. We see that you are a good person."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					He said, "God forbid that we should arrest anyone except him in whose
					possession we found our property; for then we would be unjust."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And when they despaired of him, they conferred privately. Their eldest said,
					"Don't you know that your father received a pledge from you before God, and in
					the past you failed with regard to Joseph? I will not leave this land until my
					father permits me, or God decides for me; for He is the Best of Deciders."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					"Go back to your father, and say, 'Our father, your son has stolen. We testify
					only to what we know, and we could not have prevented the unforeseen.'"
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					"Ask the town where we were, and the caravan in which we came. We are being
					truthful."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					He said, "Rather, your souls have contrived something for you. Patience is a
					virtue. Perhaps God will bring them all back to me. He is the Knowing, the
					Wise."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					Then he turned away from them, and said, "my bitterness for Joseph." And his
					eyes turned white from sorrow, and he became depressed.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					They said, "By God, you will not stop remembering Joseph, until you have ruined
					your health, or you have passed away."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					He said, "I only complain of my grief and sorrow to God, and I know from God
					what you do not know."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					"my sons, go and inquire about Joseph and his brother, and do not despair of
					God's comfort. None despairs of God's comfort except the disbelieving people."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					Then, when they entered into his presence, they said, "Mighty governor,
					adversity has befallen us, and our family. We have brought scant merchandise.
					But give us full measure, and be charitable towards us-God rewards the
					charitable."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					He said, "Do you realize what you did with Joseph and his brother, in your
					ignorance?"
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					They said, "Is that you, Joseph?" He said, "I am Joseph, and this is my
					brother. God has been gracious to us. He who practices piety and patience-God
					never fails to reward the righteous."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					They said, "By God, God has preferred you over us. We were definitely in the
					wrong."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					He said, "There is no blame upon you today. God will forgive you. He is the
					Most Merciful of the merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					"Take this shirt of mine, and lay it over my father's face, and he will recover
					his sight. And bring your whole family to me."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					As the caravan set out, their father said, "I sense the presence of Joseph,
					though you may think I am senile."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					They said, "By God, you are still in your old confusion."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Then, when the bearer of good news arrived, he laid it over his face, and he
					regained his sight. He said, "Did I not say to you that I know from God what
					you do not know?"
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					They said, "Father, pray for the forgiveness of our sins; we were indeed at
					fault."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					He said, "I will ask my Lord to forgive you. He is the Forgiver, the Most
					Merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					Then, when they entered into the presence of Joseph, he embraced his parents,
					and said, "Enter Egypt, God willing, safe and secure."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					And he elevated his parents on the throne, and they fell prostrate before him.
					He said, "Father, this is the fulfillment of my vision of long ago. My Lord has
					made it come true. He has blessed me, when he released me from prison, and
					brought you out of the wilderness, after the devil had sown conflict between me
					and my brothers. My Lord is Most Kind towards whomever He wills. He is the
					All-knowing, the Most Wise."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					"My Lord, You have given me some authority, and taught me some interpretation
					of events. Initiator of the heavens and the earth; You are my Protector in this
					life and in the Hereafter. Receive my soul in submission, and unite me with the
					righteous."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					This is news from the past that We reveal to you. You were not present with
					them when they plotted and agreed on a plan.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					But most people, for all your eagerness, are not believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					You ask them no wage for it. It is only a reminder for all mankind.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					How many a sign in the heavens and the earth do they pass by, paying no
					attention to them?
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					And most of them do not believe in God unless they associate others.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					Do they feel secure that a covering of God's punishment will not come upon
					them, or that the Hour will not come upon them suddenly, while they are
					unaware?
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					Say, "This is my way; I invite to God, based on clear knowledge-I and whoever
					follows me. Glory be to God; and I am not of the polytheists."
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					We did not send before you except men, whom We inspired, from the people of the
					towns. Have they not roamed the earth and seen the consequences for those
					before them? The Home of the Hereafter is better for those who are righteous.
					Do you not understand?
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					Until, when the messengers have despaired, and thought that they were rejected,
					Our help came to them. We save whomever We will, and Our severity is not
					averted from the guilty people.
				-
			-
				Surah 12 - Joseph: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					In their stories is a lesson for those who possess intelligence. This is not a
					fabricated tale, but a confirmation of what came before it, and a detailed
					explanation of all things, and guidance, and mercy for people who believe.
				-
		-
			Surah 13 - The Thunder
		-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Meem, Ra. These are the signs of the Scripture. What is revealed to
					you from your Lord is the truth, but most people do not believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					God is He who raised the heavens without pillars that you can see, and then
					settled on the Throne. And He regulated the sun and the moon, each running for
					a specified period. He manages all affairs, and He explains the signs, that you
					may be certain of the meeting with your Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And it is He who spread the earth, and placed in it mountains and rivers. And
					He placed in it two kinds of every fruit. He causes the night to overlap the
					day. In that are signs for people who reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					On earth are adjacent terrains, and gardens of vines, and crops, and
					date-palms, from the same root or from distinct roots, irrigated with the same
					water. We make some taste better than others. In that are proofs for people who
					reason.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Should you wonder-the real wonder is their saying: "When we have become dust,
					will we be in a new creation?" Those are they who defied their Lord. Those are
					they who will have yokes around their necks. Those are the inhabitants of the
					Fire, where they will remain forever.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And they urge you to hasten evil before good, though examples have passed away
					before them. Your Lord is full of forgiveness towards the people for their
					wrongdoings, yet your Lord is severe in retribution.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "Why was a miracle not sent down to him from his
					Lord?" You are only a warner, and to every community is a guide.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					God knows what every female bears, and every increase and decrease of the
					wombs. With Him, everything is by measure.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					The Knower of the Invisible and the Visible; the Grand, the Supreme.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					It is the same; whether one of you conceals his speech, or declares it; whether
					he goes into hiding by night, or goes out by day.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					He has a succession; before him and behind him, protecting him by God's
					command. God does not change the condition of a people until they change what
					is within themselves. And if God wills any hardship for a people, there is no
					turning it back; and apart from Him they have no protector.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					It is He who shows you the lightening, causing fear and hope. And He produces
					the heavy clouds.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					The thunder praises His glory, and so do the angels, in awe of Him. And He
					sends the thunderbolts, striking with them whomever He wills. Yet they argue
					about God, while He is Tremendous in might.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					To Him belongs the call to truth. Those they call upon besides Him do not
					respond to them with anything-except as someone who stretches his hands towards
					water, so that it may reach his mouth, but it does not reach it. The prayers of
					the unbelievers are only in vain.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					To God prostrates everyone in the heavens and the earth, willingly or
					unwillingly, as do their shadows, in the morning and in the evening.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Say, "Who is the Lord of the heavens and the earth?" Say, "God." Say, "Have you
					taken besides Him protectors, who have no power to profit or harm even
					themselves?" Say, "Are the blind and the seeing equal? Or are darkness and
					light equal? Or have they assigned to God associates, who created the likes of
					His creation, so that the creations seemed to them alike? Say, "God is the
					Creator of all things, and He is The One, the Irresistible."
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					He sends down water from the sky, and riverbeds flow according to their
					capacity. The current carries swelling froth. And from what they heat in fire
					of ornaments or utensils comes a similar froth. Thus God exemplifies truth and
					falsehood. As for the froth, it is swept away, but what benefits the people
					remains in the ground. Thus God presents the analogies.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					For those who respond to their Lord is the best. But as for those who do not
					respond to Him, even if they possessed everything on earth, and twice as much,
					they could not redeem themselves with it. Those will have the worst reckoning;
					and their home is Hell-a miserable destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Is he who knows that what was revealed to your from your Lord is the truth,
					like him who is blind? Only those who reason will remember.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Those who fulfill the promise to God, and do not violate the agreement.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And those who join what God has commanded to be joined, and fear their Lord,
					and dread the dire reckoning.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And those who patiently seek the presence of their Lord, and pray regularly,
					and spend from Our provisions to them, secretly and openly, and repel evil with
					good. These will have the Ultimate Home.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Everlasting Gardens, which they will enter, along with the righteous among
					their parents, and their spouses, and their descendants. And the angels will
					enter upon them from every gate.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					"Peace be upon you, because you endured patiently. How excellent is the Final
					Home."
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					As for those who violate the promise to God, after pledging to keep it, and
					sever what God has commanded to be joined, and spread corruption on
					earth-these, the curse will be upon them, and they will have the Worst Home.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					God dispenses the provisions to whomever He wills, and restricts. And they
					delight in the worldly life; yet the worldly life, compared to the Hereafter,
					is only enjoyment.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "If only a miracle was sent down to him from his
					Lord." Say, "God leads astray whomever He wills, and He guides to Himself
					whoever repents."
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Those who believe, and whose hearts find comfort in the remembrance of God.
					Surely, it is in the remembrance of God that hearts find comfort."
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					For those who believe and do righteous deeds-for them is happiness and a
					beautiful return.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Thus We sent you among a community before which other communities have passed
					away, that you may recite to them what We revealed to you. Yet they deny the
					Benevolent One. Say, "He is my Lord; there is no god but He; in Him I trust,
					and to Him is my repentance."
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Even if there were a Quran, by which mountains could be set in motion, or by
					which the earth could be shattered, or by which the dead could be made to
					speak. In fact, every decision rests with God. Did the believers not give up
					and realize that had God willed, He would have guided all humanity? Disasters
					will continue to strike those who disbelieve, because of their deeds, or they
					fall near their homes, until God's promise comes true. God never breaks a
					promise.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Messengers before you were ridiculed, but I granted the disbelievers respite,
					and then I seized them. What a punishment it was!
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Is He who is watchful over the deeds of every soul? Yet they ascribe associates
					to God. Say, "Name them! Or are you informing Him of something on earth He does
					not know, or is it a show of words?" In fact, the scheming of those who
					disbelieve is made to appear good to them, and they are averted from the path.
					Whomever God misguides has no guide.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					There is for them torment in the worldly life, but the torment of the Hereafter
					is harsher. And they have no defender against God.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					The likeness of the Garden promised to the righteous: rivers flowing beneath
					it; its food is perpetual, and so is its shade. Such is the sequel for those
					who guard against evil, but the sequel of the disbelievers is the Fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Those to whom We gave the Scripture rejoice in what was revealed to you, while
					some factions reject parts of it. Say, "I am commanded to worship God, and to
					never associate anything with Him. To Him I invite, and to Him is my return."
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Thus We revealed it an Arabic code of law. Were you to follow their desires,
					after the knowledge that has come to you, you would have neither ally nor
					defender against God.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					We sent messengers before you, and We assigned for them wives and offspring. No
					messenger could bring a sign except with the permission of God. For every era
					is a scripture.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					God abolishes whatever He wills, and He affirms. With Him is the source of the
					Scripture.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Whether We show you some of what We have promised them, or We cause you to
					die-your duty is to inform, and Ours is the reckoning.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Do they not see how We deal with the earth, diminishing it at its edges? God
					judges; and nothing can hold back His judgment. And He is quick to settle
					accounts.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Those before them planned, but the entire plan is up to God. He knows what
					every soul earns. Those who disbelieve will know to whom the Ultimate Home is.
				-
			-
				Surah 13 - The Thunder: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "You are not a messenger." Say, "God is a sufficient
					witness between me and you, and whoever has knowledge of the Scripture."
				-
		-
			Surah 14 - Abraham
		-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Ra. A Scripture that We revealed to you, that you may bring humanity
					from darkness to light-with the permission of their Lord-to the path of the
					Almighty, the Praiseworthy.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					God-to whom belongs what is in the heavens and the earth. And woe to the
					disbelievers from a severe torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Those who prefer the present life to the Hereafter, and repel from the path of
					God, and seek to make it crooked-these are far astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					We never sent any messenger except in the language of his people, to make
					things clear for them. God leads astray whom He wills, and guides whom He
					wills. He is the Mighty, the Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					We sent Moses with Our signs: "Bring your people out of darkness into light,
					and remind them of the Days of God." In that are signs for every patient and
					thankful person."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Moses said to his people, "Remember God's blessings upon you, as He delivered
					you from the people of Pharaoh, who inflicted on you terrible suffering,
					slaughtering your sons while sparing your daughters. In that was a serious
					trial from your Lord."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And when your Lord proclaimed: "If you give thanks, I will grant you increase;
					but if you are ungrateful, My punishment is severe."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					And Moses said, "Even if you are ungrateful, together with everyone on
					earth-God is in no need, Worthy of Praise."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Has not the story reached you, of those before you, the people of Noah, and
					Aad, and Thamood-and those after them? None knows them except God. Their
					messengers came to them with the clear proofs, but they tried to silence them,
					and said, "We reject what you are sent with, and we are in serious doubt
					regarding what you are calling us to."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Their messengers said, "Is there any doubt about God, Maker of the heavens and
					the earth? He calls you to forgive you your sins, and to defer you until a
					stated term." They said, "You are only humans like us; you want to turn us away
					from what our ancestors worshiped; so bring us a clear proof."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Their messengers said to them, "We are only humans like you, but God favors
					whomever He wills from among His servants. We cannot possibly show you any
					proof, except by leave of God. In God let the faithful put their trust."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					"And why should we not trust in God, when He has guided us in our ways? We will
					persevere in the face of your persecution. And upon God the reliant should
					rely."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieved said to their messengers, "We will expel you from our
					land, unless you return to our religion." And their Lord inspired them: "We
					will destroy the wrongdoers."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					"And We will settle you in the land after them. That is for him who fears My
					Majesty, and fears My threats."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					And they prayed for victory, and every stubborn tyrant came to disappointment.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Beyond him lies Hell, and he will be given to drink putrid water.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					He will guzzle it, but he will not swallow it. Death will come at him from
					every direction, but he will not die. And beyond this is relentless suffering.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					The likeness of those who disbelieve in their Lord: their works are like ashes,
					in a fierce wind, on a stormy day. They have no control over anything they have
					earned. That is the utmost misguidance.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Do you not see that God created the heavens and the earth with truth? If He
					wills, He can do away with you, and bring a new creation.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And that is not difficult for God.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					They will emerge before God, altogether. The weak will say to those who were
					proud, "We were your followers, can you protect us at all against God's
					punishment?" They will say, "Had God guided us, we would have guided you. It is
					the same for us; whether we mourn, or are patient; there is no asylum for us."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And Satan will say, when the issue is settled, "God has promised you the
					promise of truth, and I promised you, but I failed you. I had no authority over
					you, except that I called you, and you answered me. So do not blame me, but
					blame yourselves. I cannot come to your aid, nor can you come to my aid. I
					reject your associating with me in the past. The wrongdoers will have a torment
					most painful."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					But those who believed and did good deeds will be admitted into gardens beneath
					which rivers flow, to remain therein forever, by leave of their Lord. Their
					greeting therein will be: "Peace."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Do you not see how God presents a parable? A good word is like a good tree-its
					root is firm, and its branches are in the sky.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					It yields its fruits every season by the will of its Lord. God presents the
					parables to the people, so that they may reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And the parable of a bad word is that of a bad tree-it is uprooted from the
					ground; it has no stability.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					God gives firmness to those who believe, with the firm word, in this life, and
					in the Hereafter. And God leads the wicked astray. God does whatever He wills.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Have you not seen those who exchanged the blessing of God with blasphemy, and
					landed their people into the house of perdition?
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Hell-they will roast in it. What a miserable settlement.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					And they set up rivals to God, in order to lead away from His path. Say, "Enjoy
					yourselves; your destination is the Fire."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Tell My servants who have believed to perform the prayers, and to give from
					what We have given them, secretly and publicly, before a Day comes in which
					there is neither trading nor friendship.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					God is He Who created the heavens and the earth, and sends down water from the
					sky, and with it produces fruits for your sustenance. And He committed the
					ships to your service, sailing through the sea by His command, and He committed
					the rivers to your service.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And He committed the sun and the moon to your service, both continuously
					pursuing their courses, and He committed the night and the day to your service.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And He has given you something of all what you asked. And if you were to count
					God's blessings, you would not be able to enumerate them. The human being is
					unfair and ungrateful.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Recall that Abraham said, "my Lord, make this land peaceful, and keep me and my
					sons from worshiping idols."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					"My Lord, they have led many people astray. Whoever follows me belongs with me;
					and whoever disobeys me-You are Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					"Our Lord, I have settled some of my offspring in a valley of no vegetation, by
					Your Sacred House, our Lord, so that they may perform the prayers. So make the
					hearts of some people incline towards them, and provide them with fruits, that
					they may be thankful."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					"Our Lord, You know what we conceal and what we reveal. And nothing is hidden
					from God, on earth or in the heaven."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					"Praise be to God, Who has given me, in my old age, Ishmael and Isaac. My Lord
					is the Hearer of Prayers."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					"My Lord, make me one who performs the prayer, and from my offspring. Our Lord,
					accept my supplication."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					"Our Lord, forgive me, and my parents, and the believers, on the Day the
					Reckoning takes place."
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Do not ever think that God is unaware of what the wrongdoers do. He only defers
					them until a Day when the sights stare.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Their necks outstretched, their heads upraised, their gaze unblinking, their
					hearts void.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					And warn mankind of the Day when the punishment will come upon them, and the
					wicked will say, "Our Lord, defer us for a little while, and we will answer
					Your call and follow the messengers." Did you not swear before that there will
					be no passing away for you?
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					And you inhabited the homes of those who wronged themselves, and it became
					clear to you how We dealt with them, and We cited for you the examples.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					They planned their plans, but their plans are known to God, even if their plans
					can eliminate mountains.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					Do not ever think that God will break His promise to His messengers. God is
					Strong, Able to Avenge.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					On the Day when the earth is changed into another earth, and the heavens, and
					they will emerge before God, the One, the Irresistible.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					On that Day, you will see the sinners bound together in chains.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Their garments made of tar, and the Fire covering their faces.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					That God may repay each soul according to what it has earned. God is Quick in
					reckoning.
				-
			-
				Surah 14 - Abraham: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					This is a proclamation for mankind, that they may be warned thereby, and know
					that He is One God, and that people of understanding may remember.
				-
		-
			Surah 15 - Al-Hijr
		-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Ra. These are the Verses of the Book; a Quran that makes things
					clear.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Perhaps those who disbelieve would like to become Muslims.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Leave them to eat, and enjoy, and be lulled by hope. They will find out.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					We have never destroyed a town unless it had a set time.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					No nation can bring its time forward, nor can they delay it.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And they said, "you who received the message, you are insane."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Why do you not bring us the angels, if you are truthful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					We do not send the angels down except with reason, and they will not be held
					back.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Surely We revealed the Message, and We will surely preserve it.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					We sent others before you, to the former communities.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					But no messenger came to them, but they ridiculed him.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Thus We slip it into the hearts of the guilty.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					They do not believe in it, though the ways of the ancients have passed away.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Even if We opened for them a gateway into the sky, and they began to ascend
					through it.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					They would still say, "Our eyes are hallucinating; in fact, we are people
					bewitched."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					We placed constellations in the sky, and made them beautiful to the beholders.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And We guarded them from every outcast devil.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Except one who steals a hearing, and is followed by a visible projectile.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					We spread the earth, and placed stabilizers in it, and in it We grew all things
					in proper measure.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And in it We created livelihoods for you, and for those for whom you are not
					the providers.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					There is not a thing but with Us are its stores, and We send it down only in
					precise measure.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					We send the fertilizing winds; and send down water from the sky, and give it to
					you to drink, and you are not the ones who store it.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					It is We who give life and cause death, and We are the Inheritors.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And We know those of you who go forward, and We know those who lag behind.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					It is your Lord who will gather them together. He is the Wise, the Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					We created the human being from clay, from molded mud.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					And the jinn We created before, from piercing fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Your Lord said to the angels, "I am creating a human being from clay, from
					molded mud."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					"When I have formed him, and breathed into him of My spirit, fall down
					prostrating before him."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					So the angels prostrated themselves, all together.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Except for Satan. He refused to be among those who prostrated themselves.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					He said, "Satan, what kept you from being among those who prostrated
					themselves?"
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					He said, "I am not about to prostrate myself before a human being, whom You
					created from clay, from molded mud."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					He said, "Then get out of here, for you are an outcast".
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					"And the curse will be upon you until the Day of Judgment."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, reprieve me until the Day they are resurrected."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					He said, "You are of those reprieved."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					"Until the Day of the time appointed."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, since You have lured me away, I will glamorize for them on
					earth, and I will lure them all away."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					"Except for Your sincere servants among them."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					He said, "This is a right way with Me."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					"Over My servants you have no authority, except for the sinners who follow
					you."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					And Hell is the meeting-place for them all.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					"It has seven doors; for each door is an assigned class."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					But the righteous will be in gardens with springs.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					"Enter it in peace and security."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And We will remove all ill-feelings from their hearts-brothers and sisters, on
					couches facing one another.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					No fatigue will ever touch them therein, nor will they be asked to leave it.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					Inform My servants that I am the Forgiver, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					And that My punishment is the painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					And inform them of the guests of Abraham.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					When they entered upon him, and said, "Peace." He said, "We are wary of you."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					They said, "Do not fear; we bring you good news of a boy endowed with
					knowledge."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					He said, "Do you bring me good news, when old age has overtaken me? What good
					news do you bring?"
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					They said, "We bring you good news in truth, so do not despair."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					He said, "And who despairs of his Lord's mercy but the lost?"
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					He said, "So what is your business, O envoys?"
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					They said, "We were sent to a sinful people."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					"Except for the family of Lot; we will save them all."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					"Except for his wife." We have determined that she will be of those who lag
					behind.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					And when the envoys came to the family of Lot.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					He said, "You are a people unknown to me."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					They said, "We bring you what they have doubts about."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					"We bring you the truth, and we are truthful."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					"Travel with your family at the dead of the night, and follow up behind them,
					and let none of you look back, and proceed as commanded."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					And We informed him of Our decree: the last remnant of these will be uprooted
					by early morning.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					And the people of the town came joyfully.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					He said, "These are my guests, so do not embarrass me."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					"And fear God, and do not disgrace me."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					They said, "Did we not forbid you from strangers?"
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					He said, "These are my daughters, if you must."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					By your life, they were blundering in their drunkenness.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					So the Blast struck them at sunrise.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					And We turned it upside down, and rained down upon them stones of baked clay.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					Surely in that are lessons for those who read signs.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					And it is on an existing road.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					Surely in that is a sign for the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					The people of the Woods were also wrongdoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					So We took revenge upon them. Both are clearly documented.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					The people of the Rock also rejected the messengers.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					We gave them Our revelations, but they turned away from them.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					They used to carve homes in the mountains, feeling secure.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					But the Blast struck them in the morning.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					All they had acquired was of no avail to them.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					We did not create the heavens and the earth, and what lies between them, except
					with truth. The Hour is coming, so forgive with gracious forgiveness.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					Your Lord is the All-Knowing Creator.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					We have given you seven of the pairs, and the Grand Quran.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					Do not extend your eyes towards what We have bestowed on some couples of them
					to enjoy, and do not grieve over them, and lower your wing to the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					And say, "I am the clear warner."
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					Just as We sent down to the separatists.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					Those who made the Quran obsolete.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					By your Lord, we will question them all.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					About what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					So proclaim openly what you are commanded, and turn away from the polytheists.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					We are enough for you against the mockers.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Those who set up another god with God. They will come to know.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					We are aware that your heart is strained by what they say.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					So glorify the praise of your Lord, and be among those who bow down.
				-
			-
				Surah 15 - Al-Hijr: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					And worship your Lord in order to attain certainty.
				-
		-
			Surah 16 - The Bee
		-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					The command of God has come, so do not rush it. Glory be to Him; exalted above
					what they associate.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					He sends down the angels with the Spirit by His command, upon whom He wills of
					His servants: "Give warning that there is no god but Me, and fear Me."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					He created the heavens and the earth with justice. He is exalted above the
					associations they attribute.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					He created the human being from a drop of fluid, yet he becomes an open
					adversary.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And the livestock-He created them for you. In them are warmth and benefits for
					you, and of them you eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And there is beauty in them for you, when you bring them home, and when you
					drive them to pasture.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And they carry your loads to territory you could not have reached without great
					hardship. Your Lord is Clement and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					And the horses, and the mules, and the donkeys-for you to ride, and for luxury.
					And He creates what you do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					It is for God to point out the paths, but some of them are flawed. Had He
					willed, He could have guided you all.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					It is He Who sends down for you from the sky water. From it is drink, and with
					it grows vegetation for grazing.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					And He produces for you grains with it, and olives, and date-palms, and grapes,
					and all kinds of fruits. Surely in that is a sign for people who think.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					And He regulated for you the night and the day; and the sun, and the moon, and
					the stars are disposed by His command. Surely in that are signs for people who
					ponder.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And whatsoever He created for you on earth is of diverse colors. Surely in that
					is a sign for people who are mindful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					And it is He who made the sea to serve you, that you may eat from it tender
					meat, and extract from it ornaments that you wear. And you see the ships
					plowing through it, as you seek His bounties, so that you may give thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					And he cast mountains on the earth, lest it shifts with you; and rivers, and
					roads, so that you may be guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					And landmarks. And by the stars they guide themselves.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					Is He who creates like him who does not create? Will you not take a lesson?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And if you tried to enumerate the favors of God, you will not be able to count
					them. God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					And God knows what you hide and what you disclose.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Those they invoke besides God create nothing, but are themselves created.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					They are dead, not alive; and they do not know when they will be resurrected.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Your God is one God. As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, their
					hearts are in denial, and they are arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Without a doubt, God knows what they conceal and what they reveal. He does not
					like the arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And when it is said to them, "What has your Lord sent down?" They say, "Legends
					of the ancients."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					So let them carry their loads complete on the Day of Resurrection, and some of
					the loads of those they misguided without knowledge. Evil is what they carry.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Those before them also schemed, but God took their structures from the
					foundations, and the roof caved in on them. The punishment came at them from
					where they did not perceive.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Then, on the Day of Resurrection, He will disgrace them, and say, "Where are My
					associates for whose sake you used to dispute?" Those who were given knowledge
					will say, "Today shame and misery are upon the disbelievers."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Those wronging their souls while the angels are taking them away-they will
					propose peace: "We did no wrong." Yes you did. God is aware of what you used to
					do."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Enter the gates of Hell, to dwell therein forever. Miserable is the residence
					of the arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					And it will be said to those who maintained piety, "What has your Lord
					revealed?" They will say, "Goodness." To those who do good in this world is
					goodness, and the Home of the Hereafter is even better. How wonderful is the
					residence of the pious.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					The Gardens of Perpetuity, which they will enter, beneath which rivers flow,
					where they will have whatever they desire. Thus God rewards the pious.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Those who are in a wholesome state when the angels take them-will say, "Peace
					be upon you; enter Paradise, for what you used to do."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Are they but waiting for the angels to come to them, or for the command of your
					Lord to arrive? Those before them did likewise. God did not wrong them, but
					they used to wrong their own souls.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					So the evils of their deeds assailed them, and what they used to ridicule
					engulfed them.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					The idolaters say, "Had God willed, we would not have worshiped anything
					besides Him, neither us, nor our ancestors, nor would we have prohibited
					anything besides His prohibitions." Those before them did likewise. Are the
					messengers responsible for anything but clear communication?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					To every community We sent a messenger: "Worship God, and avoid idolatry." Some
					of them God guided, while others deserved misguidance. So travel through the
					earth, and see what the fate of the deniers was.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Even though you may be concerned about their guidance, God does not guide those
					who misguide. And they will have no saviors.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					And they swear by God with their most solemn oaths, "God will not resurrect
					anyone who dies." Yes indeed, it is a promise binding on Him, but most people
					do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					To clarify for them what they differed about, and for the faithless to know
					that they were liars.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					When We intend for something to happen, We say to it, "Be," and it becomes.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Those who emigrate for God's sake after being persecuted, We will settle them
					in a good place in this world; but the reward of the Hereafter is greater, if
					they only knew.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Those who endure patiently, and in their Lord they put their trust.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					We did not send before you except men whom We inspired. So ask the people of
					knowledge, if you do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					With the clarifications and the scriptures. And We revealed to you the
					Reminder, that you may clarify to the people what was revealed to them, and
					that they may reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					Do those who scheme evils feel secure that God will not cause the earth to cave
					in with them, or that the punishment will not come upon them from where they do
					not perceive?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Or that He will not seize them during their activities? And they will not be
					able to prevent it.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					Or that He will not seize them while in dread? Your Lord is Gentle and
					Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					Have they not observed what God has created? Their shadows revolve from the
					right and the left, bowing to God as they shrink away.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					To God bows down everything in the heavens and everything on earth-every living
					creature, and the angels, and without being proud.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					They fear their Lord above them, and they do what they are commanded.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					God has said: "Do not take two gods; He is only One God; so fear only Me."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					To Him belongs everything in the heavens and the earth; and to Him obedience is
					due always. Do you, then, fear anyone other than God?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					Whatever blessing you have is from God. And when harm touches you, it is to Him
					that you groan.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					But when He lifts the harm from you, some of you associate others with their
					Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					To show ingratitude for what We have given them. Enjoy yourselves. You will
					soon know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					And they allocate, to something they do not know, a share of what We have
					provided for them. By God, you will be questioned about what you have been
					inventing.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					And they attribute to God daughters-exalted is He-and for themselves what they
					desire.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					And when one of them is given news of a female infant, his face darkens, and he
					chokes with grief.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					He hides from the people because of the bad news given to him. Shall he keep it
					in humiliation, or bury it in the dust? Evil is the decision they make.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					Those who do not believe in the Hereafter set a bad example, while God sets the
					Highest Example. He is the Mighty, the Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					If God were to hold mankind for their injustices, He would not leave upon it a
					single creature, but He postpones them until an appointed time. Then, when
					their time arrives, they will not delay it by one hour, nor will they advance
					it.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					And they attribute to God what they themselves dislike, while their tongues
					utter the lie that theirs is the goodness. Without a doubt, for them is the
					Fire, and they will be neglected.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					By God, We sent messengers to communities before you, but Satan made their
					deeds appear alluring to them. He is their master today, and they will have a
					painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					We revealed to you the Scripture only to clarify for them what they differ
					about, and guidance and mercy for people who believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					God sends down water from the sky, with which He revives the earth after its
					death. In this is a sign for people who listen.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					And there is a lesson for you in cattle: We give you a drink from their
					bellies, from between waste and blood, pure milk, refreshing to the drinkers.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					And from the fruits of date-palms and grapevines, you derive sugar and
					wholesome food. In this is a sign for people who understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					And your Lord inspired the bee: "Set up hives in the mountains, and in the
					trees, and in what they construct."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					Then eat of all the fruits, and go along the pathways of your Lord, with
					precision. From their bellies emerges a fluid of diverse colors, containing
					healing for the people. Surely in this is a sign for people who reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					God created you; then He takes you away. Some of you will be brought back to
					the worst age, so that he will no longer know anything, after having acquired
					knowledge. God is Omniscient and Omnipotent.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					God has favored some of you over others in livelihood. Those who are favored
					would not give their properties to their servants, to the extent of making them
					partners in it. Will they then renounce God's blessings?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					God has given you mates from among yourselves; and has produced for you, from
					your mates, children and grandchildren; and has provided you with good things.
					Will they then believe in falsehood, and refuse God's favors?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					And yet they serve besides God what possesses no provisions for them in the
					heavens, nor on earth, nor are they capable.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					So do not cite the examples for God. God knows, and you do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					God cites the example of a bonded slave, who has no power over anything; and
					someone to whom We have given plentiful provision, from which he gives secretly
					and openly. Are they equal in comparison? All praise belongs to God, but most
					of them do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					And God cites the example of two men: one of them dumb, unable to do anything,
					and is a burden on his master; whichever way he directs him, he achieves
					nothing good. Is he equal to him who commands justice, and is on a straight
					path?
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					To God belongs the unseen of the heavens and the earth. The coming of the Hour
					is only as the twinkling of the eye, or even nearer. God has power over
					everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					God brought you out of your mothers' wombs, not knowing anything; and He gave
					you the hearing, and the eyesight, and the brains; that you may give thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					Have they not seen the birds, flying in the midst of the sky? None sustains
					them except God. In this are signs for people who believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And God has given you in your homes habitats for you, and has provided for you
					out of the hides of livestock portable homes for you, so you can use them when
					you travel, and when you camp; and from their wool, and fur, and hair,
					furnishings and comfort for a while.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					And God has made for you shade out of what He has created, and has given you
					resorts in the mountains, and has given you garments to protect you from the
					heat, and garments to protect you from your violence. Thus He completes His
					blessings upon you, so that you may submit.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					But if they turn away, your only duty is clear communication.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					They recognize God's blessing, but then deny it, as most of them are
					ungrateful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					On the Day when We raise up a witness from every community-those who
					disbelieved will not be permitted, nor will they be excused.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					When those who did wrong see the punishment, it will not be lightened for them,
					nor will they be reprieved.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					And when the idolaters see their associates, they will say, "Our Lord, these
					are our associates whom we used to invoke besides You." They will strike back
					at them with the saying, "Surely you are liars."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					On that Day they will offer their submission to God, and what they had invented
					will abandon them.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve and obstruct from God's path-We will add punishment to
					their punishment, on account of the mischief they used to make.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					On the Day when We raise in every community a witness against them, from among
					them, and bring you as a witness against these. We have revealed to you the
					Book, as an explanation of all things, and guidance, and mercy and good news
					for those who submit.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					God commands justice, and goodness, and generosity towards relatives. And He
					forbids immorality, and injustice, and oppression. He advises you, so that you
					may take heed.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					Fulfill God's covenant when you make a covenant, and do not break your oaths
					after ratifying them. You have made God your guarantor, and God knows what you
					do.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					And do not be like her who unravels her yarn, breaking it into pieces, after
					she has spun it strongly. Nor use your oaths as means of deception among you,
					because one community is more prosperous than another. God is testing you
					thereby. On the Day of Resurrection, He will make clear to you everything you
					had disputed about.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					Had God willed, He would have made you one congregation, but He leaves astray
					whom He wills, and He guides whom He wills. And you will surely be questioned
					about what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					And do not use your oaths to deceive one another, so that a foot may not slip
					after being firm, and you taste misery because you hindered from God's path,
					and incur a terrible torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					And do not exchange God's covenant for a small price. What is with God is
					better for you, if you only knew.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					What you have runs out, but what is with God remains. We will reward those who
					are patient according to the best of their deeds.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					Whoever works righteousness, whether male or female, while being a believer, We
					will grant him a good life-and We will reward them according to the best of
					what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					When you read the Quran, seek refuge with God from Satan the outcast.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					He has no authority over those who believe and trust in their Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					His authority is only over those who follow him, and those who associate others
					with Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					When We substitute a verse in place of another verse-and God knows best what He
					reveals-they say, "You are an impostor." But most of them do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					Say, "The Holy Spirit has brought it down from your Lord, truthfully, in order
					to stabilize those who believe, and as guidance and good news for those who
					submit."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					We are well aware that they say, "It is a human being who is teaching him." But
					the tongue of him they allude to is foreign, while this is a clear Arabic
					tongue.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					Those who do not believe in God's revelations-God will not guide them, and for
					them is a painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					It is those who do not believe in God's revelations who fabricate falsehood.
					These are the liars.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					Whoever renounces faith in God after having believed-except for someone who is
					compelled, while his heart rests securely in faith-but whoever willingly opens
					up his heart to disbelief-upon them falls wrath from God, and for them is a
					tremendous torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					That is because they have preferred the worldly life to the Hereafter, and
					because God does not guide the people who refuse.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					It is they whom God has sealed their hearts, and their hearing, and their
					sight. It is they who are the heedless.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					There is no doubt that in the Hereafter they will be the losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					But then your Lord-for those who emigrated after being persecuted, then
					struggled and persevered-your Lord thereafter is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					On the Day when every soul will come pleading for itself, and every soul will
					be paid in full for what it has done, and they will not be wronged.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 112
			-
				-
					And God cites the example of a town that was secure and peaceful, with its
					livelihood coming to it abundantly from every direction. But then it turned
					unappreciative of God's blessings, so God made it taste the robe of hunger and
					fear, because of what they used to craft.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 113
			-
				-
					A messenger from among them had come to them, but they denounced him, so the
					punishment seized them in the midst of their wrongdoing.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 114
			-
				-
					Eat of the lawful and good things God has provided for you, and be thankful for
					God's blessings, if it is Him that you serve.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 115
			-
				-
					He has forbidden you carrion, and blood, and the flesh of swine, and anything
					consecrated to other than God. But if anyone is compelled by necessity, without
					being deliberate or malicious, then God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 116
			-
				-
					And do not say of falsehood asserted by your tongues, "This is lawful, and this
					is unlawful," in order to invent lies and attribute them to God. Those who
					invent lies and attribute them to God will not succeed.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 117
			-
				-
					A brief enjoyment-then they will have a painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 118
			-
				-
					For those who are Jews, We have prohibited what We related to you before. We
					did not wrong them, but they used to wrong their own selves.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 119
			-
				-
					But towards those who do wrongs in ignorance, and then repent afterwards and
					reform, your Lord thereafter is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 120
			-
				-
					Abraham was an exemplary leader, devoted to God, a monotheist, and was not of
					the polytheists.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 121
			-
				-
					Thankful for His blessings. He chose him, and guided him to a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 122
			-
				-
					And We gave him goodness in this world, and in the Hereafter he will be among
					the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 123
			-
				-
					Then We inspired you: "Follow the religion of Abraham, the Monotheist. He was
					not an idol-worshiper."
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 124
			-
				-
					The Sabbath was decreed only for those who differed about it. Your Lord will
					judge between them on the Day of Resurrection regarding their differences.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 125
			-
				-
					Invite to the way of your Lord with wisdom and good advice, and debate with
					them in the most dignified manner. Your Lord is aware of those who stray from
					His path, and He is aware of those who are guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 126
			-
				-
					If you were to retaliate, retaliate to the same degree as the injury done to
					you. But if you resort to patience-it is better for the patient.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 127
			-
				-
					So be patient. Your patience is solely from God. And do not grieve over them,
					and do not be stressed by their schemes.
				-
			-
				Surah 16 - The Bee: Ayah 128
			-
				-
					God is with those who are righteous and those who are virtuous.
				-
		-
			Surah 17 - Israel
		-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Glory to Him who journeyed His servant by night, from the Sacred Mosque, to the
					Farthest Mosque, whose precincts We have blessed, in order to show him of Our
					wonders. He is the Listener, the Beholder.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					And We gave Moses the Scripture, and made it a guide for the Children of
					Israel: Take none for protector other than Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					The descendants of those We carried with Noah. He was an appreciative servant.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					And We conveyed to the Children of Israel in the Scripture: You will commit
					evil on earth twice, and you will rise to a great height.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					When the first of the two promises came true, We sent against you servants of
					Ours, possessing great might, and they ransacked your homes. It was a promise
					fulfilled.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Then We gave you back your turn against them, and supplied you with wealth and
					children, and made you more numerous.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					If you work righteousness, you work righteousness for yourselves; and if you
					commit evil, you do so against yourselves. Then, when the second promise comes
					true, they will make your faces filled with sorrow, and enter the Temple as
					they entered it the first time, and utterly destroy all that falls into their
					power.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Perhaps your Lord will have mercy on you. But if you revert, We will revert. We
					have made Hell a prison for the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					This Quran guides to what is most upright; and it gives good news to the
					believers who do good deeds, that they will have a great reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					And those who do not believe in the Hereafter-We have prepared for them a
					painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					The human being prays for evil as he prays for good. The human being is very
					hasty.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					We have made the night and the day two wonders. We erased the wonder of the
					night, and made the wonder of the day revealing, that you may seek bounty from
					your Lord, and know the number of years, and the calculation. We have explained
					all things in detail.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					For every person We have attached his fate to his neck. And on the Day of
					Resurrection, We will bring out for him a book which he will find spread open.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					"Read your book; today there will be none but yourself to call you to account."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Whoever is guided-is guided for his own good. And whoever goes astray-goes
					astray to his detriment. No burdened soul carries the burdens of another, nor
					do We ever punish until We have sent a messenger.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					When We decide to destroy a town, We command its affluent ones, they transgress
					in it, so the word becomes justified against it, and We destroy it completely.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					How many generations have We destroyed after Noah? Your Lord is sufficient as
					Knower and Beholder of the sins of his servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Whoever desires the fleeting life, We expedite for him what We decide to give
					him, to whomever We desire. Then We consign him to Hell, where he will roast,
					condemned and defeated.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					But whoever desires the Hereafter, and pursues it as it should be pursued,
					while he is a believer; these-their effort will be appreciated.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					To all-these and those-We extend from the gifts of your Lord. The gifts of your
					Lord are not restricted.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					See how We have favored some of them over others; yet the Hereafter is greater
					in ranks, and greater in favors.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Do not set up another god with God, lest you become condemned and damned.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Your Lord has commanded that you worship none but Him, and that you be good to
					your parents. If either of them or both of them reach old age with you, do not
					say to them a word of disrespect, nor scold them, but say to them kind words.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And lower to them the wing of humility, out of mercy, and say, "My Lord, have
					mercy on them, as they raised me when I was a child."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Your Lord knows best what is in your minds. If you are righteous-He is
					Forgiving to the obedient.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And give the relative his rights, and the poor, and the wayfarer, and do not
					squander wastefully.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					The extravagant are brethren of the devils, and the devil is ever ungrateful to
					his Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					But if you turn away from them, seeking mercy from your Lord which you hope
					for, then say to them words of comfort.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And do not keep your hand tied to your neck, nor spread it out fully, lest you
					end up liable and regretful.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Your Lord expands the provision for whomever He wills, and restricts it. He is
					fully Informed, Observant of His servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					And do not kill your children for fear of poverty. We provide for them, and for
					you. Killing them is a grave sin.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And do not come near adultery. It is immoral, and an evil way.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And do not kill the soul which God has made sacred, except in the course of
					justice. If someone is killed unjustly, We have given his next of kin certain
					authority. But he should not be excessive in killing, for he will be supported.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And do not go near the orphan's property, except with the best of intentions,
					until he has reached his maturity. And honor your pledge, because the pledge
					involves responsibility.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					And give full measure when you measure, and weigh with accurate scales. That is
					fair, and the best determination.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					And do not occupy yourself with what you have no knowledge of. The hearing, and
					the sight, and the brains-all these will be questioned.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					And do not walk proudly on earth. You can neither pierce the earth, nor can you
					match the mountains in height.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					The evil of all these is disliked by your Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					That is some of the wisdom your Lord has revealed to you. Do not set up with
					God another god, or else you will be thrown in Hell, rebuked and banished.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Has your Lord favored you with sons, while choosing for Himself daughters from
					among the angels? You are indeed saying a terrible thing.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					We have explained in this Quran in various ways, that they may remember, but it
					only adds to their rebellion.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Say, "If there were other gods with Him, as they say, they would have sought a
					way to the Lord of the Throne."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Be He glorified. He is exalted, far above what they say.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Praising Him are the seven heavens, and the earth, and everyone in them. There
					is not a thing that does not glorify Him with praise, but you do not understand
					their praises. He is indeed Forbearing and Forgiving.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					When you read the Quran, We place between you and those who do not believe in
					the Hereafter an invisible barrier.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					And We drape veils over their hearts, preventing them from understanding it,
					and heaviness in their ears. And when you mention your Lord alone in the Quran,
					they turn their backs in aversion.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					We know well what they listen to, when they listen to you, as they conspire,
					when the wrongdoers say, "You only follow a man bewitched."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					Note what they compared you to. They are lost, and unable to find a way.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					And they say, "When we have become bones and fragments, shall we really be
					resurrected as a new creation?"
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Say, "Even if you become rocks or iron.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					Or some substance, which, in your minds, is even harder." Then they will say,
					"Who will restore us?" Say, "The One who originated you the first time." Then
					they will nod their heads at you, and say, "When will it be?" Say, "Perhaps it
					will be soon."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					On the Day when He calls you, you will respond with His praise, and you will
					realize that you stayed only a little.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					Tell My servants to say what is best. Satan sows discord among them. Satan is
					to man an open enemy.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Your Lord knows you best. If He wills, He will have mercy on you; and if He
					wills, He will punish you. We did not send you as their advocate.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					Your Lord knows well everyone in the heavens and the earth. We have given some
					prophets advantage over others; and to David We gave the Psalms.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					Say, "Call upon those you claim besides Him. They have no power to relieve your
					adversity, nor can they change it."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Those they call upon are themselves seeking means of access to their Lord,
					vying to be nearer, and hoping for His mercy, and fearing His punishment. The
					punishment of your Lord is to be dreaded.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					There is no city but We will destroy before the Day of Resurrection, or punish
					it with a severe punishment. This is inscribed in the Book.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Nothing prevents Us from sending miraculous signs, except that the ancients
					called them lies. We gave Thamood the she-camel, a visible sign, but they
					mistreated her. We do not send the signs except to instill reverence.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					We said to you that your Lord encompasses humanity. We did not make the vision
					We showed you, except as a test for the people, and the tree cursed in the
					Quran. We frighten them, but that only increases their defiance.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					When We said to the angels, "Bow down before Adam," they bowed down, except for
					Satan. He said, "Shall I bow down before someone You created from mud?"
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					He said, "Do You see this one whom You have honored more than me? If You
					reprieve me until the Day of Resurrection, I will bring his descendants under
					my sway, except for a few."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					He said, "Begone! Whoever of them follows you-Hell is your reward, an ample
					reward."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					"And entice whomever of them you can with your voice, and rally against them
					your cavalry and your infantry, and share with them in wealth and children, and
					make promises to them." But Satan promises them nothing but delusion.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					"As for My devotees, you have no authority over them." Your Lord is an adequate
					Guardian.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					Your Lord is He who propels for you the ships at sea, that you may seek of His
					bounty. He is towards you Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					When harm afflicts you at sea, those you pray to vanish, except for Him. But
					when He saves you to land, you turn away. The human being is ever thankless.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					Are you confident that He will not cause a track of land to cave in beneath
					you, or unleash a tornado against you, and then you find no protector?
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					Or are you confident that He will not return you to it once again, and unleash
					a hurricane against you, and drown you for your ingratitude? Then you will find
					no helper against Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					We have honored the Children of Adam, and carried them on land and sea, and
					provided them with good things, and greatly favored them over many of those We
					created.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					On the Day when We call every people with their leader. Whoever is given his
					record in his right hand-these will read their record, and they will not be
					wronged one bit.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					But whoever is blind in this, he will be blind in the Hereafter, and further
					astray from the way.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					They almost lured you away from what We have revealed to you, so that you would
					invent something else in Our name. In that case, they would have taken you for
					a friend.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					Had We not given you stability, you might have inclined towards them a little.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					Then We would have made you taste double in life, and double at death; then you
					would have found for yourself no helper against Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					They almost provoked you, to expel you from the land. In that case, they would
					not have lasted after you, except briefly.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					The tradition of the messengers We sent before you-you will find no change in
					Our rules.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					Perform the prayer at the decline of the sun, until the darkness of the night;
					and the Quran at dawn. The Quran at dawn is witnessed.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					And keep vigil with it during parts of the night, as an extra prayer. Perhaps
					your Lord will raise you to a laudable position.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And say, "My Lord, lead me in through an entry of truth, and lead me out
					through an exit of truth, and grant me from You a supporting power."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					And say, "The truth has come, and falsehood has withered away; for falsehood is
					bound to wither away."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					We send down in the Quran healing and mercy for the believers, but it increases
					the wrongdoers only in loss.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					When We bless the human being, he turns away and distances himself. But when
					adversity touches him, he is in despair.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					Say, "Each does according to his disposition. Your Lord knows best who is
					better guided in the way."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					And they ask you about the Spirit. Say, "The Spirit belongs to the domain of my
					Lord; and you were given only little knowledge."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					If We willed, We could take away what We revealed to you. Then you will find
					for yourself no protecting guardian against Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					Except through a mercy from your Lord. His favors upon you have been great.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					Say, "If mankind and jinn came together to produce the like of this Quran, they
					could never produce the like of it, even if they backed up one another."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					We have displayed for mankind in this Quran every kind of similitude, but most
					people insist on denying the truth.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					And they said, "We will not believe in you unless you make a spring burst from
					the ground for us.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					Or you have a garden of palms and vines; then cause rivers to gush pouring
					through them.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					Or make the sky fall on us in pieces, as you claim, or bring God and the angels
					before us.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					Or you possess a house of gold. Or you ascend into the sky. Even then, we will
					not believe in your ascension, unless you bring down for us a book that we can
					read." Say, "Glory be to my Lord. Am I anything but a human messenger?"
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					Nothing prevented the people from believing, when guidance has come to them,
					except that they said, "Did God send a human messenger?"
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					Say, "If there were angels on earth, walking around in peace, We would have
					sent down to them from heaven an angel messenger."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Say, "God is enough witness between you and me. He is fully aware of His
					servants, and He sees them well."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					Whomever God guides is the guided one. And whomever He leaves astray-for them
					you will find no protectors apart from Him. And We will gather them on the Day
					of Resurrection, on their faces, blind, dumb, and deaf. Their abode is Hell;
					whenever it abates, We intensify the blaze for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					This is their repayment for having blasphemed against Our revelations, and
					having said, "Shall we, when we have become bones and fragments, be resurrected
					as a new creation?"
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					Do they not consider that God, Who created the heavens and the earth, is Able
					to create the likes of them? He has assigned for them a term, in which there is
					no doubt. But the wrongdoers persist in denying the truth.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					Say, "If you possessed the treasuries of my Lord's mercy, you would have
					withheld them for fear of spending." The human being has always been stingy.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					We gave Moses nine clear signs-ask the Children of Israel. When he went to
					them, Pharaoh said to him, "I think that you, Moses, are bewitched."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					He said, "You know that none sent these down except the Lord of the heavens and
					the earth-eye openers; and I think that you, Pharaoh, are doomed."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					He resolved to scare them off the land, but We drowned him, and those with him,
					altogether.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					After him, We said to the Children of Israel, "Inhabit the land, and when the
					promise of the Hereafter arrives, We will bring you all together."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					With the truth We sent it down, and with the truth it descended. We sent you
					only as a bearer of good news and a warner.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					A Quran which We unfolded gradually, that you may recite to the people over
					time. And We revealed it in stages.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					Say, "Believe in it, or do not believe." Those who were given knowledge before
					it, when it is recited to them, they fall to their chins, prostrating.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					And they say, "Glory to our Lord. The promise of our Lord is fulfilled."
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					And they fall to their chins, weeping, and it adds to their humility.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					Say, "Call Him God, or call Him the Most Merciful. Whichever name you use, to
					Him belong the Best Names." And be neither loud in your prayer, nor silent in
					it, but follow a course in between.
				-
			-
				Surah 17 - Israel: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					And say, "Praise be to God, who has not begotten a son, nor has He a partner in
					sovereignty, nor has He an ally out of weakness, and glorify Him constantly."
				-
		-
			Surah 18 - The Cave
		-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Praise be to God, who revealed the Book to His servant, and allowed in it no
					distortion.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Valuable-to warn of severe punishment from Himself; and to deliver good news to
					the believers who do righteous deeds, that they will have an excellent reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					In which they will abide forever.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					And to warn those who say, "God has begotten a son."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					They have no knowledge of this, nor did their forefathers. Grave is the word
					that comes out of their mouths. They say nothing but a lie.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Perhaps you may destroy yourself with grief, chasing after them, if they do not
					believe in this information.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					We made what is upon the earth an ornament for it, to test them as to which of
					them is best in conduct.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					And We will turn what is on it into barren waste.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Did you know that the People of the Cave and the Inscription were of Our
					wondrous signs?
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					When the youths took shelter in the cave, they said, "Our Lord, give us mercy
					from Yourself, and bless our affair with guidance."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Then We sealed their ears in the cave for a number of years.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Then We awakened them to know which of the two groups could better calculate
					the length of their stay.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					We relate to you their story in truth. They were youths who believed in their
					Lord, and We increased them in guidance.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					And We strengthened their hearts, when they stood up and said, "Our Lord is the
					Lord of the heavens and the earth; we will not call on any god besides Him, for
					then we would have spoken an outrage."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					"These people, our people, have taken to themselves gods other than Him. Why do
					they not bring a clear proof concerning them? Who, then, does greater wrong
					than he who invents lies and attributes them to God?"
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					"Now that you have withdrawn from them, and from what they worship besides God,
					take shelter in the cave. And your Lord will unfold His mercy for you, and will
					set your affair towards ease."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					You would have seen the sun, when it rose, veering away from their cave towards
					the right, and when it sets, moving away from them to the left, as they lay in
					the midst of the cave. That was one of God's wonders. He whom God guides is
					truly guided; but he whom He misguides, for him you will find no directing
					friend.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					You would think them awake, although they were asleep. And We turned them over
					to the right, and to the left, with their dog stretching its paws across the
					threshold. Had you looked at them, you would have turned away from them in
					flight, and been filled with fear of them.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Even so, We awakened them, so that they may ask one another. A speaker among
					them said, "How long have you stayed?" They said, "We have stayed a day, or
					part of a day." They said, "Your Lord knows best how long you have stayed."
					"Send one of you to the city, with this money of yours, and let him see which
					food is most suitable, and let him bring you some provision thereof. And let
					him be gentle, and let no one become aware of you."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					"If they discover you, they will stone you, or force you back into their
					religion; then you will never be saved."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					So it was, that We caused them to be discovered, that they would know that the
					promise of God is true, and that of the Hour there is no doubt. As they were
					disputing their case among themselves, they said, "Build over them a building."
					Their Lord knows best about them. Those who prevailed over their case said, "We
					will set up over them a place of worship."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					They will say, "Three, and their fourth being their dog." And they will say,
					"Five, and their sixth being their dog," guessing at the unknown. And they will
					say, "Seven, and their eighth being their dog." Say, "My Lord knows best their
					number." None knows them except a few. So do not argue concerning them except
					with an obvious argument, and do not consult any of them about them.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					And never say about anything, "I will do that tomorrow."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Without saying, "If God wills." And remember your Lord if you forget, and say,
					"Perhaps my Lord will guide me to nearer than this in integrity."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					And they stayed in their cave for three hundred years, adding nine.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Say, "God knows best how long they stayed." His is the mystery of the heavens
					and the earth. By Him you see and hear. They have no guardian apart from Him,
					and He shares His Sovereignty with no one.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					And recite what was revealed to you from the Book of your Lord. There is no
					changing His words, and you will find no refuge except in Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And content yourself with those who pray to their Lord morning and evening,
					desiring His Presence. And do not turn your eyes away from them, desiring the
					glitter of this world. And do not obey him whose heart We have made heedless of
					Our remembrance-so he follows his own desires-and his priorities are confused.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And say, "The truth is from your Lord. Whoever wills-let him believe. And
					whoever wills-let him disbelieve". We have prepared for the unjust a Fire,
					whose curtains will hem them in. And when they cry for relief, they will be
					relieved with water like molten brass, which scalds the faces. What a miserable
					drink, and what a terrible place.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					As for those who believe and lead a righteous life-We will not waste the reward
					of those who work righteousness.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					These will have the Gardens of Eden, beneath which rivers flow. Reclining on
					comfortable furnishings, they will be adorned with bracelets of gold, and will
					wear green garments of silk and brocade. What a wonderful reward, and what an
					excellent resting-place.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And cite for them the parable of two men. To one of them We gave two gardens of
					vine, and We surrounded them with palm-trees, and We placed between them crops.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Both gardens produced their harvest in full, and suffered no loss. And We made
					a river flow through them.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And thus he had abundant fruits. He said to his friend, as he conversed with
					him, "I am wealthier than you, and greater in manpower."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					And he entered his garden, wronging himself. He said, "I do not think this will
					ever perish."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					"And I do not think the Hour is coming. And even if I am returned to my Lord, I
					will find something better than this in return."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					His friend said to him, as he conversed with him, "Are you being ungrateful to
					Him who created you from dust, then from a sperm-drop, then evolved you into a
					man?
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					But as for me, He is God, my Lord, and I never associate with my Lord anyone.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					When you entered your garden, why did you not say, "As God wills; there is no
					power except through God"? Although you see me inferior to you in wealth and
					children.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Perhaps my Lord will give me something better than your garden, and release
					upon it thunderbolts from the sky, so it becomes barren waste.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Or its water will sink into the ground, and you will be unable to draw it."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					And ruin closed in on his crops, and so he began wringing his hands over what
					he had invested in it, as it lays fallen upon its trellises. And he was saying,
					"I wish I never associated anyone with my Lord."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					He had no faction to help him besides God, and he was helpless.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					That is because authority belongs to God, the True. He is Best in rewarding,
					and Best in requiting.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					And cite for them the parable of the present life: it is like water that We
					send down from the sky; the plants of the earth absorb it; but then it becomes
					debris, scattered by the wind. God has absolute power over everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Wealth and children are the adornments of the present life. But the things that
					last, the virtuous deeds, are better with your Lord for reward, and better for
					hope.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					On the Day when We set the mountains in motion; and you see the earth emerging;
					and We gather them together, and leave none of them behind.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					They will be presented before your Lord in a row. "You have come to Us as We
					created you the first time. Although you claimed We would not set a meeting for
					you."
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					And the book will be placed, and you will see the sinners fearful of its
					contents. And they will say, "Woe to us! What is with this book that leaves
					nothing, small or big, but it has enumerated it?" They will find everything
					they had done present. Your Lord does not wrong anyone.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					We said to the angels, "Bow down to Adam." So they bowed down, except for
					Satan. He was of the jinn, and he defied the command of his Lord. Will you take
					him and his offspring as lords instead of Me, when they are an enemy to you?
					Evil is the exchange for the wrongdoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					I did not call them to witness the creation of the heavens and the earth, nor
					their own creation; and I do not take the misleaders for assistants.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					On the Day when He will say, "Call on My partners whom you have claimed." They
					will call on them, but they will not answer them. And We will place between
					them a barrier.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					And the sinners will see the Fire, and will realize that they will tumble into
					it. They will find no deliverance from it.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					We have elaborated in this Quran for the people every kind of example, but the
					human being is a most argumentative being.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					What prevented people from accepting faith, when guidance has come to them, and
					from seeking their Lord's forgiveness? Unless they are waiting for the
					precedent of the ancients to befall them, or to have the punishment come upon
					them face to face.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					We send the messengers only as deliverers of good news and warners. Those who
					disbelieve argue with false argument, in order to defeat the truth thereby.
					They take My Verses, and the warnings, for a joke.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Who does greater wrong than he, who, when reminded of his Lord's revelations,
					turns away from them, and forgets what his hands have put forward? We have
					placed coverings over their hearts, lest they understand it, and heaviness in
					their ears. And if you call them to guidance, they will not be guided, ever.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Your Lord is the Forgiver, Possessor of Mercy. Were He to call them to account
					for what they have earned, He would have hastened the punishment for them. But
					they have an appointment from which they will find no escape.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					And these towns-We destroyed them when they committed injustices, and We set
					for their destruction an appointed time.
				-
			-
				Surah 18 - The Cave: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					Recall when Moses said to his servant, "I will not give up until I reach the
					junction of the two rivers, even if it takes me years."
				-
			-
