					decree of your Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					Then We will rescue those who were devout, and leave the wrongdoers in it, on
					their knees.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					When Our clear revelations are recited to them, those who disbelieve say to
					those who believe, "Which of the two parties is better in position, and
					superior in influence?"
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					How many a generation have We destroyed before them, who surpassed them in
					riches and splendor?
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					Say, "Whoever is in error, the Most Merciful will lead him on." Until, when
					they see what they were promised-either the punishment, or the Hour. Then they
					will know who was in worse position and weaker in forces.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					God increases in guidance those who accept guidance. And the things that
					endure-the righteous deeds-have the best reward with your Lord, and the best
					outcome.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					Have you seen him who denied Our revelations, and said, "I will be given wealth
					and children"?
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					Did he look into the future, or did he receive a promise from the Most
					Merciful?
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					No indeed! We will write what he says, and will keep extending the agony for
					him.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					Then We will inherit from him what he speaks of, and he will come to Us alone.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					And they took, besides God, other gods, to be for them a source of strength.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					By no means! They will reject their worship of them, and become opponents to
					them.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					Have you not considered how We dispatch the devils against the disbelievers,
					exciting them with incitement?
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					So do not hurry against them. We are counting for them a countdown.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					On the Day when We will gather the righteous to the Most Merciful, as guests.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					And herd the sinners into hell, like animals to water.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					They will have no power of intercession, except for someone who has an
					agreement with the Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					And they say, "The Most Merciful has begotten a son."
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					You have come up with something monstrous.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					At which the heavens almost rupture, and the earth splits, and the mountains
					fall and crumble.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					Because they attribute a son to the Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					It is not fitting for the Most Merciful to have a son.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					There is none in the heavens and the earth but will come to the Most Merciful
					as a servant.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					He has enumerated them, and counted them one by one.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					And each one of them will come to Him on the Day of Resurrection alone.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Those who believe and do righteous deeds, the Most Merciful will give them
					love.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					We made it easy in your tongue, in order to deliver good news to the righteous,
					and to warn with it a hostile people.
				-
			-
				Surah 19 - Mary: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					How many a generation have We destroyed before them? Can you feel a single one
					of them, or hear from them the slightest whisper?
				-
		-
			Surah 20 - Ta-Ha
		-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Ta, Ha.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					We did not reveal the Quran to you to make you suffer.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					But only as a reminder for him who fears.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					A revelation from He who created the earth and the high heavens.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					The Most Merciful; on the Throne He settled.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					To Him belongs everything in the heavens and the earth, and everything between
					them, and everything beneath the soil.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					If you speak aloud-He knows the secret, and the most hidden.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					God, there is no god but He, His are the Most Beautiful Names.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Has the story of Moses reached you?
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					When he saw a fire, he said to his family, "Stay; I have noticed a fire;
					Perhaps I can bring you a torch therefrom, or find some guidance by the fire."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Then, when he reached it, he was called, "Moses.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					I-I am your Lord. Take off your shoes. You are in the sacred valley of Tuwa.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					I have chosen you, so listen to what is revealed.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					I-I am God. There is no God but I. So serve Me, and practice the prayer for My
					remembrance.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					The Hour is coming-but I keep it almost hidden-so that each soul will be paid
					for what it endeavors.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					And do not let him who denies it and follows his desire turn you away from it,
					lest you fall.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And what is that in your right-hand, O Moses?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					He said, "This is my staff. I lean on it, and herd my sheep with it, and I have
					other uses for it."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					He said, "Throw it, O Moses."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					So he threw it-thereupon it became a moving serpent.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					He said, "Take hold of it, and do not fear. We will restore it to its original
					condition.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And press your hand to your side; it will come out white, without a
					blemish-another sign.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					That We may show you some of Our greatest signs.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Go to Pharaoh; He has transgressed."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, put my heart at peace for me.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And ease my task for me.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					And untie the knot from my tongue.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					So they can understand my speech.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And appoint an assistant for me, from my family.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Aaron, my brother.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Strengthen me with him.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And have him share in my mission.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					That we may glorify You much.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And remember You much.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					You are always watching over us."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					He said, "You are granted your request, O Moses.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					We had favored you another time.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					When We inspired your mother with the inspiration.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					`Put him in the chest; then cast him into the river. The river will wash him to
					shore, where an enemy of Mine and an enemy of his will pick him up. And I have
					bestowed upon you love from Me, so that you may be reared before My eye.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					When your sister walked along, and said, 'Shall I tell you about someone who
					will take care of him?' So We returned you to your mother, that she may be
					comforted, and not sorrow. And you killed a person, but We saved you from
					stress; and We tested you thoroughly. And you stayed years among the people of
					Median. Then you came back, as ordained, O Moses.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					And I made you for Myself.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Go, you and your brother, with My signs, and do not neglect My remembrance.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Go to Pharaoh. He has tyrannized.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					But speak to him nicely. Perhaps he will remember, or have some fear."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					They said, "Lord, we fear he may persecute us, or become violent."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					He said, "Do not fear, I am with you, I hear and I see.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					Approach him and say, `We are the messengers of your Lord; so let the Children
					of Israel go with us, and do not torment them. We bring you a sign from your
					Lord, and peace be upon him who follows guidance.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					It was revealed to us that the punishment falls upon him who disbelieves and
					turns away.'"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					He said, "Who is your Lord, O Moses."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					He said, "Our Lord is He who gave everything its existence, then guided it."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					He said, "What about the first generations?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					He said, "Knowledge thereof is with my Lord, in a Book. My Lord never errs, nor
					does He forget."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					He who made the earth a habitat for you; and traced in it routes for you; and
					sent down water from the sky, with which We produce pairs of diverse plants.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Eat and pasture your livestock. In that are signs for those with understanding.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					From it We created you, and into it We will return you, and from it We will
					bring you out another time.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					We showed him Our signs, all of them, but he denied and refused.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					He said, "Did you come to us to drive us out of our land with your magic, O
					Moses?
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					We will produce for you magic like it; so make an appointment between us and
					you, which we will not miss-neither us, nor you-in a central place."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					He said, "Your appointment is the day of the festival, so let the people be
					gathered together at mid-morning."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					Pharaoh turned away, put together his plan, and then came back.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					Moses said to them, "Woe to you. Do not fabricate lies against God, or He will
					destroy you with a punishment. He who invents lies will fail."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					They disagreed among themselves over their affair, and conferred secretly.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					They said, "These two are magicians who want to drive you out of your land with
					their magic, and to abolish your exemplary way of life.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					So settle your plan, and come as one front. Today, whoever gains the upper hand
					will succeed."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					They said, "Moses, either you throw, or we will be the first to throw."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					He said, "You throw." And suddenly, their ropes and sticks appeared to him,
					because of their magic, to be crawling swiftly.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					So Moses felt apprehensive within himself.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					We said, "Do not be afraid, you are the uppermost.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					Now throw down what is in your right hand-it will swallow what they have
					crafted. What they have crafted is only a magician's trickery. But the magician
					will not succeed, no matter what he does."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					And the magicians fell down prostrate. They said, "We have believed in the Lord
					of Aaron and Moses."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					He said, "Did you believe in him before I have given you permission? He must be
					your chief, who has taught you magic. I will cut off your hands and your feet
					on alternate sides, and I will crucify you on the trunks of the palm-trees.
					Then you will know which of us is more severe in punishment, and more lasting."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					They said, "We will not prefer you to the proofs that have come to us, and Him
					who created us. So issue whatever judgment you wish to issue. You can only rule
					in this lowly life.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					We have believed in our Lord, so that He may forgive us our sins, and the magic
					you have compelled us to practice. God is Better, and more Lasting."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					Whoever comes to his Lord guilty, for him is Hell, where he neither dies nor
					lives.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					But whoever comes to Him a believer, having worked righteousness-these will
					have the highest ranks.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					The Gardens of Perpetuity, beneath which rivers flow, dwelling therein forever.
					That is the reward for him who purifies himself.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					And We inspired Moses: "Travel by night with My servants, and strike for them a
					dry path across the sea, not fearing being overtaken, nor worrying."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					Pharaoh pursued them with his troops, but the sea overwhelmed them, and
					completely engulfed them.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					Pharaoh misled his people, and did not guide them.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					O Children of Israel! We have delivered you from your enemy, and promised you
					by the right side of the Mount, and sent down to you manna and quails.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					Eat of the good things We have provided for you, but do not be excessive
					therein, lest My wrath descends upon you. He upon whom My wrath descends has
					fallen.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					And I am Forgiving towards him who repents, believes, acts righteously, and
					then remains guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					"And what made you rush ahead of your people, O Moses?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					He said, "They are following in my footsteps; and I hurried on to You, my Lord,
					that you may be pleased."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					He said, "We have tested your people in your absence, and the Samarian misled
					them."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					So Moses returned to his people, angry and disappointed. He said, "my people,
					did your Lord not promise you a good promise? Was the time too long for you? Or
					did you want wrath from your Lord to descend upon you, so you broke your
					promise to me?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					They said, "We did not break our promise to you by our choice, but we were made
					to carry loads of the people's ornaments, and we cast them in. That was what
					the Samarian suggested."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					So he produced for them a calf-a mere body which lowed. And they said, "This is
					your god, and the god of Moses, but he has forgotten."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					Did they not see that it cannot return a word to them, and has no power to harm
					them or benefit them?
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					Aaron had said to them before, "my people, you are being tested by this. And
					your Lord is the Merciful, so follow me, and obey my command."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					They said, "We will not give up our devotion to it, until Moses returns to us."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					He said, "Aaron, what prevented you, when you saw them going astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					From following me? Did you disobey my command?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					He said, "Son of my mother, do not seize me by my beard or my head. I feared
					you would say, `You have caused division among the Children of Israel, and did
					not regard my word.'"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					He said, "What do you have to say, O Samarian?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					He said, "I saw what they did not see, so I grasped a handful from the
					Messenger's traces, and I flung it away. Thus my soul prompted me."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					He said, "Begone! Your lot in this life is to say, 'No contact.' And you have
					an appointment that you will not miss. Now look at your god that you remained
					devoted to-we will burn it up, and then blow it away into the sea, as powder."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					Surely your god is God, the One besides whom there is no other god. He
					comprehends everything in knowledge.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					Thus We narrate to you reports of times gone by; and We have given you a
					message from Our Presence.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					Whoever turns away from it will carry on the Day of Resurrection a burden.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					Abiding therein forever. And wretched is their burden on the Day of
					Resurrection.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					On the Day when the Trumpet is blown-We will gather the sinners on that Day,
					blue.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					Murmuring among themselves: "You have lingered only for ten."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					We are fully aware of what they say, when the most exemplary of them in conduct
					will say, "You have lingered only a day."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					And they ask you about the mountains. Say, "My Lord will crumble them utterly."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					And leave them desolate waste.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					You will see in them neither crookedness, nor deviation."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					On that Day, they will follow the caller, without any deviation. Voices will be
					hushed before the Merciful, and you will hear nothing but murmur.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					On that Day, intercession will not avail, except for him permitted by the
					Merciful, and whose words He has approved.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					He knows what is before them and what is behind them, and they cannot
					comprehend Him in their knowledge.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					Faces will be humbled before the Living, the Eternal. Whoever carries injustice
					will despair.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 112
			-
				-
					But whoever has done righteous deeds, while being a believer-will fear neither
					injustice, nor grievance.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 113
			-
				-
					Thus We have revealed it an Arabic Quran, and We have diversified the warnings
					in it, that perhaps they would become righteous, or it may produce a lesson for
					them.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 114
			-
				-
					Exalted is God, the True King. Do not be hasty with the Quran before its
					inspiration to you is concluded, and say, "My Lord, increase me in knowledge."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 115
			-
				-
					And We covenanted with Adam before, but he forgot, and We found in him no
					resolve.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 116
			-
				-
					And when We said to the angels, "Bow down to Adam." They bowed down, except for
					Satan; he refused.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 117
			-
				-
					We said, "Adam, this is an enemy to you and to your wife. So do not let him
					make you leave the Garden, for then you will suffer.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 118
			-
				-
					In it you will never go hungry, nor be naked.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 119
			-
				-
					Nor will you be thirsty in it, nor will you swelter."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 120
			-
				-
					But Satan whispered to him. He said, "Adam, shall I show you the Tree of
					Immortality, and a kingdom that never decays?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 121
			-
				-
					And so they ate from it; whereupon their bodies became visible to them, and
					they started covering themselves with the leaves of the Garden. Thus Adam
					disobeyed his Lord, and fell.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 122
			-
				-
					But then his Lord recalled him, and pardoned him, and guided him.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 123
			-
				-
					He said, "Go down from it, altogether; some of you enemies of some others. But
					whenever guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows My guidance, will not
					go astray, nor suffer.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 124
			-
				-
					But whoever turns away from My Reminder, for him is a confined life. And We
					will raise him on the Day of Resurrection blind."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 125
			-
				-
					He will say, "My Lord, why did You raise me blind, though I was seeing?"
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 126
			-
				-
					He will say, "Just as Our revelations came to you, and you forgot them, today
					you will be forgotten."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 127
			-
				-
					Thus We recompense him who transgresses and does not believe in the revelations
					of his Lord. The punishment of the Hereafter is more severe, and more lasting.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 128
			-
				-
					Is it not instructive to them, how many generations before them We destroyed,
					in whose settlements they walk? Surely in that are signs for people of
					understanding.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 129
			-
				-
					Were it not for a word that issued from your Lord, the inevitable would have
					happened, but there is an appointed term.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 130
			-
				-
					So bear patiently what they say, and celebrate the praises of your Lord before
					the rising of the sun, and before its setting. And during the hours of the
					night glorify Him, and at the borders of the day, that you may be satisfied.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 131
			-
				-
					And do not extend your glance towards what We have given some classes of them
					to enjoy-the splendor of the life of this world-that We may test them thereby.
					Your Lord's provision is better, and more lasting.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 132
			-
				-
					And exhort your people to pray, and patiently adhere to it. We ask of you no
					sustenance, but it is We who sustain you. The good ending is that for
					righteousness.
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 133
			-
				-
					And they say, "Why does he not bring us a miracle from his Lord?" Were they not
					given enough miracles in the former scriptures?
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 134
			-
				-
					Had We destroyed them with a punishment before him, they would have said, "Our
					Lord, if only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your
					revelations before we were humiliated and disgraced."
				-
			-
				Surah 20 - Ta-Ha: Ayah 135
			-
				-
					Say, "Everybody is waiting, so wait. You will know who the people of the
					straight path are, and who is rightly-guided.
				-
		-
			Surah 21 - The Prophets
		-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Mankind's reckoning has drawn near, but they turn away heedlessly.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					No fresh reminder comes to them from their Lord, but they listen to it
					playfully.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Their hearts distracted, the wrongdoers confer secretly, "Is this anything but
					a mortal like you? Will you take to sorcery, with open-eyes?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord knows what is said in the heaven and the earth; and He is the
					Hearer, the Knower."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And they said, "A jumble of dreams," and, "He made it up," and, "He is a poet,"
					"let him bring us a sign, like those sent to the ancients."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					None of the towns We destroyed before them had believed. Will they, then,
					believe?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					We did not send before you except men, whom We inspired. Ask the people of
					knowledge, if you do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					We did not make them mere bodies that ate no food, nor were they immortal.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Then We fulfilled Our promise to them, and We saved them together with whomever
					We willed, and We destroyed the extravagant.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					We have sent down to you a Book, containing your message. Do you not
					understand?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					How many a guilty town have We crushed, and established thereafter another
					people?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Then, when they sensed Our might, they started running away from it.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					Do not run, but come back to your luxuries, and to your homes, that you may be
					questioned.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					They said, "Woe to us; we were unfair."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					This continued to be their cry, until We made them silent ashes.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					We did not create the sky and the earth and what is between them for amusement.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					If We wanted amusement, We could have found it within Us, were We to do so.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					In fact, We hurl the truth against falsehood, and it crushes it, so it
					vanishes. Woe unto you, for what you describe.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					To Him belongs everyone in the heavens and the earth. Those near Him are not
					too proud to worship Him, nor do they waver.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					They praise night and day, without ever tiring.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Or have they taken to themselves gods from the earth who resurrect?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					If there were in them gods other than God, they would have gone to ruin. So
					glory be to God, Lord of the Throne, beyond what they allege.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					He will not be questioned about what He does, but they will be questioned.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Or have they taken, besides Him, other gods? Say, "Bring your proof. This is a
					message for those with me, and a message of those before me." But most of them
					do not know the truth, so they turn away.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					We never sent a messenger before you without inspiring him that: "There is no
					god but I, so worship Me."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And they say, "The Most Merciful has taken to himself a son." Be He glorified;
					they are but honored servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					They never speak before He has spoken, and they only act on His command.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					He knows what is before them, and what is behind them; and they do not
					intercede except for him whom He approves; and they tremble in awe of Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And whoever of them says, "I am a god besides Him," We will reward him with
					Hell. Thus We reward the wrongdoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Do the disbelievers not see that the heavens and the earth were one mass, and
					We tore them apart? And We made from water every living thing. Will they not
					believe?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					And We placed on earth stabilizers, lest it sways with them, and We placed
					therein signposts and passages, that they may be guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And We made the sky a protected ceiling; yet they turn away from its wonders.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					It is He who created the night and the day, and the sun and the moon; each
					floating in an orbit.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					We did not grant immortality to any human being before you. Should you die, are
					they then the immortal?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Every soul will taste death. We burden you with adversity and prosperity-a
					test. And to Us you will be returned.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					When those who disbelieve see you, they treat you only with ridicule: "Is this
					the one who mentions your gods?" And they reject the mention of the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					The human being was created of haste. I will show you My signs, so do not seek
					to rush Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					And they say, "When will this promise come true, if you are truthful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					If those who disbelieve only knew, when they cannot keep the fire off their
					faces and off their backs, and they will not be helped.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					In fact, it will come upon them suddenly, and bewilder them. They will not be
					able to repel it, and they will not be reprieved.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Messengers before you were also ridiculed, but those who jeered were surrounded
					by what they had ridiculed.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Say, "Who guards you against the Merciful by night and by day?" But they turn
					away from the mention of their Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Or do they have gods who can defend them against Us? They cannot help
					themselves, nor will they be protected from Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					We have given these enjoyments, and their ancestors, until time grew long upon
					them. Do they not see how We gradually reduce the land from its extremities?
					Are they then the victors?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					Say, "I am warning you through inspiration." But the deaf cannot hear the call
					when they are being warned.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					And when a breath of your Lord's punishment touches them, they say, "Woe to us,
					we were truly wicked."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					We will set up the scales of justice for the Day of Resurrection, so that no
					soul will suffer the least injustice. And even if it be the weight of a
					mustard-seed, We will bring it up. Sufficient are We as Reckoners.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					We gave Moses and Aaron the Criterion, and illumination, and a reminder for the
					righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					Those who fear their Lord in private, and are apprehensive of the Hour.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					This too is a blessed message that We revealed. Are you going to deny it?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					We gave Abraham his integrity formerly, and We knew him well.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					When he said to his father and his people, "What are these statues to which you
					are devoted?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					They said, "We found our parents worshiping them."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					He said, "You and your parents are in evident error."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					They said, "Are you telling us the truth, or are you just playing?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					He said, "Your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the One who
					created them, and I bear witness to that.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					"By God, I will have a plan for your statues after you have gone away."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					So he reduced them into pieces, except for their biggest, that they may return
					to it.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					They said, "Who did this to our gods? He is certainly one of the wrongdoers."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					They said, "We heard a youth mentioning them. He is called Abraham."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					They said, "Bring him before the eyes of the people, so that they may witness."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					They said, "Are you the one who did this to our gods, O Abraham?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					He said, "But it was this biggest of them that did it. Ask them, if they can
					speak."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					Then they turned to one another, and said, "You yourselves are the wrongdoers."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					But they reverted to their old ideas: "You certainly know that these do not
					speak."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					He said, "Do you worship, instead of God, what can neither benefit you in
					anything, nor harm you?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					Fie on you, and on what you worship instead of God. Do you not understand?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					They said, "Burn him and support your gods, if you are going to act."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					We said, "fire, be coolness and safety upon Abraham."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					They planned to harm him, but We made them the worst losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					And We delivered him, and Lot, to the land that We blessed for all people.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					And We granted him Isaac and Jacob as a gift; and each We made righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					And We made them leaders, guiding by Our command; and We inspired them to do
					good works, and to observe the prayer, and to give out charity. They were
					devoted servants to Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					And Lot-We gave him judgment and knowledge, and We delivered him from the town
					that practiced the abominations. They were wicked and perverted people.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					And We admitted him into Our mercy; for He was one of the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					And Noah, when he called before. So We answered him, and delivered him and his
					family from the great disaster.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					And We supported him against the people who rejected Our signs. They were an
					evil people, so We drowned them all.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					And David and Solomon, when they gave judgment in the case of the field, when
					some people's sheep wandered therein by night; and We were witnesses to their
					judgment.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					And so We made Solomon understand it, and to each We gave wisdom and knowledge.
					And We subjected the mountains along with David to sing Our praises, and the
					birds as well-surely We did.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And We taught him the making of shields for you, to protect you from your
					violence. Are you, then, appreciative?
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					And to Solomon the stormy wind, blowing at His command towards the land that We
					have blessed. We are aware of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					And of the devils were some that dived for him, and performed other, lesser
					tasks. But We kept them restrained.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					And Job, when he cried out to his Lord: "Great harm has afflicted me, and you
					are the Most Merciful of the merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					So We answered him, lifted his suffering, and restored his family to him, and
					their like with them-a mercy from Us, and a reminder for the worshipers.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					And Ishmael, and Enoch, and Ezekiel; each was one of the steadfast.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					And We admitted them into Our mercy. They were among the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					And Jonah, when he stormed out in fury, thinking We had no power over him. But
					then He cried out in the darkness, "There is no god but You! Glory to You! I
					was one of the wrongdoers!"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					So We answered him, and saved him from the affliction. Thus We save the
					faithful.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					And Zechariah, when he called out to his Lord, "My Lord, do not leave me alone,
					even though you are the Best of heirs."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					So We answered him, and gave him John. And We cured his wife for him. They used
					to vie in doing righteous deeds, and used to call on Us in love and awe, and
					they used to humble themselves to Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					And she who guarded her virginity. We breathed into her of Our spirit, and made
					her and her son a sign to the world.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					This community of yours is one community, and I am your Lord, so worship Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					But they splintered themselves into factions. They will all return to Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					Whoever does righteous deeds, and is a believer, his effort will not be denied.
					We are writing it down for him.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					There is a ban on the town that We had destroyed-that they will not return.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Until, when Gog and Magog are let loose, and they swarm down from every mound.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					The promise of truth has drawn near. The eyes of those who disbelieved will
					stare in horror: "Woe to us. We were oblivious to this. In fact, we were
					wrongdoers."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					You and what you worship besides God are fuel for Hell. You will descend into
					it.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					Had these been gods, they would not have descended into it. All will abide in
					it.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					In it they will wail. In it they will not hear.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					As for those who deserved goodness from Us-these will be kept away from it.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					They will not hear its hissing, and they will forever abide in what their
					hearts desire.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					The Supreme Fear will not worry them, and the angels will receive them: "This
					is your Day which you were promised."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					On the Day when We fold the heaven, like the folding of a book. Just as We
					began the first creation, We will repeat it-a promise binding on Us. We will
					act.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					We have written in the Psalms, after the Reminder, that the earth will be
					inherited by My righteous servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					Indeed, in this is a message for people who worship.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					We did not send you except as mercy to mankind.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					Say, "It is revealed to me that your God is One God. Are you going to submit?"
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					But if they turn away, say, "I have informed you sufficiently. Although I do
					not know whether what you are promised is near or far."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					He knows what is said openly, and He knows what you conceal.
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					"And I do not know whether it is perhaps a trial for you, and an enjoyment for
					a while."
				-
			-
				Surah 21 - The Prophets: Ayah 112
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, judge with justice." And, "Our Lord is the Gracious, Whose
					help is sought against what you allege."
				-
		-
			Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage
		-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					O people, be conscious of your Lord. The quaking of the Hour is a tremendous
					thing.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					On the Day when you will see it: every nursing mother will discard her infant,
					and every pregnant woman will abort her load, and you will see the people
					drunk, even though they are not drunk-but the punishment of God is severe.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Among the people is he who argues about God without knowledge, and follows
					every defiant devil.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					It was decreed for him, that whoever follows him-he will misguide him, and lead
					him to the torment of the Blaze.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					O people! If you are in doubt about the Resurrection-We created you from dust,
					then from a small drop, then from a clinging clot, then from a lump of flesh,
					partly developed and partly undeveloped. In order to clarify things for you.
					And We settle in the wombs whatever We will for a designated term, and then We
					bring you out as infants, until you reach your full strength. And some of you
					will pass away, and some of you will be returned to the vilest age, so that he
					may not know, after having known. And you see the earth still; but when We send
					down water on it, it vibrates, and swells, and grows all kinds of lovely pairs.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					That is because God is the truth, and because He gives life to the dead, and
					because He is Capable of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And because the Hour is coming-there is no doubt about it-and because God will
					resurrect those in the graves.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					And among the people is he who argues about God without knowledge, or guidance,
					or an enlightening scripture.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Turning aside in contempt, to lead away from the path of God. He will have
					humiliation in this world, and on the Day of Resurrection We will make him
					taste the agony of burning.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					That is for what your hands have advanced, and because God is not unjust to the
					servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					And among the people is he who worships God on edge. When something good comes
					his way, he is content with it. But when an ordeal strikes him, he makes a
					turnaround. He loses this world and the next. That is the obvious loss.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					He invokes, instead of God, what can neither harm him nor benefit him. That is
					the far straying.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					He invokes one whose harm is closer than his benefit. What a miserable master.
					What a miserable companion.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					God will admit those who believe and do righteous deeds into Gardens beneath
					which rivers flow. God does whatever He wills.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Whoever thinks that God will not help him in this life and in the Hereafter-let
					him turn to heaven, then sever, and see if his cunning eliminates what enrages
					him.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Thus We revealed it as clarifying signs, and God guides whomever He wills.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					Those who believe, and those who are Jewish, and the Sabeans, and the
					Christians, and the Zoroastrians, and the Polytheists-God will judge between
					them on the Day of Resurrection. God is witness to all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Do you not realize that to God prostrates everyone in the heavens and everyone
					on earth, and the sun, and the moon, and the stars, and the mountains, and the
					trees, and the animals, and many of the people? But many are justly deserving
					of punishment. Whomever God shames, there is none to honor him. God does
					whatever He wills.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Here are two adversaries feuding regarding their Lord. As for those who
					disbelieve, garments of fire will be tailored for them, and scalding water will
					be poured over their heads.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Melting their insides and their skins.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And they will have maces of iron.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Whenever they try to escape the gloom, they will be driven back to it: "Taste
					the suffering of burning."
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					But God will admit those who believe and do good deeds into Gardens beneath
					which rivers flow. They will be decorated therein with bracelets of gold and
					pearls, and their garments therein will be of silk.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					They were guided to purity of speech. They were guided to the path of the Most
					Praised.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					As for those who disbelieve and repel from God's path and from the Sacred
					Mosque-which We have designated for all mankind equally, whether residing
					therein or passing through-and seek to commit sacrilege therein-We will make
					him taste of a painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					We showed Abraham the location of the House: "Do not associate anything with
					Me; and purify My House for those who circle around, and those who stand to
					pray, and those who kneel and prostrate."
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					And announce the pilgrimage to humanity. They will come to you on foot, and on
					every transport. They will come from every distant point.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					That they may witness the benefits for themselves, and celebrate the name of
					God during the appointed days, for providing them with the animal livestock. So
					eat from it, and feed the unfortunate poor.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Then let them perform their acts of cleansing, and fulfill their vows, and
					circle around the Ancient House.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					All that. Whoever venerates the sanctities of God-it is good for him with his
					Lord. All livestock are permitted to you, except what is recited to you. So
					stay away from the abomination of idols, and stay away from perjury.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Being true to God, without associating anything with Him. Whoever associates
					anything with God-it is as though he has fallen from the sky, and is snatched
					by the birds, or is swept away by the wind to a distant abyss.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					So it is. Whoever venerates the sacraments of God-it is from the piety of the
					hearts.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					In them are benefits for you until a certain time. Then their place is by the
					Ancient House.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					We have appointed a rite for every nation, that they may commemorate God's name
					over the livestock He has provided for them. Your God is One God, so to Him
					submit, and announce good news to the humble.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Those whose hearts tremble when God is mentioned, and those who endure what has
					befallen them, and those who perform the prayer and spend from what We have
					provided for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					We have made the animal offerings emblems of God for you. In them is goodness
					for you. So pronounce God's name upon them as they line up. Then, when they
					have fallen on their sides, eat of them and feed the contented and the beggar.
					Thus We have subjected them to you, that you may be thankful.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Neither their flesh, nor their blood, ever reaches God. What reaches Him is the
					righteousness from you. Thus He subdued them to you, that you may glorify God
					for guiding you. And give good news to the charitable.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					God defends those who believe. God does not love any ungrateful traitor.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Permission is given to those who are fought against, and God is Able to give
					them victory.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Those who were unjustly evicted from their homes, merely for saying, "Our Lord
					is God." Were it not that God repels people by means of others: monasteries,
					churches, synagogues, and mosques-where the name of God is mentioned much-would
					have been demolished. God supports whoever supports Him. God is Strong and
					Mighty.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Those who, when We empower them in the land, observe the prayer, and give
					regular charity, and command what is right, and forbid what is wrong. To God
					belongs the outcome of events.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					If they deny you-before them the people of Noah, and Aad, and Thamood also
					denied.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					And the people of Abraham, and the people of Lot.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					And the inhabitants of Median. And Moses was denied. Then I reprieved those who
					disbelieved, but then I seized them. So how was My rejection?
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					How many a town have We destroyed while it was doing wrong? They lie in ruins;
					with stilled wells, and lofty mansions.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Have they not journeyed in the land, and had minds to reason with, or ears to
					listen with? It is not the eyes that go blind, but it is the hearts, within the
					chests, that go blind.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And they ask you to hasten the punishment. But God never breaks His promise. A
					day with your Lord is like a thousand years of your count.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					How many a town have I reprieved, although it was unjust? Then I seized it. To
					Me is the destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					Say, "people, I am only a plain warner to you."
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Those who believe and work righteousness-for them is forgiveness and a generous
					provision.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					But those who strive against Our revelations-these are the inmates of Hell.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					We never sent a messenger before you, or a prophet, but when he had a desire
					Satan interfered in his wishes. But God nullifies what Satan interjects, and
					God affirms His revelations. God is Omniscient and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					In order to make Satan's suggestions a trial for those whose hearts are
					diseased, and those whose hearts are hardened. The wrongdoers are in profound
					discord.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					And so that those endowed with knowledge may know that it is the truth from
					your Lord, and so believe in it, and their hearts soften to it. God guides
					those who believe to a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve will continue to be hesitant about it, until the Hour
					comes upon them suddenly, or there comes to them the torment of a desolate Day.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					Sovereignty on that Day belongs to God; He will judge between them. Those who
					believe and do good deeds will be in the Gardens of Bliss.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					But those who disbelieve and reject Our revelations-these will have a
					humiliating punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Those who emigrate in God's cause, then get killed, or die, God will provide
					them with fine provisions. God is the Best of Providers.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					He will admit them an admittance that will please them. God is Knowing and
					Clement.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					That is so! Whoever retaliates similarly to the affliction he was made to
					suffer, and then he is wronged again, God will definitely assist him. God is
					Pardoning and Forgiving.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					That is because God merges the night into the day, and He merges the day into
					the night, and because God is Hearing and Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					That is because God is the Reality, and what they invoke besides Him is vanity,
					and because God is the Sublime, the Grand.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					Do you not see that God sends down water from the sky, and the land becomes
					green? God is Kind and Aware.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					To Him belongs everything in the heavens and everything on earth. God is the
					Rich, the Praised.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					Do you not see that God made everything on earth subservient to you? How the
					ships sail at sea by His command? That He holds up the sky lest it falls on
					earth-except by His permission? God is Gracious towards the people, Most
					Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					And it is He who gives you life, then makes you die, then revives you. The
					human being is unappreciative.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					For every congregation We have appointed acts of devotion, which they observe.
					So do not let them dispute with you in this matter. And invite to your Lord;
					you are upon a straight guidance.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					But if they dispute with you, say, "God is fully aware of what you do."
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					God will judge between you on the Day of Resurrection regarding what you
					disagree about.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					Do you not know that God knows everything in the heavens and the earth? This is
					in a book. That is easy for God.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					Yet they worship, besides God, things for which He sent down no warrant, and
					what they have no knowledge of. There is no savior for the transgressors.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					And when Our Clear Verses are recited to them, you will recognize disgust on
					the faces of those who disbelieve. They nearly assault those who recite to them
					Our Verses. Say, "Shall I inform you of something worse than that? The Fire!
					God has promised it to those who disbelieve. And what a wretched outcome!"
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					O people! A parable is presented, so listen to it: Those you invoke besides God
					will never create a fly, even if they banded together for that purpose. And if
					the fly steals anything from them, they cannot recover it from it. Weak are the
					pursuer and the pursued.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					They do not value God as He should be valued. God is Strong and Powerful.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					God chooses messengers from among the angels, and from among the people. God is
					Hearing and Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					He knows what is before them, and what is behind them. To God all matters are
					referred.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Kneel, and prostrate, and worship your Lord, and do good
					deeds, so that you may succeed.
				-
			-
				Surah 22 - The Pilgrimage: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					And strive for God, with the striving due to Him. He has chosen you, and has
					not burdened you in religion-the faith of your father Abraham. It is he who
					named you Muslims before, and in this. So that the Messenger may be a witness
					over you, and you may be witnesses over the people. So pray regularly, and give
					regular charity, and cleave to God. He is your Protector. What an excellent
					Protector, and what an excellent Helper.
				-
		-
			Surah 23 - The Believers
		-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Successful are the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Those who are humble in their prayers.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Those who avoid nonsense.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Those who work for charity.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Those who safeguard their chastity.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Except from their spouses, or their dependents-for then they are free from
					blame.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					But whoever seeks anything beyond that-these are the transgressors.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Those who are faithful to their trusts and pledges.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Those who safeguard their prayers.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					These are the inheritors.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Who will inherit Paradise, wherein they will dwell forever.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					We created man from an extract of clay.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					Then We made him a seed, in a secure repository.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Then We developed the seed into a clot. Then We developed the clot into a lump.
					Then We developed the lump into bones. Then We clothed the bones with flesh.
					Then We produced it into another creature. Most Blessed is God, the Best of
					Creators.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Then, after that, you will die.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Then, on the Day of Resurrection, you will be resurrected.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					We created above you seven pathways, and We are never heedless of the creation.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And We sent down water from the sky in proper quantity, and settled it in the
					ground, and We are Able to take it away.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					With it We produce for you gardens of palms and vines, yielding abundant fruit
					for you to eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And a tree springing out of Mount Sinai, producing oil, and seasoning for those
					who eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And there is a lesson for you in livestock: We give you to drink from what is
					in their bellies, and you have many benefits in them, and from them you eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And on them, and on the ships, you are transported.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					We sent Noah to his people. He said, "my people, worship God, you have no deity
					other than Him. Will you not take heed?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					But the notables of his people, who disbelieved, said, "This is nothing but a
					human like you, who wants to gain superiority over you. Had God willed, He
					would have sent down angels. We never heard of this from our forefathers of
					old.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					He is nothing but a man possessed. Just ignore him for a while."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, help me, for they have rejected me."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					So We inspired him: "Build the Ark under Our observation and by Our
					inspiration. And when Our decree comes to pass, and the oven boils over, load
					into it two pairs of every kind, together with your family, except those of
					them against whom the word has already been pronounced. And do not speak to me
					concerning those who did wrong; for they are to be drowned."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Then, when you and those with you are settled in the Ark, say, "Praise be to
					God, who has saved us from the wrongdoing people."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And say, "My Lord, land me with a blessed landing, as you are the best of
					transporters."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Surely in that are signs. We are always testing.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Then, after them, We established another generation.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And We sent among them a messenger from themselves: "Serve God. You have no god
					other than Him. Will you not be cautious?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					But the dignitaries of his people, those who disbelieved and denied the meeting
					of the Hereafter, and We had indulged them in the present life, said, "This is
					nothing but a human like you; he eats what you eat, and he drinks what you
					drink.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					If you obey a human being like yourselves, then you will be losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Does he promise you that when you have died and become dust and bones, you will
					be brought out?
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Farfetched, farfetched is what you are promised.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					There is nothing but our life in this world. We die, and we live, and we are
					not resurrected.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					He is nothing but a man, making up lies about God. We have no faith in him."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, help me, for they have rejected me."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					He said, "Soon they will be filled with regret."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Then the Blast struck them, justifiably, and We turned them into scum. So away
					with the wicked people.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Then, after them, We raised other generations.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					No nation can advance its time, nor can they postpone it.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Then We sent Our messengers in succession. Every time a messenger came to his
					community, they called him a liar. So We made them follow one another, and made
					them history. So away with a people who do not believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron, with Our signs and a clear authority.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					To Pharaoh and his nobles, but they turned arrogant. They were oppressive
					people.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					They said, "Are we to believe in two mortals like us, and their people are our
					slaves?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					So they called them liars, and thus were among those destroyed.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					And We gave Moses the Scripture, that they may be guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					And We made Mary's son and his mother a sign, and We sheltered them on high
					ground with security and flowing springs.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					O messengers, eat of the good things, and act with integrity. I am aware of
					what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					This nation of yours is one nation, and I am your Lord, so fear Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					But they tore themselves into sects; each party happy with what they have.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					So leave them in their bewilderment until a time.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					Do they assume that, in furnishing them with wealth and children.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					We race to give them the good things? In fact, they have no idea.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Those who, from awe of their Lord, are fearful.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					And those who believe in their Lord's Verses.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					And those who associate no partners with their Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					And those who give what they give, while their hearts quake, knowing that to
					their Lord they will return.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					It is they who race towards goodness. It is they who will reach it first.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					We never burden any soul beyond its capacity. And with Us is a record that
					tells the truth, and they will not be wronged.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					But their hearts are puzzled because of this; and they have deeds that do not
					conform to this, which they continue to perpetrate.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					Until, when We seize the decadent among them with torment, they begin to groan.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					Do not groan today. You will receive no help from Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					My Verses were recited to you, but you turned back on your heels.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					Arrogant towards it-talked nonsense about it-disregarded it.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					Have they not pondered the Word? Or has there come to them what came not to
					their forefathers of old?
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					Or is it that they did not recognize their messenger, so they are denying him?
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					Or do they say, "He is possessed?" In fact, he brought them the truth, but most
					of them hate the truth.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					If the truth conformed to their desires, the heavens, the earth, and everyone
					in them would have gone to ruin. In fact, We have given them their message, but
					they keep avoiding their message.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					Or are you asking them for a payment? The revenue from your Lord is better, and
					He is the Best of providers.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					You are inviting them to a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					But those who do not believe in the Hereafter are swerving from the path.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					Even if We had mercy on them, and relieved their problems, they would still
					blindly persist in their defiance.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					We have already gripped them with suffering, but they did not surrender to
					their Lord, nor did they humble themselves.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					Until, when We have opened before them a gate of intense agony, at once they
					will despair.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					It is He who produced for you the hearing, and the eyesight, and the feelings.
					But little gratitude you show.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					And it is He who multiplied you on earth, and to Him you will be gathered.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And it is He who gives life and brings death, and to Him is the alternation of
					night and day. Do you not understand?
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					But they say the like of what the ancients said.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					They say, "After we have died, and become dust and bones, will we be
					resurrected?
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					We were promised this before-we and our ancestors-these are nothing but legends
					of the ancients."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					Say, "To whom does the earth belong, and everyone in it, if you happen to
					know?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					They will say, "To God." Say, "Will you not reflect?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 86
			-
				-
					Say, "Who is the Lord of the seven heavens, and Lord of the Splendid Throne?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 87
			-
				-
					They will say, "To God." Say, "Will you not become righteous?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 88
			-
				-
					Say, "In whose hand is the dominion of all things, and He protects and cannot
					be protected from, if you happen to know?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 89
			-
				-
					They will say, "To God." Say, "Then are you bewitched?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 90
			-
				-
					In fact, We have given them the truth, and they are liars.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 91
			-
				-
					God has never begotten a son, nor is there any god besides Him. Otherwise, each
					god would have taken away what it has created, and some of them would have
					gained supremacy over others. Glory be to God, far beyond what they describe.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 92
			-
				-
					The Knower of the hidden and the manifest. He is exalted, far above what they
					associate.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 93
			-
				-
					Say, "My Lord, if You would show me what they are promised.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 94
			-
				-
					My Lord, do not place me among the wicked people."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 95
			-
				-
					We are surely Able to show you what We promise them.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 96
			-
				-
					Repel evil by what is better. We are aware of what they describe.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 97
			-
				-
					And say, "My Lord, I seek refuge with You from the urgings of the devils.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 98
			-
				-
					And I seek refuge with You, my Lord, lest they become present."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 99
			-
				-
					Until, when death comes to one of them, he says, "My Lord, send me back.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 100
			-
				-
					That I may do right in what I have neglected." By no means! It is just a word
					that he utters. And behind them is a barrier, until the Day they are
					resurrected.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 101
			-
				-
					When the Horn is blown, no relations between them will exist on that Day, and
					they will not ask after one another.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 102
			-
				-
					Those whose scales are heavy-those are the successful.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 103
			-
				-
					But those whose scales are light-those are they who have lost their souls; in
					Hell they will dwell forever.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 104
			-
				-
					The Fire lashes their faces, and therein they grimace.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 105
			-
				-
					"Were not My revelations recited to you, and you kept on rejecting them?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 106
			-
				-
					They will say, "Our Lord, our wretchedness prevailed over us, and we were a
					people astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 107
			-
				-
					Our Lord! Bring us out of this. If we ever returned, we would truly be evil."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 108
			-
				-
					He will say, "Be despised therein, and do not speak to Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 109
			-
				-
					There was a group of My servants who would say, `Our Lord, we have believed, so
					forgive us, and have mercy on us; You are the Best of the merciful.'
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 110
			-
				-
					But you made them a target of ridicule, until they made you forget My
					remembrance; and you used to laugh at them.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 111
			-
				-
					Today, I have rewarded them for their endurance. They are the ones who are the
					triumphant."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 112
			-
				-
					He will say, "How many years did you remain on earth?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 113
			-
				-
					They will say, "We remained a day, or part of a day; but ask those who keep
					count."
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 114
			-
				-
					He will say, "You remained only for a little while, if you only knew.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 115
			-
				-
					Did you think that We created you in vain, and that to Us you will not be
					returned?"
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 116
			-
				-
					So Exalted is God, the Ruler, the Real. There is no god except He, the Lord of
					the Noble Throne.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 117
			-
				-
					Whoever invokes another god besides God-he has no proof thereof-his reckoning
					rests with his Lord. The disbelievers will not succeed.
				-
			-
				Surah 23 - The Believers: Ayah 118
			-
				-
					And say, "My Lord, forgive and have mercy, for You are the Best of the
					merciful."
				-
		-
			Surah 24 - The Light
		-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					A chapter that We have revealed, and made obligatory, and revealed in it clear
					Verses, that you may take heed.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					The adulteress and the adulterer-whip each one of them a hundred lashes, and
					let no pity towards them overcome you regarding God's Law, if you believe in
					God and the Last Day. And let a group of believers witness their punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					The adulterer shall marry none but an adulteress or an idolatress; and the
					adulteress shall marry none but an adulterer or an idolater. That has been
					prohibited for the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Those who accuse chaste women, then cannot bring four witnesses, whip them
					eighty lashes, and do not ever accept their testimony. For these are the
					immoral.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Except for those who repent afterwards, and reform; for God is Forgiving and
					Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					As for those who accuse their own spouses, but have no witnesses except
					themselves, the testimony of one of them is equivalent to four testimonies, if
					he swears by God that he is truthful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And the fifth time, that God's curse be upon him, if he is a liar.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					But punishment shall be averted from her, if she swears four times by God, that
					he is a liar.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					And the fifth time, that God's wrath be upon her, if he is truthful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Were it not for God's grace upon you, and His mercy, and that God is
					Conciliatory and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Those who perpetrated the slander are a band of you. Do not consider it bad for
					you, but it is good for you. Each person among them bears his share in the sin.
					As for him who played the major role-for him is a terrible punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Why, when you heard about it, the believing men and women did not think well of
					one another, and say, "This is an obvious lie"?
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					Why did they not bring four witnesses to testify to it? If they fail to bring
					the witnesses, then in God's sight, they are liars.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Were it not for God's favor upon you, and His mercy, in this world and the
					Hereafter, you would have suffered a great punishment for what you have
					ventured into.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					When you rumored it with your tongues, and spoke with your mouths what you had
					no knowledge of, and you considered it trivial; but according to God, it is
					serious.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					When you heard it, you should have said, "It is not for us to repeat this. By
					Your glory, this is a serious slander."
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					God cautions you never to return to the like of it, if you are believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					God explains the Verses to you. God is Knowing and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Those who love to see immorality spread among the believers-for them is a
					painful punishment, in this life and in the Hereafter. God knows, and you do
					not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Were it not for God's grace upon you, and His mercy, and that God is Clement
					and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not follow Satan's footsteps. Whoever follows Satan's
					footsteps-he advocates obscenity and immorality. Were it not for God's grace
					towards you, and His mercy, not one of you would have been pure, ever. But God
					purifies whomever He wills. God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Those of you who have affluence and means should not refuse to give to the
					relatives, and the needy, and the emigrants for the sake of God. And let them
					pardon, and let them overlook. Do you not love for God to pardon you? God is
					All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Those who slander honorable, innocent, believing women are cursed in this life
					and in the Hereafter. They will have a terrible punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					On the Day when their tongues, and their hands, and their feet will testify
					against them regarding what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					On that Day, God will pay them their account in full, and they will know that
					God is the Evident Reality.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Bad women are for bad men, and bad men are for bad women, and good women are
					for good men, and good men are for good women. Those are acquitted of what they
					say. There is forgiveness for them, and a generous provision.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not enter homes other than your own, until you have asked
					permission and greeted their occupants. That is better for you, that you may be
					aware.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And if you find no one in them, do not enter them until you are given
					permission. And if it is said to you, "Turn back," then turn back. That is more
					proper for you. God is aware of what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					There is no blame on you for entering uninhabited houses, in which are
					belongings of yours. God knows what you reveal and what you conceal.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Tell the believing men to restrain their looks, and to guard their privates.
					That is purer for them. God is cognizant of what they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					And tell the believing women to restrain their looks, and to guard their
					privates, and not display their beauty except what is apparent thereof, and to
					draw their coverings over their breasts, and not expose their beauty except to
					their husbands, their fathers, their husbands' fathers, their sons, their
					husbands' sons, their brothers, their brothers' sons, their sisters' sons,
					their women, what their right hands possess, their male attendants who have no
					sexual desires, or children who are not yet aware of the nakedness of women.
					And they should not strike their feet to draw attention to their hidden beauty.
					And repent to God, all of you believers, so that you may succeed.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And wed the singles among you, and those who are fit among your servants and
					maids. If they are poor, God will enrich them from His bounty. God is
					All-Encompassing, All-Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And let those who do not find the means to marry abstain, until God enriches
					them from His bounty. If any of your servants wish to be freed, grant them
					their wish, if you recognize some good in them. And give them of God's wealth
					which he has given you. And do not compel your girls to prostitution, seeking
					the materials of this life, if they desire to remain chaste. Should anyone
					compel them-after their compulsion, God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					We have sent down to you clarifying revelations, and examples of those who
					passed on before you, and advice for the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					God is the Light of the heavens and the earth. The allegory of His light is
					that of a pillar on which is a lamp. The lamp is within a glass. The glass is
					like a brilliant planet, fueled by a blessed tree, an olive tree, neither
					eastern nor western. Its oil would almost illuminate, even if no fire has
					touched it. Light upon Light. God guides to His light whomever He wills. God
					thus cites the parables for the people. God is cognizant of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					In houses which God has permitted to be raised, and His name is celebrated
					therein. He is glorified therein, morning and evening.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					By men who neither trading nor commerce distracts them from God's remembrance,
					and from performing the prayers, and from giving alms. They fear a Day when
					hearts and sights are overturned.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					God will reward them according to the best of what they did, and He will
					increase them from His bounty. God provides for whomever He wills without
					reckoning.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					As for those who disbelieve, their works are like a mirage in a desert. The
					thirsty assumes it is to be water. Until, when he has reached it, he finds it
					to be nothing, but there he finds God, Who settles his account in full. God is
					swift in reckoning.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Or like utter darkness in a vast ocean, covered by waves, above which are
					waves, above which is fog. Darkness upon darkness. If he brings out his hand,
					he will hardly see it. He to whom God has not granted a light has no light.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Do you not realize that God is glorified by whatever is in the heavens and the
					earth, and even by the birds in formation? Each knows its prayer and its manner
					of praise. God knows well what they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					To God belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and to God is the
					ultimate return.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Have you not seen how God propels the clouds, then brings them together, then
					piles them into a heap, and you see rain drops emerging from its midst? How He
					brings down loads of hail from the sky, striking with it whomever He wills, and
					diverting it from whomever He wills? The flash of its lightening almost
					snatches the sight away.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					God alternates the night and the day. In that is a lesson for those who have
					insight.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					God created every living creature from water. Some of them crawl on their
					bellies, and some walk on two feet, and others walk on four. God creates
					whatever He wills. God is Capable of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					We sent down enlightening revelations, and God guides whomever He wills to a
					straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And they say, "We have believed in God and the Messenger, and we obey," but
					some of them turn away afterwards. These are not believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					And when they are called to God and His Messenger, in order to judge between
					them, some of them refuse.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					But if justice is on their side, they accept it willingly.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Is there sickness in their hearts? Or are they suspicious? Or do they fear that
					God may do them injustice? Or His Messenger? In fact, they themselves are the
					unjust.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					The response of the believers, when they are called to God and His Messenger in
					order to judge between them, is to say, "We hear and we obey." These are the
					successful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Whoever obeys God and His Messenger, and fears God, and is conscious of
					Him-these are the winners.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					And they swear by God with their solemn oaths, that if you commanded them, they
					would mobilize. Say, "Do not swear. Obedience will be recognized. God is
					experienced with what you do."
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Say, "Obey God and obey the Messenger." But if they turn away, then he is
					responsible for his obligations, and you are responsible for your obligations.
					And if you obey him, you will be guided. It is only incumbent on the Messenger
					to deliver the Clarifying Message.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					God has promised those of you who believe and do righteous deeds, that He will
					make them successors on earth, as He made those before them successors, and He
					will establish for them their religion-which He has approved for them-and He
					will substitute security in place of their fear. They worship Me, never
					associating anything with Me. But whoever disbelieves after that-these are the
					sinners.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					Pray regularly, and give regular charity, and obey the Messenger, so that you
					may receive mercy.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Never think that those who disbelieve can escape on earth. Their place is the
					Fire; a miserable destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Permission must be requested by your servants and those of
					you who have not reached puberty. On three occasions: before the Dawn Prayer,
					and at noon when you change your clothes, and after the Evening Prayer. These
					are three occasions of privacy for you. At other times, it is not wrong for you
					or them to intermingle with one another. God thus clarifies the revelations for
					you. God is Knowledgeable and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					When the children among you reach puberty, they must ask permission, as those
					before them asked permission. God thus clarifies His revelations for you. God
					is Knowledgeable and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					Women past the age of childbearing, who have no desire for marriage, commit no
					wrong by taking off their outer clothing, provided they do not flaunt their
					finery. But to maintain modesty is better for them. God is Hearing and Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					There is no blame on the blind, nor any blame on the lame, nor any blame on the
					sick, nor on yourselves for eating at your homes, or your fathers' homes, or
					your mothers' homes, or your brothers' homes, or your sisters' homes, or the
					homes of your paternal uncles, or the homes of your paternal aunts, or the
					homes of your maternal uncles, or the homes of your maternal aunts, or those
					whose keys you own, or the homes of your friends. You commit no wrong by eating
					together or separately. But when you enter any home, greet one another with a
					greeting from God, blessed and good. God thus explains the revelations for you,
					so that you may understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					The believers are those who believe in God and His Messenger, and when they are
					with him for a matter of common interest, they do not leave until they have
					asked him for permission. Those who ask your permission are those who believe
					in God and His Messenger. So when they ask your permission to attend to some
					affair of theirs, give permission to any of them you wish, and ask God's
					forgiveness for them. God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					Do not address the Messenger in the same manner you address one another. God
					knows those of you who slip away using flimsy excuses. So let those who oppose
					his orders beware, lest an ordeal strikes them, or a painful punishment befalls
					them.
				-
			-
				Surah 24 - The Light: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					Surely, to God belongs everything in the heavens and the earth. He knows what
					you are about. And on the Day they are returned to Him, He will inform them of
					what they did. God has full knowledge of all things.
				-
		-
			Surah 25 - The Criterion
		-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Blessed is He who sent down the Criterion upon His servant, to be a warning to
					humanity.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					He to whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, who took to
					Himself no son, who never had a partner in His kingship; who created everything
					and determined its measure.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And yet, instead of Him, they produce for themselves gods that create nothing,
					but are themselves created; that have no power to harm or benefit themselves;
					and no power over life, death, or resurrection.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "This is nothing but a lie that he made up, and
					others have helped him at it." They have committed an injustice and a perjury.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And they say, "Tales of the ancients; he wrote them down; they are dictated to
					him morning and evening."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Say, "It was revealed by He who knows the Secret in the heavens and the earth.
					He is always Forgiving and Merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And they say, "What sort of messenger is this, who eats food, and walks in the
					marketplaces? If only an angel was sent down with him, to be alongside him a
					warner."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Or, "If only a treasure was dropped on him." Or, "If only he had a garden from
					which he eats." The evildoers also say, "You are following but a man under
					spell."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Look how they invent examples for you. They have gone astray, and cannot find a
					way.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Blessed is He who, if He wills, can provide you with better than that-gardens
					beneath which rivers flow-and He will give you palaces.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					In fact, they have denied the Hour, and We have prepared for those who deny the
					Hour a Blaze.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					When it sees them from a distant place, they will hear it raging and roaring.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And when they are thrown into it, into a tight place, shackled, they will plead
					there for death.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					"Do not plead for one death today, but plead for a great many deaths."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Say, "Is this better, or the Garden of Eternity promised to the righteous? It
					is for them a reward and a destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					They will have therein whatever they desire, forever. That is upon your Lord a
					binding promise.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					On the Day when He gathers them, and what they worshiped besides God, He will
					say, "Was it you who misled these servants of Mine, or was it they who lost the
					way?"
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					They will say, "Glory be to You. It was not for us to take any lords besides
					You. But you gave them enjoyments, and their ancestors, until they forgot the
					Message, and became ruined people."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					They have denied you because of what you say; so you can neither avert, nor
					help. Whoever among you commits injustice, We will make him taste a grievous
					punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					We never sent any messengers before you, but they ate food and walked in the
					marketplaces. And We made some of you tempters for one another-will you be
					patient? Your Lord is always Observing.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Those who do not expect to meet Us say, "If only the angels were sent down to
					us, or we could see our Lord." They have grown arrogant within themselves, and
					have become excessively defiant.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					On the Day when they see the angels-there will be no good news for sinners on
					that Day; and they will say, "A protective refuge."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					We will proceed to the works they did, and will turn them into scattered dust.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					The companions of Paradise on that Day will be better lodged, and more fairly
					accommodated.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					The Day when the sky is cleft with clouds, and the angels are sent down in
					streams.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					On that Day, true sovereignty will belong to the Merciful, and it will be a
					difficult Day for the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					On that Day, the wrongdoer will bite his hands, and say, "If only I had
					followed the way with the Messenger.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Oh, woe to me; I wish I never took so-and-so for a friend.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					He led me away from the Message after it had come to me; for Satan has always
					been a betrayer of man."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					And the Messenger will say, "My Lord, my people have abandoned this Quran."
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Likewise, to every prophet We assign enemies from among the wicked. But your
					Lord suffices as a Guide and Savior.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "Why was the Quran not revealed to him at once?" Thus
					in order to strengthen your heart thereby, and We revealed it in stages.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Whatever argument they come to you with, We provide you with the truth, and a
					better exposition.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Those who are herded into Hell on their faces-those are in a worse position,
					and further astray from the way.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					We gave Moses the Scripture, and appointed his brother Aaron as his assistant.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					We said, "Go to the people who rejected Our signs," and We destroyed them
					completely.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					And the people of Noah: when they rejected the messengers, We drowned them, and
					made them a lesson for mankind. We have prepared for the wrongdoers a painful
					retribution.
				-
			-
				Surah 25 - The Criterion: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					And Aad, and Thamood, and the inhabitants of Arras, and many generations in
