					heavens and the Earth. Those who believe in vanity and reject God-it is they
					who are the losers."
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					And they urge you to hasten the punishment. Were it not for a specified time,
					the punishment would have come to them. But it will come upon them suddenly,
					while they are unaware.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					They urge you to hasten the punishment. But Hell will engulf the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					On the Day when the punishment will envelop them, from above them, and from
					beneath their feet, He will say, "Taste what you used to do!"
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					O My servants who have believed: My earth is vast, so worship Me alone.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Every soul will taste death. Then to Us you will be returned.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Those who believe and work righteousness-We will settle them in Paradise, in
					mansions under which rivers flow, dwelling therein forever. Excellent is the
					compensation for the workers.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Those who endure patiently, and in their Lord they trust.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					How many a creature there is that does not carry its provision? God provides
					for them, and for you. He is the Hearer, the Knowledgeable.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					And if you asked them, "Who created the heavens and the earth and regulated the
					sun and the moon?" They would say, "God." Why then do they deviate?
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					God expands the provision for whomever He wills of His servants, and restricts
					it. God is Cognizant of all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					And if you asked them, "Who sends water down from the sky, with which He
					revives the earth after it had died?" They would say, "God." Say, "Praise be to
					God." But most of them do not understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					The life of this world is nothing but diversion and play, and the Home of the
					Hereafter is the Life, if they only knew.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					When they embark on a vessel, they pray to God, devoting their faith to Him;
					but once He has delivered them safely to land, they attribute partners to Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					To be ungrateful for what We have given them, and to enjoy themselves. They
					will surely come to know.
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					Do they not see that We established a Secure Sanctuary, while all around them
					the people are being carried away? Do they believe in falsehood, and reject the
					blessings of God?
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					And who does greater wrong than he who fabricates lies and attributes them to
					God, or calls the truth a lie when it has come to him? Is there not in Hell a
					dwelling for the blasphemers?
				-
			-
				Surah 29 - The Spider: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					As for those who strive for Us-We will guide them in Our ways. God is with the
					doers of good.
				-
		-
			Surah 30 - The Romans
		-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Meem.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					The Romans have been defeated.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					In a nearby territory. But following their defeat, they will be victorious.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					In a few years. The matter is up to God, in the past, and in the future. On
					that day, the believers will rejoice.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					In God's support. He supports whomever He wills. He is the Almighty, the
					Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					The promise of God-God never breaks His promise, but most people do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					They know an outer aspect of the worldly life, but they are heedless of the
					Hereafter.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Do they not reflect within themselves? God did not create the heavens and the
					earth, and what is between them, except with reason, and for a specific
					duration. But most people, regarding meeting their Lord, are disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Have they not travelled the earth and seen how those before them ended up? They
					were more powerful than them, and they cultivated the land and developed it
					more than they developed it, and their messengers came to them with clear
					signs. God would never wrong them, but they used to wrong themselves.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Then, evil was the end of those who committed evil. That is because they
					rejected God's revelations, and used to ridicule them.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					God originates creation, and then repeats it. Then to Him you will be returned.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					On the Day when the Hour takes place, the guilty will despair.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					They will have no intercessors from among their idols, and they will disown
					their partners.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					On the Day when the Hour takes place-on that Day they will separate.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					As for those who believed and did good deeds-they will be delighted in meadows.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					But as for those who disbelieved, and rejected Our signs and the encounter of
					the Hereafter-those will be hauled into the torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					So glorify God when you retire at night, and when you rise in the morning.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					His is the praise in the heavens and on earth, and in the evening, and when you
					reach midday.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					He brings the living out of the dead, and He brings the dead out of the living,
					and He revives the land after it had died. Likewise you will be resurrected.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And of His signs is that He created you from dust; and behold, you become
					humans spreading out.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And of His signs is that He created for you mates from among yourselves, so
					that you may find tranquility in them; and He planted love and compassion
					between you. In this are signs for people who reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the
					diversity of your languages and colors. In this are signs for those who know.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					And of His signs are your sleep by night and day, and your pursuit of His
					bounty. In this are signs for people who listen.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And of His signs is that He shows you the lightning, causing fear and hope. And
					He brings down water from the sky, and with it He revives the earth after it
					was dead. In this are signs for people who understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					And of His signs is that the heaven and the earth stand at His disposal. And
					then, when He calls you out of the earth, you will emerge at once.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					To Him belongs everyone in the heavens and the earth. All are submissive to
					Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					It is He who initiates creation, and then repeats it, something easy for Him.
					His is the highest attribute, in the heavens and the earth. He is the Almighty,
					the Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					He illustrates an example for you, from your own selves: do you make your
					servants full partners in the wealth We have given you? Do you revere them as
					you revere one another? We thus explain the revelations for a people who
					understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Yet the wrongdoers follow their desires without knowledge. But who can guide
					whom God leaves astray? They will have no helpers.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					So devote yourself to the religion of monotheism-the natural instinct God has
					instilled in mankind. There is no altering God's creation. This is the true
					religion, but most people do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Turning towards Him-and be conscious of Him, and perform the prayer, and do not
					be of the idolaters.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Of those who divided their religion, and became sects; each faction pleased
					with what they have.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					When affliction touches the people, they call on their Lord, turning to Him in
					repentance. But then, when He gives them a taste of His mercy, some of them
					attribute partners to their Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					To show ingratitude for what We have given them. Indulge yourselves-you will
					surely know.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Have We sent down to them any authority, which speaks in support of their
					idols?
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					When We give people a taste of mercy, they rejoice in it. But when adversity
					befalls them, because of what their hands have perpetrated, they begin to
					despair.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Do they not see that God expands the provision for whomever He wills, or
					restricts it? Surely in this are signs for people who believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					So give the relative his rights, and the destitute, and the wayfarer. That is
					best for those who seek God's presence. Those are the prosperous.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					The usury you practice, seeking thereby to multiply people's wealth, will not
					multiply with God. But what you give in charity, desiring God's approval-these
					are the multipliers.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					God is He who created you, then provides for you, then makes you die, then
					brings you back to life. Can any of your idols do any of that? Glorified is He,
					and Exalted above what they associate.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Corruption has appeared on land and sea, because of what people's hands have
					earned, in order to make them taste some of what they have done, so that they
					might return.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Say, "Roam the earth, and observe the fate of those who came before. Most of
					them were idolaters."
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					So devote yourself to the upright religion, before there comes from God a Day
					that cannot be averted. On that Day, they will be shocked.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Whoever disbelieves, upon him falls his disbelief. And whoever acts
					righteously-they are preparing for themselves.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					So that He may reward those who have believed and done the righteous deeds out
					of His bounty. Indeed, He does not love the ungrateful.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					And of His signs is that He sends the winds bearing good news, to give you a
					taste of His mercy, and so that the ships may sail by His command, and so that
					you may seek of His bounty, and so that you may give thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					Before you, We sent messengers to their people. They came to them with clear
					proofs. Then We took revenge on those who sinned. It is incumbent on Us to help
					the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					God is He who sends the winds. They stir up clouds. Then He spreads them in the
					sky as He wills. And He breaks them apart. Then you see rain drops issuing from
					their midst. Then, when He makes it fall upon whom He wills of His servants,
					behold, they rejoice.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					Although they were before this-before it was sent down upon them-in despair.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					So observe the effects of God's mercy-how He revives the earth after it was
					dead. Indeed, He is the Reviver of the dead. He is Capable of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					But if We send a wind, and they see it turning things yellow, they would
					continue thereafter to disbelieve.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					You cannot make the dead hear, nor can you make the deaf hear the call when
					they turn away.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					Nor can you guide the blind out of their error. You can make hear only those
					who believe in Our signs, and so have submitted.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					God is He Who created you weak, then after weakness gave you strength, then
					after strength gave you weakness and gray hair. He creates whatever He wills.
					He is the Omniscient, the Omnipotent.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					On the Day when the Hour takes place, the sinners will swear they had stayed
					but an hour. Thus they were deluded.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					But those endowed with knowledge and faith will say, "You remained in God's
					Book until the Day of Resurrection. This is the Day of Resurrection, but you
					did not know."
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					On that Day, the sinners' excuses will not benefit them, nor will they be
					excused.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					We have cited in this Quran for the people every sort of parable. But even if
					you bring them a miracle, those who disbelieve will say, "You are nothing but
					fakers."
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					God thus seals the hearts of those who do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 30 - The Romans: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					So be patient. The promise of God is true. And do not let those who lack
					certainty belittle you.
				-
		-
			Surah 31 - Luqman
		-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Meem.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					These are the Verses of the Wise Book.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					A guide and a mercy for the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Those who observe the prayer, and pay the obligatory charity, and are certain
					of the Hereafter.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					These are upon guidance from their Lord. These are the successful.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Among the people is he who trades in distracting tales; intending, without
					knowledge, to lead away from God's way, and to make a mockery of it. These will
					have a humiliating punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And when Our Verses are recited to him, he turns away in pride, as though he
					did not hear them, as though there is deafness in his ears. So inform him of a
					painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					As for those who believe and do good deeds-for them are the Gardens of Bliss.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Dwelling therein forever. The promise of God is true. He is the Mighty, the
					Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					He created the heavens without pillars that you can see, and placed stabilizers
					on earth lest it shifts with you, and scattered throughout it all kinds of
					creatures. And from the sky We sent down water, and caused to grow therein of
					every noble pair.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Such is God's creation. Now show me what those besides Him have created. In
					fact, the wicked are in obvious error.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					We endowed Luqman with wisdom: "Give thanks to God." Whoever is appreciative-is
					appreciative for the benefit of his own soul. And whoever is unappreciative-God
					is Sufficient and Praiseworthy.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					When Luqman said to his son, as he advised him, "my son, do not associate
					anything with God, for idolatry is a terrible wrong."
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					We have entrusted the human being with the care of his parents. His mother
					carried him through hardship upon hardship, weaning him in two years. So give
					thanks to Me, and to your parents. To Me is the destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					But if they strive to have you associate with Me something of which you have no
					knowledge, do not obey them. But keep them company in this life, in kindness,
					and follow the path of him who turns to Me. Then to Me is your return; and I
					will inform you of what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					"my son, even if it were the weight of a mustard-seed, in a rock, or in the
					heavens, or on earth, God will bring it to light. God is Kind and Expert.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					O my son, observe the prayer, advocate righteousness, forbid evil, and be
					patient over what has befallen you. These are of the most honorable traits.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And do not treat people with arrogance, nor walk proudly on earth. God does not
					love the arrogant showoffs.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					And moderate your stride, and lower your voice. The most repulsive of voices is
					the donkey's voice."
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Do you not see how God placed at your service everything in the heavens and the
					earth? How He showered you with His blessings, both outward and inward? Yet
					among the people is he who argues about God without knowledge, without
					guidance, and without an enlightening Scripture.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And when it is said to them, "Follow what God has revealed," they say, "Rather,
					we follow what we found our parents devoted to." Even if Satan is calling them
					to the suffering of the Blaze?
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Whoever submits himself wholly to God, and is a doer of good, has grasped the
					most trustworthy handle. With God rests the outcome of all events.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Whoever disbelieves-let not his disbelief sadden you. To Us is their return.
					Then We will inform them of what they did. God knows what lies within the
					hearts.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					We give them a little comfort; then We compel them to a harsh torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					And if you ask them, "Who created the heavens and the earth?" They will say,
					"God." Say, "Praise be to God." But most of them do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					To God belongs everything in the heavens and the earth. God is the Rich, the
					Praised.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					If all the trees on earth were pens, filled by the ocean, with seven more
					oceans besides, the Words of God would not run out. God is Majestic and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Your creation and your resurrection are only as a single soul. God is Hearing
					and Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Have you not seen how God merges the night into the day, and merges the day
					into the night? That He subjected the sun and the moon, each running for a
					stated term? And that God is Cognizant of everything you do?
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					That is because God is the Reality, and what they worship besides Him is
					falsehood, and because God is the Exalted, the Supreme.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Have you not seen how the ships sail through the sea, by the grace of God, to
					show you of His wonders? In that are signs for every persevering, thankful
					person.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					When waves, like canopies, cover them, they call upon God, devoting their
					religion to Him. But when He has delivered them to dry land, some of them
					waver. No one renounces Our revelations except the treacherous blasphemer.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					O people! Be conscious of your Lord, and dread a Day when no parent can avail
					his child, nor can a child avail his parent, in anything. The promise of God is
					true. Therefore, do not let this life deceive you, nor let illusions deceive
					you regarding God.
				-
			-
				Surah 31 - Luqman: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					With God rests the knowledge of the Hour. He sends down the rain, and He knows
					what the wombs contain. No soul knows what it will reap tomorrow, and no soul
					knows in what land it will die. God is All-Knowing, Well-Informed.
				-
		-
			Surah 32 - The Prostration
		-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Alif, Lam, Meem.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					The revelation of the Book, without a doubt, is from the Lord of the Universe.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Yet they say, "He made it up." In fact, it is the Truth from your Lord, to warn
					a people who received no warner before you, that they may be guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					God is He who created the heavens and the earth and everything between them in
					six days, and then established Himself on the Throne. Apart from Him, you have
					no master and no intercessor. Will you not reflect?
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					He regulates all affairs, from the heavens, to the earth. Then it ascends to
					Him on a Day the length of which is a thousand years by your count.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					That is the Knower of the Invisible and the Visible, the Powerful, the
					Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					He who perfected everything He created, and originated the creation of man from
					clay.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Then made his reproduction from an extract of an insignificant fluid.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Then He proportioned him, and breathed into him of His Spirit. Then He gave you
					the hearing, and the eyesight, and the brains-but rarely do you give thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					And they say, "When we are lost into the earth, shall we be in a new creation?"
					In fact, they deny the meeting with their Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Say, "The angel of death put in charge of you will reclaim you. Then to your
					Lord you will be returned."
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					If only you could see the guilty, bowing their heads before their Lord: "Our
					Lord, we have seen and we have heard, so send us back, and we will act
					righteously; we are now convinced."
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					Had We willed, We could have given every soul its guidance, but the declaration
					from Me will come true: "I will fill Hell with jinn and humans, altogether."
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					So taste, because you forgot the meeting of this Day of yours; We have
					forgotten you; so taste the eternal torment for what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					They believe in Our communications, those who, when reminded of them, fall down
					prostrate, and glorify their Lord with praise, and are not proud.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Their sides shun their beds, as they pray to their Lord, out of reverence and
					hope; and from Our provisions to them, they give.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					No soul knows what eye's delight awaits them-a reward for what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Is someone who is faithful like someone who is a sinner? They are not equal.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					As for those who believe and do righteous deeds, for them are the Gardens of
					Shelter-hospitality for what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					But as for those who transgressed, their shelter is the Fire. Every time they
					try to get out of it, they will be brought back into it, and it will be said to
					them, "Taste the suffering of the Fire which you used to deny."
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					We will make them taste the lesser torment, prior to the greater torment, so
					that they may return.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Who is more wrong than he, who, when reminded of his Lord's revelations, turns
					away from them? We will certainly wreak vengeance upon the criminals.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					We gave Moses the Book; so do not be in doubt regarding His encounter; and We
					made it a guidance for the Children of Israel.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And We appointed leaders from among them, guiding by Our command, as long as
					they persevered and were certain of Our communications.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection regarding
					everything they had disputed.
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Is it not a lesson for them, how many generations We have destroyed before
					them, in whose habitations they walk? Surely in that are signs. Do they not
					hear?
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Do they not see how We conduct the water to a dry land, and with it We produce
					vegetation, from which their livestock eat, and themselves? Do they not see?
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And they say, "When is this victory, if you are truthful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Say, "On the day of victory, the faith of those who disbelieved will be of no
					avail to them, and they will not be granted respite."
				-
			-
				Surah 32 - The Prostration: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					So turn away from them, and wait. They too are waiting.
				-
		-
			Surah 33 - The Clans
		-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					O Prophet! Fear God, and do not obey the unbelievers and the hypocrites. God is
					Knowledgeable and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					And follow what is revealed to you from your Lord. God is fully aware of what
					you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And put your trust in God. God is enough as a trustee.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					God did not place two hearts inside any man's body. Nor did He make your wives
					whom you equate with your mothers, your actual mothers. Nor did He make your
					adopted sons, your actual sons. These are your words coming out of your mouths.
					God speaks the truth, and guides to the path.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Call them after their fathers; that is more equitable with God. But if you do
					not know their fathers, then your brethren in faith and your friends. There is
					no blame on you if you err therein, barring what your hearts premeditates. God
					is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					The Prophet is more caring of the believers than they are of themselves, and
					his wives are mothers to them. And blood-relatives are closer to one another in
					God's Book than the believers or the emigrants, though you should do good to
					your friends. That is inscribed in the Book.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Recall that We received a pledge from the prophets, and from you, and from
					Noah, and Abraham, and Moses, and Jesus son of Mary. We received from them a
					solemn pledge.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					That He may ask the sincere about their sincerity. He has prepared for the
					disbelievers a painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Remember God's blessings upon you, when forces came against
					you, and We sent against them a wind, and forces you did not see. God is
					Observant of what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					When they came upon you, from above you, and from beneath you; and the eyes
					became dazed, and the hearts reached the throats, and you harbored doubts about
					God.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					There and then the believers were tested, and were shaken most severely.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					When the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is sickness said, "God and His
					Messenger promised us nothing but illusion."
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And when a group of them said, "people of Yathrib, you cannot make a stand, so
					retreat." And a faction of them asked the Prophet to excuse them, saying, "Our
					homes are exposed," although they were not exposed. They only wanted to flee.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Had it been invaded from its sides, and they were asked to dissent, they would
					have done so with little hesitation.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Although they had made a pledged to God, in the past, that they will not turn
					their backs. A pledge to God is a responsibility.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Say, "Flight will not benefit you, if you flee from death or killing, even then
					you will be given only brief enjoyment."
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					Say, "Who is it who will shield you from God, if He intends adversity for you,
					or intends mercy for you?" Besides God, they will find for themselves neither
					friend nor helper.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					God already knows the hinderers among you, and those who say to their brethren,
					"Come and join us." Rarely do they mobilize for battle.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Being stingy towards you. And when fear approaches, you see them staring at
					you-their eyes rolling-like someone fainting at death. Then, when panic is
					over, they whip you with sharp tongues. They resent you any good. These have
					never believed, so God has nullified their works; a matter easy for God.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					They assumed that the confederates had not withdrawn. But were the confederates
					to advance, they would wish they were in the desert with the Bedouins,
					inquiring about your news. And if they were among you, they would have done
					little fighting.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					You have an excellent example in the Messenger of God; for anyone who seeks God
					and the Last Day, and remembers God frequently.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And when the believers saw the confederates, they said, "This is what God and
					His messenger have promised us; and God and His messenger have told the truth."
					And it only increased them in faith and submission.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Of the believers are men who are true to what they pledged to God. Some of them
					have fulfilled their vows; and some are still waiting, and never wavering.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					That God may reward the truthful for their truthfulness; and punish the
					hypocrites, if He wills, or pardon them. God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					God repelled the disbelievers in their rage; they gained no advantage. God thus
					spared the believers combat. God is Strong and Mighty.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And He brought down from their strongholds those of the People of the Book who
					backed them, and He threw terror into their hearts. Some of them you killed,
					and others you took captive.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					And He made you inherit their land, and their homes, and their possessions, and
					a region you have never stepped on. God has power over all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					O Prophet! Say to your wives, "If you desire the life of this world and its
					finery, then let me compensate you, and release you kindly.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					But if you desire God, His Messenger, and the Home of the Hereafter, then God
					has prepared for the righteous among you a magnificent compensation."
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					O wives of the Prophet! Whoever of you commits a proven indecency, the
					punishment for her will be doubled. And that would be easy for God.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					But whoever of you remains obedient to God and His Messenger, and acts
					righteously, We will give her a double reward; and We have prepared for her a
					generous provision.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					O wives of the Prophet! You are not like any other women, if you observe piety.
					So do not speak too softly, lest the sick at heart lusts after you, but speak
					in an appropriate manner.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And settle in your homes; and do not display yourselves, as in the former days
					of ignorance. And perform the prayer, and give regular charity, and obey God
					and His Messenger. God desires to remove all impurity from you, O People of the
					Household, and to purify you thoroughly.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And remember what is recited in your homes of God's revelations and wisdom. God
					is Kind and Informed.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Muslim men and Muslim women, believing men and believing women, obedient men
					and obedient women, truthful men and truthful women, patient men and patient
					women, humble men and humble women, charitable men and charitable women,
					fasting men and fasting women, men who guard their chastity and women who
					guard, men who remember God frequently and women who remember-God has prepared
					for them a pardon, and an immense reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					It is not for any believer, man or woman, when God and His Messenger have
					decided a matter, to have liberty of choice in their decision. Whoever disobeys
					God and His Messenger has gone far astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					When you said to him whom God had blessed, and you had favored, "Keep your wife
					to yourself, and fear God." But you hid within yourself what God was to reveal.
					And you feared the people, but it was God you were supposed to fear. Then, when
					Zaid ended his relationship with her, We gave her to you in marriage, that
					there may be no restriction for believers regarding the wives of their adopted
					sons, when their relationship has ended. The command of God was fulfilled.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					There is no blame on the Prophet regarding what God has ordained for him. Such
					is the pattern of God among those who passed before. The command of God is an
					absolute decree.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Those who deliver the messages of God, and fear Him, and never fear anyone
					except God. God is sufficient as a reckoner.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Muhammad is not the father of any of your men; but he is the Messenger of God,
					and the seal of the prophets. God is Cognizant of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					O you who believe, remember God with frequent remembrance.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					And glorify Him morning and evening.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					It is He who reaches out to you, and His angels, to bring you out of darkness
					into the light. And He is Ever-Merciful towards the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Their greeting on the Day they meet Him is, "Peace," and He has prepared for
					them a generous reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					O prophet! We have sent you as a witness, and a bearer of good news, and a
					warner.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					And a caller towards God by His leave, and an illuminating beacon.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And give the believers the good news that for them is a great reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					And do not obey the blasphemers and the hypocrites, and ignore their insults,
					and rely on God. God is a sufficient protector.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					O you who believe! When you marry believing women, but then divorce them before
					you have touched them, there is no waiting period for you to observe in respect
					to them; but compensate them, and release them in a graceful manner.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					O Prophet! We have permitted to you your wives to whom you have given their
					dowries, and those you already have, as granted to you by God, and the
					daughters of your paternal uncle, and the daughters of your paternal aunts, and
					the daughters of your maternal uncle, and the daughters of your maternal aunts
					who emigrated with you, and a believing woman who has offered herself to the
					Prophet, if the Prophet desires to marry her, exclusively for you, and not for
					the believers. We know what We have ordained for them regarding their wives and
					those their right-hands possess. This is to spare you any difficulty. God is
					Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					You may defer any of them you wish, and receive any of them you wish. Should
					you desire any of those you had deferred, there is no blame on you. This is
					more proper, so that they will be comforted, and not be grieved, and be content
					with what you have given each one of them. God knows what is within your
					hearts. God is Omniscient and Clement.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Beyond that, no other women are permissible for you, nor can you exchange them
					for other wives, even if you admire their beauty, except those you already
					have. God is Watchful over all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not enter the homes of the Prophet, unless you are given
					permission to come for a meal; and do not wait for its preparation. And when
					you are invited, go in. And when you have eaten, disperse, without lingering
					for conversation. This irritates the Prophet, and he shies away from you, but
					God does not shy away from the truth. And when you ask his wives for something,
					ask them from behind a screen; that is purer for your hearts and their hearts.
					You must never offend the Messenger of God, nor must you ever marry his wives
					after him, for that would be an enormity with God.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Whether you declare a thing, or hide it, God is Aware of all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					There is no blame on them concerning their fathers, or their sons, or their
					brothers, or their brothers' sons, or their sisters' sons, or their women, or
					their female servants. But they should remain conscious of God. God is Witness
					over all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					God and His angels give blessings to the Prophet. O you who believe, call for
					blessings on him, and greet him with a prayer of peace.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Those who insult God and His Messenger, God has cursed them in this life and in
					the Hereafter, and has prepared for them a demeaning punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Those who harm believing men and believing women, for acts they did not commit,
					bear the burden of perjury and a flagrant sin.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					O Prophet! Tell your wives, and your daughters, and the women of the believers,
					to lengthen their garments. That is more proper, so they will be recognized and
					not harassed. God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					If the hypocrites, and those with sickness in their hearts, and the
					rumormongers in the City, do not desist, We will incite you against them; then
					they will not be your neighbors there except for a short while.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					They are cursed; wherever they are found, they should be captured and killed
					outright.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					Such has been God's precedent with those who passed away before. You will find
					no change in God's system.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					The people ask you about the Hour. Say, "The knowledge thereof rests with God.
					But what do you know? Perhaps the hour is near."
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					God has cursed the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a Blaze.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					Dwelling therein forever, not finding a protector or a savior.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					The Day when their faces are flipped into the Fire, they will say, "If only we
					had obeyed God and obeyed the Messenger."
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					And they will say, "Lord, we have obeyed our superiors and our dignitaries, but
					they led us away from the way.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					Lord, give them double the punishment, and curse them with a great curse."
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not be like those who abused Moses; but God cleared him
					of what they said. He was distinguished with God.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Be conscious of God, and speak in a straightforward manner.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					He will rectify your conduct for you, and will forgive you your sins. Whoever
					obeys God and His Messenger has won a great victory.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					We offered the Trust to the heavens, and the earth, and the mountains; but they
					refused to bear it, and were apprehensive of it; but the human being accepted
					it. He was unfair and ignorant.
				-
			-
				Surah 33 - The Clans: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					God will punish the hypocrites, men and women, and the idolaters, men and
					women. And God will redeem the believers, men and women. God is Ever-Forgiving,
					Most Merciful.
				-
		-
			Surah 34 - Saba
		-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Praise be to God, to Whom belongs everything in the heavens and the earth; and
					praise be to Him in the Hereafter. He is the Wise, the Expert.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					He knows what penetrates into the earth, and what comes out of it, and what
					descends from the sky, and what ascends to it. He is the Merciful, the
					Forgiving.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "The Hour will not come upon us." Say, "Yes indeed,
					by my Lord, it will come upon you. He is the Knower of the unseen." Not an
					atom's weight in the heavens and the earth, or anything smaller or larger,
					escapes His knowledge. All are in a Clear Record.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					That He may recompense those who believe and do good works. Those will have
					forgiveness, and a generous provision.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					As for those who strive against Our revelations, seeking to undermine them-for
					them is a punishment of a painful plague.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Those who received knowledge know that what is revealed to you from your Lord
					is the truth; and it guides to the path of the Majestic, the Praiseworthy.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieved said, "Shall we point out to you a man, who will tell you
					that, once torn into shreds, you will be in a new creation?
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Did he invent a lie about God, or is there madness in him?" Indeed, those who
					do not believe in the Hereafter are in torment, and far astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Do they not reflect upon what lies before them and behind them, of the heaven
					and the earth? If We will, We can make the earth cave in beneath them, or make
					pieces of the sky fall down on them. In that is a sign for every devout
					servant.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					We bestowed upon David favor from Us: "mountains, and birds: echo with him."
					And We softened iron for him.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					"Make coats of armor, and measure the links well; and work righteousness. I am
					Observant of everything you do."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					And for Solomon the wind-its outward journey was one month, and its return
					journey was one month. And We made a spring of tar flow for him. And there were
					sprites that worked under him, by the leave of his Lord. But whoever of them
					swerved from Our command, We make him taste of the punishment of the Inferno.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					They made for him whatever he wished: sanctuaries, statues, bowls like pools,
					and heavy cauldrons. "House of David, work with appreciation," but a few of My
					servants are appreciative.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Then, when We decreed death for him, nothing indicated his death to them except
					an earthworm eating at his staff. Then, when he fell down, it became clear to
					the sprites that, had they known the unseen, they would not have remained in
					the demeaning torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					In Sheba's homeland there used to be a wonder: two gardens, on the right, and
					on the left. "Eat of your Lord's provision, and give thanks to Him." A good
					land, and a forgiving Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					But they turned away, so We unleashed against them the flood of the dam; and We
					substituted their two gardens with two gardens of bitter fruits, thorny shrubs,
					and meager harvest.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					We thus penalized them for their ingratitude. Would We penalize any but the
					ungrateful?
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Between them and the towns We had blessed, We placed prominent towns, and We
					made the travel between them easy. "Travel between them by night and day, in
					safety."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					But they said, "Our Lord, lengthen the distances of our journeys." They wronged
					themselves; so We made them history, and We scattered them in every direction.
					In this are lessons for every steadfast and appreciative person.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Satan was correct in his assessment of them. They followed him, except for a
					group of believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					He had no authority over them; except that We willed to distinguish him who
					believes in the Hereafter, from him who is doubtful about it. Your Lord is
					Guardian over all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Say, "Call upon those whom you claim besides God. They possess not an atom's
					weight in the heavens or the earth, and they possess no share of either, and He
					has no backers from among them."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Intercession with Him is of no value, except for someone He has permitted.
					Until, when fear has subsided from their hearts, they will say, "What did your
					Lord say?" They will say, "The truth, and He is the High, the Great."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Say, "Who provides for you from the heavens and the earth?" Say, "God. And
					Either you, or we, are rightly guided, or in evident error."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Say, "You will not be asked about our misdeeds, nor will we be asked about what
					you do."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Say, "Our Lord will bring us together; then He will judge between us equitably.
					He is the All-Knowing Judge."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Say, "Show me those you have attached to Him as associates. No indeed! But He
					is God, the Powerful, the Wise."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					We sent you only universally to all people, a herald and warner, but most
					people do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And they say, "When is this promise due, if you are truthful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Say, "You are promised a Day, which you cannot postpone by one hour, nor bring
					forward."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "We will never believe in this Quran, nor in what
					came before it." If you could only see the wrongdoers, captive before their
					Lord, throwing back allegations at one another. Those who were oppressed will
					say to those who were arrogant, "Were it not for you, we would have been
					believers."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Those who were arrogant will say to those who were oppressed, "Was it us who
					turned you away from guidance when it came to you? No indeed, you yourselves
					were sinful."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And those who were oppressed will say to those who were arrogant, "It was your
					scheming by night and day; as you instructed us to reject God, and to set up
					rivals to Him." They will hide their remorse when they see the retribution. We
					will put yokes around the necks of those who disbelieved. Will they be repaid
					for anything other than what they used to do?
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					We sent no warner to any town, without its affluent saying, "We reject what you
					are sent with."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					And they say, "We have more wealth and more children, and we will not be
					punished."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Say, "My Lord spreads out His bounty to whomever He wills, or restricts it; but
					most people do not know."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					It is neither your wealth nor your children that bring you closer to Us, but it
					is he who believes and does good deeds. These will have a double reward for
					what they did; and they will reside in the Chambers, in peace and security.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					But those who work against Our revelations, seeking to undermine them-those
					will be summoned to the punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Say, "My Lord extends the provision to whomever He wills of His servants, or
					withholds it. Anything you spend, He will replace it. He is the Best of
					providers."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					On the Day when He gathers them all together, then say to the angels, "Was it
					you these used to worship?"
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					They will say, "Be You glorified; You are our Master, not them. In fact, they
					used to worship the jinn, and most of them had faith in them."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					"Today, none of you has the power to profit or harm the other." And We will say
					to those who did wrong, "Taste the agony of the Fire which you used to deny."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					And when Our enlightening Verses are recited to them, they say, "This is
					nothing but a man who wants to divert you from what your ancestors used to
					worship." And they say, "This is nothing but a fabricated lie." And when the
					Truth comes to them, the blasphemers say of the Truth, "This is nothing but
					plain magic."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					But We gave them no book to study, and We did not send them any warner before
					you.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					Those before them also denied the Truth, yet they have not attained one-tenth
					of what We had given them. They rejected My messengers, so how was My
					disapproval?
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Say, "I offer you a single advice: devote yourselves to God, in pairs, or
					individually; and reflect. There is no madness in your friend. He is just a
					warner to you, before the advent of a severe punishment."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					Say, "Whatever compensation I have asked of you, is yours. My compensation
					comes only from God, and He is Witness over all things."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					Say, "My Lord projects the truth. He is the Knower of the Unseen."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					Say, "The Truth has come; while falsehood can neither originate, nor
					regenerate."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Say, "If I err, I err only to my own loss; but if I am guided, it is by what my
					Lord inspires me. He is Hearing and Near."
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					If you could only see when they are terrified, and there is no escape, and they
					are seized from a nearby place.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					And they say, "We have believed in it." But how can they attain it from a
					distant place?
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					They have rejected it in the past, and made allegations from a far-off place.
				-
			-
				Surah 34 - Saba: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					A barrier will be placed between them and what they desire, as was done
					formerly with their counterparts. They were in disturbing doubt.
				-
		-
			Surah 35 - The Angels
		-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Praise be to God, Originator of the heavens and the earth, Maker of the angels
					messengers with wings-double, triple, and quadruple. He adds to creation as He
					wills. God is Able to do all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Whatever mercy God unfolds for the people, none can withhold it. And if He
					withholds it, none can release it thereafter. He is the Exalted in Power, Full
					of Wisdom.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					O people! Remember God's blessings upon you. Is there a creator other than God
					who provides for you from the heaven and the earth? There is no god but He. So
					how are you misled?
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					If they reject you, messengers before you were also rejected. To God all
					matters are returned.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					O people! The promise of God is true; so let not the lowly life seduce you, and
					let not the Tempter tempt you away from God.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Satan is an enemy to you, so treat him as an enemy. He only invites his gang to
					be among the inmates of the Inferno.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve will suffer a harsh punishment, but those who believe and
					do righteous deeds will have forgiveness and a great reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					What of him whose evil deed was made attractive to him, and so he regards it as
					good? God leads astray whomever He wills, and He guides whomever He wills.
					Therefore, do not waste yourself sorrowing over them. God knows exactly what
					they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					God is He who sends the winds, which agitate clouds, which We drive to a dead
					land, and thereby revive the ground after it had died. Likewise is the
					Resurrection.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Whoever desires honor-all honor belongs to God. To Him ascends speech that is
					pure, and He elevates righteous conduct. As for those who plot evil, a terrible
					punishment awaits them, and the planning of these will fail.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					God created you from dust, then from a small drop; then He made you pairs. No
					female conceives, or delivers, except with His knowledge. No living thing
					advances in years, or its life is shortened, except it be in a Record. That is
					surely easy for God.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					The two seas are not the same. One is fresh, sweet, good to drink, while the
					other is salty and bitter. Yet from each you eat tender meat, and extract
					jewelry which you wear. And you see the ships plowing through them, so that you
					may seek of His bounty, so that you may give thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					He merges the night into the day, and He merges the day into the night; and He
					regulates the sun and the moon, each running for a stated term. Such is God,
					your Lord; His is the sovereignty. As for those you call upon besides Him, they
					do not possess a speck.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					If you pray to them, they cannot hear your prayer. And even if they heard, they
					would not answer you. And on the Day of Resurrection, they will reject your
					partnership. None informs you like an Expert.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					O people! It is you who are the poor, in need of God; while God is the Rich,
					the Praiseworthy.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					If He wills, He can do away with you, and produce a new creation.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And that would not be difficult for God.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					No burdened soul can carry the burden of another. Even if one weighted down
					calls for help with its burden, nothing can be lifted from it, even if they
					were related. You are to warn those who fear their Lord inwardly, and perform
					the prayer. He who purifies himself purifies himself for his own good. To God
					is the ultimate return.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Not equal are the blind and the seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Nor are the darkness and the light.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Nor are the shade and the torrid heat.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Nor are equal the living and the dead. God causes whomever He wills to hear,
					but you cannot make those in the graves hear.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					You are only a warner.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					We sent you with the truth; a bearer of good news, and a warner. There is no
					community but a warner has passed through it.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					If they disbelieve you, those before them also disbelieved. Their messengers
					came to them with the clear proofs, with the Psalms, and with the Enlightening
					Scripture.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Then I seized those who disbelieved-so how was My rejection?
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Have you not seen that God sends down water from the sky? With it We produce
					fruits of various colors. And in the mountains are streaks of white and
					red-varying in their hue-and pitch-black.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Likewise, human beings, animals, and livestock come in various colors. From
					among His servants, the learned fear God. God is Almighty, Oft-Forgiving.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Those who recite the Book of God, and perform the prayer, and spend of what We
					have provided for them, secretly and publicly, expect a trade that will not
					fail.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					He will pay them their dues in full, and will increase them from His bounty. He
					is Forgiving and Appreciative.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					What We inspired in you, of the Book, is the truth, confirming what preceded
					it. God is Well-Informed of His servants, All-Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Then We passed the Book to those of Our servants whom We chose. Some of them
					wrong their souls, and some follow a middle course, and some are in the
					foremost in good deeds by God's leave; that is the greatest blessing.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					The Gardens of Eden, which they will enter. They will be adorned therein with
					gold bracelets and pearls, and their garments therein will be of silk.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And they will say, "Praise God, who has lifted all sorrow from us. Our Lord is
					Most Forgiving, Most Appreciative.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					He Who settled us in the Home of Permanence, by His grace, where boredom will
					not touch us, and fatigue will not afflict us."
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					As for those who disbelieve, for them is the Fire of Hell, wherein they will
					never be finished off and die, nor will its punishment be lightened for them.
					Thus We will repay every ingrate.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					And they will scream therein, "Our Lord, let us out, and we will act
					righteously, differently from the way we used to act." Did We not give you a
					life long enough, in which anyone who wanted to understand would have
					understood? And the warner did come to you. So taste. The evildoers will have
					no helper.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					God is the Knower of the future of the heavens and the earth. He knows what the
					hearts contain.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					It is He who made you successors on earth. Whoever disbelieves, his disbelief
					will recoil upon him. The disbelief of the disbelievers adds only to their
					Lord's disfavor of them. The disbelief of the disbelievers adds only to their
					perdition.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Say, "Have you considered those partners of yours that you worship instead of
					God? Show me what they have created on earth. Or do they have any share in the
					heavens?" Or have We given them a book whose clear teachings they follow? In
					fact, the wrongdoers promise one another nothing but delusions.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					God holds the heavens and the earth, lest they fall apart. And were they to
					fall apart, there is none to hold them together except He. He is Most Clement,
					Most Forgiving.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					And they swore by God with their solemn oaths, that if a warner came to them,
					they would be more guided than any other people. Yet when a warner came to
					them, it only increased them in aversion.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Priding themselves on earth, and scheming evil. But evil scheming overwhelms
					none but its authors. Do they expect anything but the precedent of the
					ancients? You will not find any change in God's practice, and you will not find
					any substitute to God's practice.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Have they not journeyed in the land and observed the fate of those who preceded
					them? They were superior to them in strength. But nothing can defeat God in the
					heavens or on Earth. He is indeed Omniscient and Omnipotent.
				-
			-
				Surah 35 - The Angels: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					If God were to punish the people for what they have earned, He would not leave
					a single living creature on its surface. But He defers them until a stated
					time. Then, when their time has arrived-God is Observant of His creatures.
				-
		-
			Surah 36 - Ya-seen
		-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Ya, Seen.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					By the Wise Quran.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					You are one of the messengers.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					On a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					The revelation of the Almighty, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					To warn a people whose ancestors were not warned, and so they are unaware.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					The Word was realized against most of them, for they do not believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					We placed shackles around their necks, up to their chins, so they are
					stiff-necked.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					And We placed a barrier in front of them, and a barrier behind them, and We
					have enshrouded them, so they cannot see.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					It is the same for them, whether you warn them, or do not warn them-they will
					not believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					You warn only him who follows the Message, and fears the Most Gracious
					inwardly. So give him good news of forgiveness, and a generous reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					It is We who revive the dead; and We write down what they have forwarded, and
					their traces. We have tallied all things in a Clear Record.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And cite for them the parable of the landlords of the town-when the messengers
					came to it.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					We sent them two messengers, but they denied them both, so We reinforced them
					with a third. They said, "We are messengers to you."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					They said, "You are nothing but humans like us, and the Gracious did not send
					down anything; you are only lying."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					They said, "Our Lord knows that we are messengers to you.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And our only duty is clear communication."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					They said, "We see an evil omen in you; if you do not give up, we will stone
					you, and a painful punishment from us will befall you."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					They said, "Your evil omen is upon you. Is it because you were reminded? But
					you are an extravagant people."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Then a man came running from the remotest part of the city. He said, "my
					people, follow the messengers.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Follow those who ask you of no wage, and are themselves guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					"And why should I not worship Him Who created me, and to Whom you will be
					returned?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Shall I take other gods instead of Him? If the Merciful desires harm for me,
					their intercession will not avail me at all, nor will they save me.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					In that case, I would be completely lost.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					I have believed in your Lord, so listen to me."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					It was said, "Enter Paradise." He said, "If only my people knew.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					How my Lord has forgiven me, and made me one of the honored."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					After him, We sent down no hosts from heaven to his people; nor would We ever
					send any down.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					It was just one Cry, and they were stilled.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Alas for the servants. No messenger ever came to them, but they ridiculed him.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Have they not considered how many generations We destroyed before them; and
					that unto them they will not return?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					All of them, every single one of them, will be arraigned before Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And there is a sign for them in the dead land: We give it life, and produce
					from it grains from which they eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And We place in it gardens of palm-trees and vines, and cause springs to gush
					out of it.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					That they may eat from its fruits, although their hands did not make it. Will
					they not be appreciative?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Glory be to Him who created all the pairs; of what the earth produces, and of
					their own selves, and of what they do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Another sign for them is the night: We strip the day out of it-and they are in
					darkness.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					And the sun runs towards its destination. Such is the design of the Almighty,
					the All-Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					And the moon: We have disposed it in phases, until it returns like the old
					twig.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					The sun is not to overtake the moon, nor is the night to outpace the day. Each
					floats in an orbit.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Another sign for them is that We carried their offspring in the laden Ark.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					And We created for them the like of it, in which they ride.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					If We will, We can drown them-with no screaming to be heard from them, nor will
					they be saved.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Except by a mercy from Us, and enjoyment for a while.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					Yet when it is said to them, "Beware of what lies before you, and what lies
					behind you, that you may receive mercy."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Yet never came to them a sign of their Lord's signs, but they turned away from
					it.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And when it is said to them, "Spend of what God has provided for you," those
					who disbelieve say to those who believe, "Shall we feed someone whom God could
					feed, if He so willed? You must be deeply misguided."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					And they say, "When will this promise be, if you are truthful?"
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					All they can expect is a single blast, which will seize them while they feud.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					They will not be able to make a will, nor will they return to their families.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					The Trumpet will be blown, then behold, they will rush from the tombs to their
					Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					They will say, "Woe to us! Who resurrected us from our resting-place?" This is
					what the Most Gracious had promised, and the messengers have spoken the truth."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					It will be but a single scream; and behold, they will all be brought before Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					On that Day, no soul will be wronged in the least, and you will be recompensed
					only for what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					The inhabitants of Paradise, on that Day, will be happily busy.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					They and their spouses, in shades, reclining on couches.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					They will have therein fruits. They will have whatever they call for.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Peace-a saying from a Most Merciful Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					But step aside today, you criminals.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					Did I not covenant with you, O Children of Adam, that you shall not serve the
					devil? That he is your sworn enemy?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					And that you shall serve Me? This is a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					He has misled a great multitude of you. Did you not understand?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					This is Hellfire, which you were promised.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					Roast in it today, because you persistently disbelieved.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					On this Day, We will seal their mouths, and their hands will speak to Us, and
					their feet will testify to everything they had done.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					If We will, We can blind their eyes as they rush towards the path-but how will
					they see?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					And if We will, We can cripple them in their place; so they can neither move
					forward, nor go back.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					Whomever We grant old age, We reverse his development. Do they not understand?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					We did not teach him poetry, nor is it proper for him. It is only a reminder,
					and a Clear Quran.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					That he may warn whoever is alive, and prove the Word against the faithless.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					Have they not seen that We created for them, of Our Handiwork, livestock that
					they own?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					And We subdued them for them. Some they ride, and some they eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					And they have in them other benefits, and drinks. Will they not give thanks?
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					Yet they have taken to themselves gods other than God, that perhaps they may be
					helped.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					They cannot help them, although they are arrayed as troops for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					So let their words not sadden you. We know what they conceal, and what they
					reveal.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					Does the human being not consider that We created him from a seed? Yet he
					becomes a fierce adversary.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					And he produces arguments against Us, and he forgets his own creation. He says,
					"Who will revive the bones when they have decayed?"
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					Say, "He who initiated them in the first instance will revive them. He has
					knowledge of every creation."
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					He who produced fuel for you from the green trees, with which you kindle a
					fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					Is not He who created the heavens and the earth able to create the like of
					them? Certainly. He is the Supreme All-Knowing Creator.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					His command, when He wills a thing, is to say to it, "Be," and it comes to be.
				-
			-
				Surah 36 - Ya-seen: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					So glory be to Him in whose hand is the dominion of everything, and to Him you
					will be returned.
				-
		-
			Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks
		-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					By the aligners aligning.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					And the drivers driving.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And the reciters of the Reminder.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Your God is indeed One.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Lord of the heavens and the earth, and everything between them; and Lord of the
					Easts.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					We have adorned the lower heaven with the beauty of the planets.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And guarded it against every defiant devil.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					They cannot eavesdrop on the Supernal Elite, for they get bombarded from every
					side.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Repelled-they will have a lingering torment.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Except for him who snatches a fragment-he gets pursued by a piercing
					projectile.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Inquire of them, "Are they more difficult to create, or the others We created?"
					We created them from sticky clay.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					But you wonder, and they ridicule.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And when reminded, they pay no attention.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					And when they see a sign, they ridicule.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					And they say, "This is nothing but plain magic.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					When we have died and become dust and bones, shall we be resurrected?
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And our ancestors of old?"
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Say, "Yes indeed, and you will be totally subdued."
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					It will be a single nudge, and they will be staring.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					They will say, "Woe to us. This is the Day of Judgment."
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					"This is the Day of Separation which you used to deny.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Gather those who did wrong, and their mates, and what they used to worship.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Besides God, and lead them to the way to Hell.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And stop them. They are to be questioned."
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					What is the matter with you? Why do you not help one another?
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					In fact, on that Day, they will be submissive.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					They will come to one another, questioning one another.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					They will say, "You used to come at us from the right."
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					They will say, "You yourselves were not believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					We had no authority over you. You yourselves were rebellious people.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					The Word of our Lord has been realized against us. We are tasting it.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					We seduced you. We were seducers."
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					On that Day, they will share in the punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Thus We deal with the sinners.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					When it was said to them, "There is no god except God," they grew arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					And said, "Are we to abandon our gods for a mad poet?"
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					In fact, he came with the truth, and he confirmed the messengers.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Most assuredly, you will taste the painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					And you will be repaid only for what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 37 - Those Who Set The Ranks: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Except for God's sincere servants.
				-
