			-
				-
					We sent down upon you the Book for mankind in truth. He who follows guidance
					does so for the good of his soul. And he who strays in error does so to its
					detriment. You are not their overseer.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					God takes the souls at the time of their death, and those that have not died
					during their sleep. He retains those for which He has decreed death, and He
					releases the others until a predetermined time. In that are signs for people
					who reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Or have they chosen intercessors other than God? Say, "Even though they have no
					power over anything, and are devoid of reason?"
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Say, "All intercession is up to God. To Him belongs the kingdom of the heavens
					and the earth. Then to Him you will be returned."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					When God alone is mentioned, the hearts of those who do not believe in the
					Hereafter shrink with resentment. But when those other than Him are mentioned,
					they become filled with joy.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Say, "Our God, Initiator of the heavens and the earth, Knower of all secrets
					and declarations. You will judge between your servants regarding what they had
					differed about."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					If those who did wrong owned everything on earth, and the like of it with it,
					they would redeem themselves with it from the terrible suffering on the Day of
					Resurrection. But there will appear to them from God what they never
					anticipated.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					There will appear to them the evils of their deeds, and they will be surrounded
					by what they used to ridicule.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					When adversity touches the human being, he calls on Us. But then, when We favor
					him with a blessing from Us, he says, "I have attained this by virtue of my
					knowledge." However, it is a test, but most of them do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					Those before them said it, but what they had earned did not avail them.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					The evils of their deeds caught up with them. And the wrongdoers among these
					will also be afflicted by the evils of what they earned, and they cannot
					prevent it.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Do they not know that God extends the provision to whomever He wills, and
					constricts it? In that are signs for people who believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					Say, "My servants who have transgressed against themselves: do not despair of
					God's mercy, for God forgives all sins. He is indeed the Forgiver, the
					Clement."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					And turn to your Lord, and submit to Him, before the retribution comes upon
					you. Then you will not be helped.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					And follow the best of what was revealed to you from your Lord, before the
					punishment comes upon you suddenly, while you are unaware.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					So that a soul may not say, "How sorry I am, for having neglected my duty to
					God, and for having been of the scoffers."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Or say, "Had God guided me; I would have been of the pious."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Or say, when it sees the penalty, "If only I had another chance, I would be of
					the virtuous."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Yes indeed! My Verses did come to you, but you called them lies, turned
					arrogant, and were of the faithless.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					On the Day of Resurrection, you will see those who told lies about God with
					their faces blackened. Is there not a place in Hell for the arrogant?
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					And God will save those who maintained righteousness to their place of
					salvation. No harm will touch them, nor will they grieve.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					God is the Creator of all things, and He is in Charge of all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					To Him belong the reins of the heavens and the earth. But those who blaspheme
					against the revelations of God-it is they who are the losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					Say, "Is it other than God you instruct me to worship, you ignorant ones?"
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					It was revealed to you, and to those before you, that if you idolize, your
					works will be in vain, and you will be of the losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					Rather, worship God, and be of the appreciative.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					They have not esteemed God as He ought to be esteemed. The entire earth will be
					in His grip on the Day of Resurrection, and the heavens will be folded in His
					right. Immaculate is He, and Transcendent He is beyond the associations they
					make.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					And the Trumpet will be sounded, whereupon everyone in the heavens and the
					earth will be stunned, except whomever God wills. Then it will be sounded
					another time, whereupon they will rise up, looking on.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					And the earth will shine with the Light of its Lord; and the Book will be put
					in place; and the prophets and the witnesses will be brought in; and Judgment
					will be passed among them equitably, and they will not be wronged.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					And every soul will be fully compensated for what it had done. He is well aware
					of what they do.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieved will be driven to Hell in throngs. Until, when they have
					reached it, and its gates are opened, its keepers will say to them, "Did not
					messengers from among you come to you, reciting to you the revelations of your
					Lord, and warning you of the meeting of this Day of yours?" They will say,
					"Yes, but the verdict of punishment is justified against the disbelievers."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					It will be said, "Enter the gates of Hell, to abide therein eternally." How
					wretched is the destination of the arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					And those who feared their Lord will be led to Paradise in throngs. Until, when
					they have reached it, and its gates are opened, its keepers will say to them,
					"Peace be upon you, you have been good, so enter it, to abide therein
					eternally."
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					And they will say, "Praise be to God, who has fulfilled His promise to us, and
					made us inherit the land, enjoying Paradise as we please." How excellent is the
					reward of the workers.
				-
			-
				Surah 39 - The Troops: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					And you will see the angels hovering around the Throne, glorifying their Lord
					with praise. And it will be judged between them equitably, and it will be said,
					"Praise be to God, Lord of the Worlds."
				-
		-
			Surah 40 - The Forgiver
		-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Ha, Meem.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					The sending down of the Scripture is from God the Almighty, the Omniscient.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Forgiver of sins, Accepter of repentance, Severe in punishment, Bountiful in
					bounty. There is no god but He. To Him is the ultimate return.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					None argues against God's revelations except those who disbelieve. So do not be
					impressed by their activities in the land.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Before them the people of Noah rejected the truth, as did the confederates
					after them. Every community plotted against their messenger, to capture him.
					And they argued with falsehood, to defeat with it the truth. But I seized them.
					What a punishment it was!
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Thus the sentence of your Lord became realized against those who disbelieve,
					that they are to be inmates of the Fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Those who carry the Throne, and those around it, glorify their Lord with
					praise, and believe in Him, and ask for forgiveness for those who believe: "Our
					Lord, You have encompassed everything in mercy and knowledge; so forgive those
					who repent and follow Your path, and protect them from the agony of the Blaze.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					And admit them, Our Lord, into the Gardens of Eternity, which You have promised
					them, and the righteous among their parents, and their spouses, and their
					offspring. You are indeed the Almighty, the Most Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					And shield them from the evil deeds. Whomever You shield from the evil deeds,
					on that Day, You have had mercy on him. That is the supreme achievement."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieved will be addressed, "The loathing of God is greater than
					your loathing of yourselves-for you were invited to the faith, but you
					refused."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					They will say, "Our Lord, you made us die twice, and twice you gave us life.
					Now we acknowledge our sins. Is there any way out?"
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					That is because when God alone was called upon, you disbelieved; but when
					others were associated with Him, you believed. Judgment rests with God the
					Sublime, the Majestic.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					It is He who shows you His wonders, and sends down sustenance from the sky for
					you. But none pays heed except the repentant.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					So call upon God, with sincere devotion to Him, even though the disbelievers
					resent it.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Exalted in rank, Owner of the Throne. He conveys the Spirit, by His command,
					upon whomever He wills of His servants, to warn of the Day of Encounter.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					The Day when they will emerge, nothing about them will be concealed from God.
					"To whom does the sovereignty belong today?" "To God, the One, the
					Irresistible."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					On that Day, every soul will be recompensed for what it had earned. There will
					be no injustice on that Day. God is quick to settle accounts.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And warn them of the Day of Imminence, when the hearts are at the throats,
					choking them. The evildoers will have no intimate friend, and no intercessor to
					be obeyed.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					He knows the deceptions of the eyes, and what the hearts conceal.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					God judges with justice, while those whom they invoke besides Him cannot judge
					with anything. It is God who is the Hearing, the Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Have they not travelled through the earth, and seen the consequences for those
					before them? They were stronger than them, and they left more impact on earth.
					But God seized them for their sins, and they had no defender against God.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					That is because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but
					they disbelieved, so God seized them. He is Strong, Severe in retribution.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					We sent Moses with Our signs, and a clear authority.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					To Pharaoh, Hamaan, and Quaroon. But they said, "A lying sorcerer."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Then, when he came to them with the truth from Us, they said, "Kill the sons of
					those who have believed with him, and spare their daughters." But the scheming
					of the unbelievers can only go astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Pharaoh said, "Leave me to kill Moses, and let him appeal to his Lord. I fear
					he may change your religion, or spread disorder in the land."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Moses said, "I have sought the protection of my Lord and your Lord, from every
					tyrant who does not believe in the Day of Account."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					A believing man from Pharaoh's family, who had concealed his faith, said, "Are
					you going to kill a man for saying, `My Lord is God,' and he has brought you
					clear proofs from your Lord? If he is a liar, his lying will rebound upon him;
					but if he is truthful, then some of what he promises you will befall you. God
					does not guide the extravagant imposter.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					O my people! Yours is the dominion today, supreme in the land; but who will
					help us against God's might, should it fall upon us?" Pharaoh said, "I do not
					show you except what I see, and I do not guide you except to the path of
					prudence."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					The one who had believed said, "my people, I fear for you the like of the day
					of the confederates.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Like the fate of the people of Noah, and Aad, and Thamood, and those after
					them. God wants no injustice for the servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					O my people, I fear for you the Day of Calling Out.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					The Day when you will turn and flee, having no defender against God. Whomever
					God misguides has no guide."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Joseph had come to you with clear revelations, but you continued to doubt what
					he came to you with. Until, when he perished, you said, "God will never send a
					messenger after him." Thus God leads astray the outrageous skeptic.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Those who argue against God's revelations, without any proof having come to
					them-a heinous sin in the sight of God, and of those who believe. Thus God
					seals the heart of every proud bully.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					And Pharaoh said, "Hamaan, build me a tower, that I may reach the pathways.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					The pathways of the heavens, so that I may glance at the God of Moses; though I
					think he is lying." Thus Pharaoh's evil deeds were made to appear good to him,
					and he was averted from the path. Pharaoh's guile was only in defeat.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					The one who had believed said, "my people, follow me, and I will guide you to
					the path of rectitude."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					"my people, the life of this world is nothing but fleeting enjoyment, but the
					Hereafter is the Home of Permanence.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Whoever commits a sin will be repaid only with its like. But whoever works
					righteousness, whether male or female, and is a believer-these will enter
					Paradise, where they will be provided for without account.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					O my people, how is it that I call you to salvation, and you call me to the
					Fire?
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					You call me to reject God, and to associate with Him what I have no knowledge
					of, while I call you to the Mighty Forgiver.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Without a doubt, what you call me to has no say in this world, or in the
					Hereafter; and our turning back is to God; and the transgressors are the
					inmates of the Fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					You will remember what I am telling you, so I commit my case to God. God is
					Observant of the servants."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					So God protected him from the evils of their scheming, while a terrible torment
					besieged Pharaoh's clan.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					The Fire. They will be exposed to it morning and evening. And on the Day the
					Hour takes place: "Admit the clan of Pharaoh to the most intense agony."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					As they quarrel in the Fire, the weak will say to those who were arrogant, "We
					were followers of yours; will you then spare us a portion of the Fire?"
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					Those who were arrogant will say, "We are all in it; God has judged between the
					servants."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					And those in the Fire will say to the keepers of Hell, "Call to your Lord to
					lessen our suffering for one day."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					They will say, "Did not your messengers come to you with clear signs?" They
					will say, "Yes." They will say, "Then pray, but the prayers of the disbelievers
					will always be in vain."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					Most surely We will support Our messengers and those who believe, in this life,
					and on the Day the witnesses arise.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					The Day when their excuses will not profit the wrongdoers, and the curse will
					be upon them, and they will have the Home of Misery.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					We gave Moses guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the Scripture.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					A guide and a reminder for those endowed with reason.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					So be patient. The promise of God is true. And ask forgiveness for your sin,
					and proclaim the praise of your Lord evening and morning.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					Those who dispute regarding God's revelations without any authority having come
					to them-there is nothing in their hearts but the feeling of greatness, which
					they will never attain. So seek refuge in God; for He is the All-Hearing, the
					All-Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					Certainly the creation of the heavens and the earth is greater than the
					creation of humanity, but most people do not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					Not equal are the blind and the seeing. Nor are those who believe and work
					righteousness equal to the sinners. How little you reflect.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Indeed, the Hour is coming; there is no doubt about it; but most people do not
					believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					Your Lord has said, "Pray to Me, and I will respond to you. But those who are
					too proud to worship Me will enter Hell forcibly."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					It is God Who made the night for you, that you may rest therein; and the day
					allowing sight. God is gracious towards the people, but most people do not give
					thanks.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					Such is God, your Lord, Creator of all things. There is no god except Him; so
					how could you turn away?
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 63
			-
				-
					Thus are turned away those who dispute the signs of God.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 64
			-
				-
					It is God who made the earth a habitat for you, and the sky a structure. And He
					designed you, and designed you well; and He provided you with the good things.
					Such is God, your Lord; so Blessed is God, Lord of the Worlds.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 65
			-
				-
					He is the Living One. There is no god except He. So pray to Him, devoting your
					religion to Him. Praise be to God, the Lord of the Worlds.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 66
			-
				-
					Say, "I was prohibited from worshiping those you invoke besides God, now that
					clear revelations have come to me from my Lord; and I was commanded to submit
					to the Lord of the Worlds."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 67
			-
				-
					It is He who created you from dust, then from a seed, then from an embryo, then
					He brings you out as an infant, then He lets you reach your maturity, then you
					become elderly-although some of you die sooner-so that you may reach a
					predetermined age, so that you may understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 68
			-
				-
					It is He who gives life and death; and when He decides on a thing, He just says
					to it, "Be," and it comes to be.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 69
			-
				-
					Have you not observed those who dispute regarding God's revelations, how they
					have deviated?
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 70
			-
				-
					Those who call the Book a lie, and what We sent Our messengers with-they will
					surely know.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 71
			-
				-
					When the yokes are around their necks, and they will be dragged by the chains.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 72
			-
				-
					Into the boiling water, then in the Fire they will be consumed.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 73
			-
				-
					Then it will be said to them, "Where are those you used to deify?
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 74
			-
				-
					Instead of God?" They will say, "They have abandoned us. In fact, we were
					praying to nothing before." Thus God sends the disbelievers astray.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 75
			-
				-
					That is because you used to rejoice on earth in other than the truth, and
					because you used to behave with vanity.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 76
			-
				-
					Enter the gates of Hell, to remain therein forever. What a terrible dwelling
					for the arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 77
			-
				-
					So be patient. The promise of God is true. Whether We show you some of what We
					have promised them, or take you to Us, to Us they will be returned.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 78
			-
				-
					We sent messengers before you. Some of them We told you about, and some We did
					not tell you about. No messenger can bring a miracle except by leave of God.
					Then, when the command of God is issued, fair judgment will be passed, and
					there and then the seekers of vanity will lose.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 79
			-
				-
					God is He who created the domestic animals for you-some for you to ride, and
					some you eat.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 80
			-
				-
					And in them you have other benefits as well, and through them you satisfy your
					needs. And on them, and on the ships, you are transported.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 81
			-
				-
					And He shows you His signs. So which of God's signs will you deny?
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 82
			-
				-
					Have they not journeyed through the land, and seen the outcome for those before
					them? They were more numerous than they, and had greater power and influence in
					the land. But what they had achieved availed them nothing.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 83
			-
				-
					When their messengers came to them with clear proofs, they rejoiced in the
					knowledge they had, and the very things they used to ridicule besieged them.
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 84
			-
				-
					Then, when they witnessed Our might, they said, "We believe in God alone, and
					we reject what we used to associate with Him."
				-
			-
				Surah 40 - The Forgiver: Ayah 85
			-
				-
					But their faith could not help them once they witnessed Our might. This has
					been God's way of dealing with His servants. And there and then the
					disbelievers lost.
				-
		-
			Surah 41 - Explained In Detail
		-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Ha, Meem.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					A revelation from the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					A Scripture whose Verses are detailed, a Quran in Arabic for people who know.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Bringing good news, and giving warnings. But most of them turn away, so they do
					not listen.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And they say, "Our hearts are screened from what you call us to, and in our
					ears is deafness, and between us and you is a barrier. So do what you want, and
					so will we."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Say, "I am only a human like you; it is inspired in me that your God is One
					God. So be upright towards Him, and seek forgiveness from Him." And woe to the
					idolaters.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Those who do not pay the alms; and regarding the Hereafter, they are
					disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					As for those who believe and do righteous deeds-for them is a reward
					uninterrupted.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Say, "Do you reject the One who created the earth in two days? And you
					attribute equals to Him? That is the Lord of the Universe."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					He placed stabilizers over it; and blessed it; and planned its provisions in
					four days, equally to the seekers.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Then He turned to the sky, and it was smoke, and said to it and to the earth,
					"Come, willingly or unwillingly." They said, "We come willingly."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					So He completed them as seven universes in two days, and He assigned to each
					universe its laws. And We decorated the lower universe with lamps, and for
					protection. That is the design of the Almighty, the All-Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					But if they turn away, say, "I have warned you of a thunderbolt, like the
					thunderbolt of Aad and Thamood."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Their messengers came to them, from before them and from behind them, saying,
					"Do not worship anyone but God." They said, "Had our Lord willed, He would have
					sent down angels; Therefore, we reject what you are sent with."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					As for Aad, they turned arrogant on earth, and opposed justice, and said, "Who
					is more powerful than us?" Have they not considered that God, who created them,
					is more powerful than they? And they went on denying Our revelations.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					So We unleashed upon them a screaming wind, for a few miserable days, to make
					them taste the punishment of shame in this life; but the punishment of the
					Hereafter is more shameful; and they will not be saved.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And as for Thamood, We guided them, but they preferred blindness over guidance.
					So the thunderbolt of the humiliating punishment seized them, because of what
					they used to earn.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And We saved those who believed and were righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					The Day when God's enemies are herded into the Fire, forcibly.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Until, when they have reached it, their hearing, and their sight, and their
					skins will testify against them regarding what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And they will say to their skins, "Why did you testify against us?" They will
					say, "God, Who made all things speak, made us speak. It is He who created you
					the first time, and to Him you are returned."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					You were unable to hide yourselves from your hearing, and your sight, and your
					skins, to prevent them from testifying against you, and you imagined that God
					was unaware of much of what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					It is that thought of yours about your Lord that led you to ruin-so you became
					of the losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					If they endure patiently, the Fire will be their residence; and if they make up
					excuses, they will not be pardoned.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					We had assigned companions for them, who glamorized to them what was in front
					of them, and what was behind them. And the Word proved true against them in
					communities of jinn and humans that have passed away before them. They were
					losers.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve say, "Do not listen to this Quran, and talk over it, so
					that you may prevail."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					We will make those who disbelieve taste an intense agony, and We will
					recompense them according to the worst of what they used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Such is the recompense of God's enemies-the Fire-where they will have their
					permanent home, in recompense for having disregarded Our revelations.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieved will say, "Our Lord, show us those who led us
					astray-among jinn and humans-and we will trample them under our feet, so they
					become of the lowest."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Surely, those who say: "Our Lord is God," and then go straight, the angels will
					descend upon them: "Do not fear, and do not grieve, but rejoice in the news of
					the Garden which you were promised.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					We are your allies in this life and in the Hereafter, wherein you will have
					whatever your souls desire, and you will have therein whatever you call for.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					As Hospitality from an All-Forgiving, Merciful One."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And who is better in speech than someone who calls to God, and acts with
					integrity, and says, "I am of those who submit"?
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Good and evil are not equal. Repel evil with good, and the person who was your
					enemy becomes like an intimate friend.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					But none will attain it except those who persevere, and none will attain it
					except the very fortunate.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					When a temptation from the Devil provokes you, seek refuge in God; He is the
					Hearer, the Knower.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					And of His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. Do not
					bow down to the sun, nor to the moon, but bow down to God, Who created them
					both, if it is Him that you serve.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					But if they are too proud-those in the presence of your Lord praise Him night
					and day, and without ever tiring.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					And of His signs is that you see the land still. But when We send down water
					upon it, it stirs and grows. Surely, He Who revived it will revive the dead. He
					is Able to do all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Those who despise Our revelations are not hidden from Us. Is he who is hurled
					into the Fire better? Or he who arrives safely on the Day of Resurrection? Do
					as you please; He is Seeing of everything you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Those who reject the Reminder when it has come to them-it is an invincible
					Book.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Falsehood cannot approach it, from before it or behind it. It is a revelation
					from One Wise and Praiseworthy.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Nothing is said to you but was said to the Messengers before you: your Lord is
					Possessor of Forgiveness, and Possessor of Painful Repayment.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Had We made it a Quran in a foreign language, they would have said, "If only
					its verses were made clear." Non-Arabic and an Arab? Say, "For those who
					believe, it is guidance and healing. But as for those who do not believe: there
					is heaviness in their ears, and it is blindness for them. These are being
					called from a distant place."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					We gave Moses the Book, but disputes arose concerning it. Were it not for a
					prior decree from your Lord, judgment would have been pronounced between them.
					But they are in perplexing doubt concerning it.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					Whoever acts righteously does so for himself; and whoever works evil does so
					against himself. Your Lord is not unjust to the servants.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					To Him is referred the knowledge of the Hour. No fruit emerges from its sheath,
					and no female conceives or delivers, except with His knowledge. And on the Day
					when He calls out to them, "Where are My associates?" They will say, "We admit
					to you, none of us is a witness."
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					What they used to pray to before will forsake them, and they will realize that
					they have no escape.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					The human being never tires of praying for good things; but when adversity
					afflicts him, he despairs and loses hope.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					And when We let him taste a mercy from Us, after the adversity that had
					afflicted him, he will say, "This is mine, and I do not think that the Hour is
					coming; and even if I am returned to my Lord, I will have the very best with
					Him." We will inform those who disbelieve of what they did, and We will make
					them taste an awful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					When We provide comfort for the human being, he withdraws and distances
					himself; but when adversity befalls him, he starts lengthy prayers.
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Say, "Have you considered? If it is from God and you reject it-who is further
					astray than he who is cutoff and alienated?"
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					We will show them Our proofs on the horizons, and in their very souls, until it
					becomes clear to them that it is the truth. Is it not sufficient that your Lord
					is witness over everything?
				-
			-
				Surah 41 - Explained In Detail: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					Surely they are in doubt about the encounter with their Lord. Surely He
					comprehends everything.
				-
		-
			Surah 42 - Council
		-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Ha, Meem.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Ayn, Seen, Qaf.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Thus He inspires you, and those before you-God the Almighty, the Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					To him belongs everything in the heavens and everything on earth. He is the
					Sublime, the Magnificent.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					The heavens above them almost burst apart, while the angels glorify the praises
					of their Lord, and ask forgiveness for those on earth. God is indeed the
					Forgiver, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					As for those who take masters other than Him: God is in charge of them, and you
					are not responsible for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Thus We inspired you with an Arabic Quran, that you may warn the Central City
					and whoever is around it, and to warn of the Day of Assembly, of which there is
					no doubt; a group in the Garden, and a group in the Furnace.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Had God willed, He could have made them one community, but He admits into His
					mercy whomever He wills. As for the wrongdoers, they will have no protector and
					no savior.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Or have they adopted protectors besides him? But God is the Protector, and He
					gives life to the dead, and He has power over all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Whatever matter you differ about, its judgment rests with God. "Such is God, my
					Lord, in Whom I trust, and unto Him I repent."
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Originator of the heavens and the earth. He made for you mates from among
					yourselves, and pairs of animals, by means of which He multiplies you. There is
					nothing like Him. He is the Hearing, the Seeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					To Him belongs absolute control of the heavens and the earth. He spreads the
					bounties to whomever He wills, or reduces it. He is aware of all things.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					He prescribed for you the same religion He enjoined upon Noah, and what We
					inspired to you, and what We enjoined upon Abraham, and Moses, and Jesus: "You
					shall uphold the religion, and be not divided therein." As for the idolaters,
					what you call them to is outrageous to them. God chooses to Himself whom He
					wills, and He guides to Himself whoever repents.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					They became divided only after knowledge came to them, out of resentment among
					themselves. Were it not for a predetermined decision from your Lord, judgment
					would have been pronounced between them. Indeed, those who were made to inherit
					the Book after them are in grave doubt about it.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					To this go on inviting, and be upright as you were commanded, and do not follow
					their inclinations, and say, "I believe in whatever Book God has sent down, and
					I was commanded to judge between you equitably. God is our Lord and your Lord.
					We have our deeds, and you have your deeds. Let there be no quarrel between us
					and you. God will bring us together, and to Him is the ultimate return."
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					As for those who dispute about God after having answered His call, their
					argument is invalid with their Lord; and upon them falls wrath; and a grievous
					torment awaits them.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					It is God who revealed the Book with the truth, and the Balance. And what will
					make you realize that perhaps the Hour is near?
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Those who do not believe in it seek to hasten it; but those who believe are
					apprehensive of it, and they know it to be the truth. Absolutely, those who
					question the Hour are in distant error.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					God is kind towards His worshipers. He provides for whomever He wills. He is
					the Powerful, the Honorable.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Whoever desires the harvest of the Hereafter, We increase for him his harvest;
					and whoever desires the harvest of this world, We give him thereof, and he has
					no share of the Hereafter.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Or is it that they have partners who litigate for them religious laws never
					authorized by God? Were it not for the conclusive decision, it would have been
					settled between them. The wicked will have a painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					You will see the unjust terrified of what they have earned, and it will befall
					them. As for those who believe and do good deeds, they will be in the Meadows
					of the Gardens; they will have whatever they please in the presence of their
					Lord; that is the supreme blessing.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					That is the good news God gives to His servants who believe and do good deeds.
					Say, "I ask of you no wage for it, except affection among the near of kin."
					Whoever does a good deed, We will increase its goodness for him. God is
					Forgiving and Appreciative.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Or do they say, "He forged a lie about God." If God so willed, He could have
					sealed your heart. But God obliterates the false, and confirm the true by His
					Words. He knows what is in the hearts.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					It is He who accepts the repentance of His worshipers, and remits the sins, and
					knows what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					And He answers those who believe and do good deeds, and He increases them of
					His grace. But the disbelievers will suffer a terrible punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					If God were to increase the provision to His servants, they would transgress on
					earth; but He sends down in precise measure whatever He wills. Surely,
					regarding His servants, He is Expert and Observant.
				-
			-
				Surah 42 - Council: Ayah 28
			-
				-
