			-
				-
					Recall when We dispatched towards you a number of jinn, to listen to the Quran.
					When they came in its presence, they said, "Pay attention!" Then, when it was
					concluded, they rushed to their people, warning them.
				-
			-
				Surah 46 - The Wind-curved Sandhills: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					They said, "our people, we have heard a Scripture, sent down after Moses,
					confirming what came before it. It guides to the truth, and to a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 46 - The Wind-curved Sandhills: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					O our people! Answer the caller to God, and believe in Him; and He will forgive
					you your sins, and will save you from a painful punishment."
				-
			-
				Surah 46 - The Wind-curved Sandhills: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					He who does not answer the caller to God will not escape on earth, and has no
					protectors besides Him. Those are in obvious error.
				-
			-
				Surah 46 - The Wind-curved Sandhills: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Do they not realize that God, who created the heavens and the earth, and was
					never tired by creating them, is Able to revive the dead? Yes indeed; He is
					Capable of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 46 - The Wind-curved Sandhills: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					On the Day when those who disbelieved are presented to the Fire: "Is this not
					real?" They will say, "Yes, indeed, by our Lord." He will say, "Then taste the
					suffering for having disbelieved."
				-
			-
				Surah 46 - The Wind-curved Sandhills: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					So be patient, as the messengers with resolve were patient, and do not be hasty
					regarding them. On the Day when they witness what they are promised, it will
					seem as if they had lasted only for an hour of a day. A proclamation: Will any
					be destroyed except the sinful people?
				-
		-
			Surah 47 - Muhammad
		-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve and repel from the path of God-He nullifies their works.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					While those who believe, and work righteousness, and believe in what was sent
					down to Muhammad-and it is the truth from their Lord-He remits their sins, and
					relieves their concerns.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					That is because those who disbelieve follow falsehoods, while those who believe
					follow the truth from their Lord. God thus cites for the people their examples.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					When you encounter those who disbelieve, strike at their necks. Then, when you
					have routed them, bind them firmly. Then, either release them by grace, or by
					ransom, until war lays down its burdens. Had God willed, He could have defeated
					them Himself, but He thus tests some of you by means of others. As for those
					who are killed in the way of God, He will not let their deeds go to waste.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					He will guide them, and will improve their state of mind.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And will admit them into Paradise, which He has identified for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					O you who believe! If you support God, He will support you, and will strengthen
					your foothold.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					But as for those who disbelieve, for them is perdition, and He will waste their
					deeds.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					That is because they hated what God revealed, so He nullified their deeds.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Have they not journeyed through the earth and seen the consequences for those
					before them? God poured destruction upon them, and for the unbelievers is
					something comparable.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					That is because God is the Master of those who believe, while the disbelievers
					have no master.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					God will admit those who believe and do good deeds into gardens beneath which
					rivers flow. As for those who disbelieve, they enjoy themselves, and eat as
					cattle eat, and the Fire will be their dwelling.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					How many a town was more powerful than your town which evicted you? We
					destroyed them, and there was no helper for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Is he who stands upon evidence from his Lord, like someone whose evil deed is
					made to appear good to him? And they follow their own desires?
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					The likeness of the Garden promised to the righteous: in it are rivers of pure
					water, and rivers of milk forever fresh, and rivers of wine delightful to the
					drinkers, and rivers of strained honey. And therein they will have of every
					fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. Like one abiding in the Fire forever,
					and are given to drink boiling water, that cuts-up their bowels?
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Among them are those who listen to you, but when they leave your presence, they
					say to those given knowledge, "What did he say just now?" Those are they whose
					hearts God has sealed, and they follow their own desires.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					As for those who are guided, He increases them in guidance, and He has granted
					them their righteousness.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Are they just waiting until the Hour comes to them suddenly? Its tokens have
					already come. But how will they be reminded when it has come to them?
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Know that there is no god but God, and ask forgiveness for your sin, and for
					the believing men and believing women. God knows your movements, and your
					resting-place.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Those who believe say, "If only a chapter is sent down." Yet when a decisive
					chapter is sent down, and fighting is mentioned in it, you see those in whose
					hearts is sickness looking at you with the look of someone fainting at death.
					So woe to them!
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Obedience and upright speech. Then, when the matter is settled, being true to
					God would have been better for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					If you turn away, you are likely to make mischief on earth, and sever your
					family ties.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Those are they whom God has cursed. He made them deaf, and blinded their sight.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Will they not ponder the Quran? Or are there locks upon their hearts?
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Those who reverted after the guidance became clear to them-Satan has enticed
					them, and has given them latitude.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					That is because they said to those who hated what God has revealed, "We will
					obey you in certain matters." But God knows their secret thoughts.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					How about when the angels take them at death, beating their faces and their
					backs?
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					That is because they pursued what displeases God, and they disliked His
					approval, so He nullified their works.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Do those in whose hearts is sickness think that God will not expose their
					malice?
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Had We willed, We could have shown them to you, and you would have recognized
					them by their marks. Yet you will recognize them by their tone of speech. And
					God knows your actions.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					We will certainly test you, until We know those among you who strive, and those
					who are steadfast, and We will test your reactions.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve, and hinder from the path of God, and oppose the Messenger
					after guidance has become clear to them-they will not hurt God in the least,
					but He will nullify their deeds.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Obey God, and obey the Messenger, and do not let your deeds
					go to waste.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieve, and hinder from God's path, and then die as
					disbelievers-God will not forgive them.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					So do not waver and call for peace while you have the upper hand. God is with
					you, and He will not waste your efforts.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					The life of this world is nothing but play and pastime. But if you have faith
					and lead a righteous life, He will grant you your rewards, and He will not ask
					you for your possessions.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Were He to ask you for it, and press you, you would become tightfisted, and He
					would expose your unwillingness.
				-
			-
				Surah 47 - Muhammad: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Here you are, being called to spend in the cause of God. Among you are those
					who withhold; but whoever withholds is withholding against his own soul. God is
					the Rich, while you are the needy. And if you turn away, He will replace you
					with another people, and they will not be like you.
				-
		-
			Surah 48 - Victory
		-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					We have granted you a conspicuous victory.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					That God may forgive you your sin, past and to come, and complete His favors
					upon you, and guide you in a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And help you with an unwavering support.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					It is He who sent down tranquility into the hearts of the believers, to add
					faith to their faith. To God belong the forces of the heavens and the earth.
					God is Knowing and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					He will admit the believers, male and female, into Gardens beneath which rivers
					flow, to abide therein forever, and He will remit their sins. That, with God,
					is a great triumph.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And He will punish the hypocrites, male and female, and the idolaters, male and
					female, those who harbor evil thoughts about God. They are surrounded by evil;
					and God is angry with them, and has cursed them, and has prepared for them
					Hell-a miserable destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					To God belong the troops of the heavens and the earth. God is Mighty and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					We sent you as a witness, and a bearer of good news, and a warner.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					That you may believe in God and His Messenger, and support Him, and honor Him,
					and praise Him morning and evening.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Those who pledge allegiance to you are pledging allegiance to God. The hand of
					God is over their hands. Whoever breaks his pledge breaks it to his own loss.
					And whoever fulfills his covenant with God, He will grant him a great reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					The Desert-Arabs who remained behind will say to you, "Our belongings and our
					families have preoccupied us, so ask forgiveness for us." They say with their
					tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, "Who can avail you anything against
					God, if He desires loss for you, or desires gain for you?" In fact, God is
					Informed of what you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					But you thought that the Messenger and the believers will never return to their
					families, and this seemed fine to your hearts; and you harbored evil thoughts,
					and were uncivilized people.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					He who does not believe in God and His Messenger-We have prepared for the
					disbelievers a Blazing Fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					To God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whomever
					He wills, and He punishes whomever He wills. God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Those who lagged behind will say when you depart to collect the gains, "Let us
					follow you." They want to change the Word of God. Say, "You will not follow us;
					God has said so before." Then they will say, "But you are jealous of us." In
					fact, they understand only a little.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Say to the Desert-Arabs who lagged behind, "You will be called against a people
					of great might; you will fight them, unless they submit. If you obey, God will
					give you a fine reward. But if you turn away, as you turned away before, He
					will punish you with a painful punishment."
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					There is no blame on the blind, nor any blame on the lame, nor any blame on the
					sick. Whoever obeys God and His Messenger-He will admit him into gardens
					beneath which rivers flow; but whoever turns away-He will punish him with a
					painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					God was pleased with the believers, when they pledged allegiance to you under
					the tree. He knew what was in their hearts, and sent down serenity upon them,
					and rewarded them with an imminent conquest.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					And abundant gains for them to capture. God is Mighty and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					God has promised you abundant gains, which you will capture. He has expedited
					this for you, and has restrained people's hands from you; that it may be a sign
					to the believers, and that He may guide you on a straight path.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And other things, of which you were incapable, but God has encompassed them.
					God is Capable of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					If those who disbelieve had fought you, they would have turned back and fled,
					then found neither protector nor helper.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					It is God's pattern, ongoing since the past. You will never find any change in
					God's pattern.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					It is He who withheld their hands from you, and your hands from them, in the
					valley of Mecca, after giving you advantage over them. God is Observer of what
					you do.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					It is they who disbelieved, and barred you from the Sacred Mosque, and
					prevented the offering from reaching its destination. Were it not for faithful
					men and faithful women, whom you did not know, you were about to hurt them, and
					became guilty of an unintentional crime. Thus God admits into His mercy
					whomever He wills. Had they dispersed, We would have punished those who
					disbelieved among them with a painful penalty.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Those who disbelieved filled their hearts with rage-the rage of the days of
					ignorance. But God sent His serenity down upon His Messenger, and upon the
					believers, and imposed on them the words of righteousness-of which they were
					most worthy and deserving. God is aware of everything.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					God has fulfilled His Messenger's vision in truth: "You will enter the Sacred
					Mosque, God willing, in security, heads shaven, or hair cut short, not fearing.
					He knew what you did not know, and has granted besides that an imminent
					victory."
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					It is He who sent His Messenger with the guidance and the religion of truth, to
					make it prevail over all religions. God suffices as Witness.
				-
			-
				Surah 48 - Victory: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					Muhammad is the Messenger of God. Those with him are stern against the
					disbelievers, yet compassionate amongst themselves. You see them kneeling,
					prostrating, seeking blessings from God and approval. Their marks are on their
					faces from the effects of prostration. Such is their description in the Torah,
					and their description in the Gospel: like a plant that sprouts, becomes strong,
					grows thick, and rests on its stem, impressing the farmers. Through them He
					enrages the disbelievers. God has promised those among them who believe and do
					good deeds forgiveness and a great reward.
				-
		-
			Surah 49 - The Private Apartments
		-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not place your opinions above that of God and His
					Messenger, and fear God. God is Hearing and Knowing.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, and
					do not speak loudly to him, as you speak loudly to one another, lest your works
					be in vain without you realizing.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Those who lower their voices before God's Messenger-those are they whose hearts
					God has tested for piety. They will have forgiveness and a great reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Those who call you from behind the chambers-most of them do not understand.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Had they remained patient until you came out to them, it would have been better
					for them. But God is Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					O you who believe! If a troublemaker brings you any news, investigate, lest you
					harm people out of ignorance, and you become regretful for what you have done.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And know that among you is the Messenger of God. Had he obeyed you in many
					things, you would have suffered hardship. But God has given you the love of
					faith, and adorned it in your hearts, and made disbelief, mischief, and
					rebellion hateful to you. These are the rightly guided.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					A Grace and Favor from God. God is Knowing and Wise.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					If two groups of believers fight each other, reconcile between them. But if one
					group aggresses against the other, fight the aggressing group until it complies
					with God's command. Once it has complied, reconcile between them with justice,
					and be equitable. God loves the equitable.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					The believers are brothers, so reconcile between your brothers, and remain
					conscious of God, so that you may receive mercy.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					O you who believe! No people shall ridicule other people, for they may be
					better than they. Nor shall any women ridicule other women, for they may be
					better than they. Nor shall you slander one another, nor shall you insult one
					another with names. Evil is the return to wickedness after having attained
					faith. Whoever does not repent-these are the wrongdoers.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					O you who believe! Avoid most suspicion-some suspicion is sinful. And do not
					spy on one another, nor backbite one another. Would any of you like to eat the
					flesh of his dead brother? You would detest it. So remain mindful of God. God
					is Most Relenting, Most Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					O people! We created you from a male and a female, and made you races and
					tribes, that you may know one another. The best among you in the sight of God
					is the most righteous. God is All-Knowing, Well-Experienced.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					The Desert-Arabs say, "We have believed." Say, "You have not believed; but say,
					'We have submitted,' for faith has not yet entered into your hearts. But if you
					obey God and His Messenger, He will not diminish any of your deeds. God is
					Forgiving and Merciful."
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					The believers are those who believe in God and His Messenger, and then have not
					doubted, and strive for God's cause with their wealth and their persons. These
					are the sincere.
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Say, "Are you going to teach God about your religion, when God knows everything
					in the heavens and the earth, and God is aware of all things?"
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					They regarded it a favor to you that they have submitted. Say, "Do not consider
					your submission a favor to me; it is God who has done you a favor by guiding
					you to the faith, if you are sincere."
				-
			-
				Surah 49 - The Private Apartments: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					God knows the secrets of the heavens and the earth, and God is seeing of
					everything you do.
				-
		-
			Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf
		-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Qaf. By the Glorious Quran.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					They marveled that a warner has come to them from among them. The disbelievers
					say, "This is something strange.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					When we have died and become dust? This is a farfetched return."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					We know what the earth consumes of them, and with Us is a comprehensive book.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					But they denied the truth when it has come to them, so they are in a confused
					state.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Have they not observed the sky above them, how We constructed it, and decorated
					it, and it has no cracks?
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And the earth, how We spread it out, and set on it mountains, and grew in it
					all kinds of delightful pairs?
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					A lesson and a reminder for every penitent worshiper.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					And We brought down from the sky blessed water, and produced with it gardens
					and grain to harvest.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					And the soaring palm trees, with clustered dates.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					As sustenance for the servants. And We revive thereby a dead town. Likewise is
					the resurrection.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Before them the people of Noah denied the truth, and so did the dwellers of
					Russ, and Thamood.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And Aad, and Pharaoh, and the brethren of Lot.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					And the Dwellers of the Woods, and the people of Tubba. They all rejected the
					messengers, so My threat came true.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Were We fatigued by the first creation? But they are in doubt of a new
					creation.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					We created the human being, and We know what his soul whispers to him. We are
					nearer to him than his jugular vein.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					As the two receivers receive, seated to the right and to the left.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Not a word does he utter, but there is a watcher by him, ready.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					The daze of death has come in truth: "This is what you tried to evade."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And the Trumpet is blown: "This is the Promised Day."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And every soul will come forward, accompanied by a driver and a witness.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					"You were in neglect of this, so We lifted your screen from you, and your
					vision today is keen."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					And His escort will say, "This is what I have ready with me."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					"Throw into Hell every stubborn disbeliever.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Preventer of good, aggressor, doubter.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Who fabricated another god with God; toss him into the intense agony."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					His escort will say, "Our Lord, I did not make him rebel, but he was far
					astray."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					He will say, "Do not feud in My presence-I had warned you in advance.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					The decree from Me will not be changed, and I am not unjust to the servants."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					On the Day when We will say to Hell, "Are you full?" And it will say, "Are
					there any more?"
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					And Paradise will be brought closer to the pious, not far away.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					"This is what you were promised-for every careful penitent.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Who inwardly feared the Most Gracious, and came with a repentant heart.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					Enter it in peace. This is the Day of Eternity."
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Therein they will have whatever they desire-and We have even more.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					How many generations before them, who were more powerful than they, did We
					destroy? They explored the lands-was there any escape?
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					In that is a reminder for whoever possesses a heart, or cares to listen and
					witness.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					We created the heavens and the earth and what is between them in six days, and
					no fatigue touched Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					So endure what they say, and proclaim the praises of your Lord before the
					rising of the sun, and before sunset.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					And glorify Him during the night, and at the end of devotions.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					And listen for the Day when the caller calls from a nearby place.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					The Day when they will hear the Shout in all truth. That is the Day of
					Emergence.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					It is We who control life and death, and to Us is the destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					The Day when the earth will crack for them at once. That is an easy gathering
					for Us.
				-
			-
				Surah 50 - The Letter Qaf: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					We are fully aware of what they say, and you are not a dictator over them. So
					remind by the Quran whoever fears My warning.
				-
		-
			Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds
		-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					By the spreaders spreading.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					And those carrying loads.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And those moving gently.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					And those distributing as commanded.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					What you are promised is true.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Judgment will take place.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					By the sky that is woven.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					You differ in what you say.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Averted from it is he who is averted.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Perish the imposters.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Those who are dazed in ignorance.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					They ask, "When is the Day of Judgment?"
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					The Day they are presented to the Fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					"Taste your ordeal. This is what you used to challenge."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					But the pious are amidst gardens and springs.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Receiving what their Lord has given them. They were virtuous before that.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					They used to sleep a little at night.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					And at dawn, they would pray for pardon.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					And in their wealth, there was a share for the beggar and the deprived.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And on earth are signs for the convinced.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					And within yourselves. Do you not see?
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And in the heaven is your livelihood, and what you are promised.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					By the Lord of the heaven and the earth, it is as true as the fact that you
					speak.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Has the story of Abraham's honorable guests reached you?
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					When they entered upon him, they said, "Peace." He said, "Peace, strangers."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Then he slipped away to his family, and brought a fatted calf.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					He set it before them. He said, "Will you not eat?"
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And he harbored fear of them. They said, "Do not fear," and they announced to
					him the good news of a knowledgeable boy.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					His wife came forward crying. She clasped her face, and said, "A barren old
					woman?"
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					They said, "Thus spoke your Lord. He is the Wise, the Knowing."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					He said, "What is your business, O envoys?"
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					They said, "We are sent to a people guilty of sin."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					"To unleash upon them rocks of clay."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					"Marked by your Lord for the excessive."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					We evacuated all the believers who were in it.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					But found in it only one household of Muslims.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					And We left in it a sign for those who fear the painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					And in Moses. We sent him to Pharaoh with a clear authority.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					But he turned away with his warlords, and said, "A sorcerer or a madman."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					So We seized him and his troops, and threw them into the sea, and He was to
					blame.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					And in Aad. We unleashed against them the devastating wind.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					It spared nothing it came upon, but rendered it like decayed ruins.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					And in Thamood. They were told, "Enjoy yourselves for a while."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					But they defied the command of their Lord, so the lightning struck them as they
					looked on.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					They could not rise up, nor could they find help.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					And before that, the people of Noah. They were immoral people.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					We constructed the universe with power, and We are expanding it.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					And the earth-We spread it out-How well We prepared it!
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					We created all things in pairs, so that you may reflect and ponder.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					"So flee towards God. I am to you from Him a clear warner."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					"And do not set up any other god with God. I am to you from Him a clear
					warner."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					Likewise, no messenger came to those before them, but they said, "A sorcerer or
					a madman."
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					Did they recommend it to one another? In fact, they are rebellious people.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					So turn away from them; you are not to blame.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					And remind, for the reminder benefits the believers.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					I did not create the jinn and the humans except to worship Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					I need no livelihood from them, nor do I need them to feed Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					God is the Provider, the One with Power, the Strong.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Those who do wrong will have their turn, like the turn of their counterparts,
					so let them not rush Me.
				-
			-
				Surah 51 - The Winnowing Winds: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					So woe to those who disbelieve because of that Day of theirs which they are
					promised.
				-
		-
			Surah 52 - The Mount
		-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					By the Mount.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					And a Book inscribed.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					In a published scroll.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					And the frequented House.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And the elevated roof.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And the seething sea.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					The punishment of your Lord is coming.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					There is nothing to avert it.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					On the Day when the heaven sways in agitation.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					And the mountains go into motion.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Woe on that Day to the deniers.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Those who play with speculation.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					The Day when they are shoved into the Fire of Hell forcefully.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					"This is the Fire which you used to deny.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Is this magic, or do you not see?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Burn in it. Whether you are patient, or impatient, it is the same for you. You
					are only being repaid for what you used to do."
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					But the righteous will be amid gardens and bliss.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Enjoying what their Lord has given them, and their Lord has spared them the
					suffering of Hell.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Eat and drink happily, for what you used to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Relaxing on luxurious furnishings; and We will couple them with gorgeous
					spouses.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Those who believed, and their offspring followed them in faith-We will unite
					them with their offspring, and We will not deprive them of any of their works.
					Every person is hostage to what he has earned.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And We will supply them with fruit, and meat; such as they desire.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					They will exchange therein a cup; wherein is neither harm, nor sin.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Serving them will be youths like hidden pearls.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					And they will approach one another, inquiring.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					They will say, "Before this, we were fearful for our families.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					But God blessed us, and spared us the agony of the Fiery Winds.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					Before this, we used to pray to Him. He is the Good, the Compassionate."
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					So remind. By the grace of your Lord, you are neither a soothsayer, nor a
					madman.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Or do they say, "A poet-we await for him a calamity of time"?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					Say, "Go on waiting; I will be waiting with you."
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Or is it that their dreams compel them to this? Or are they aggressive people?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Or do they say, "He made it up"? Rather, they do not believe.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					So let them produce a discourse like it, if they are truthful.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Or were they created out of nothing? Or are they the creators?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Or did they create the heavens and the earth? In fact, they are not certain.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Or do they possess the treasuries of your Lord? Or are they the controllers?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Or do they have a stairway by means of which they listen? Then let their
					listener produce a clear proof.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Or for Him the daughters, and for you the sons?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					Or do you demand a payment from them, and they are burdened by debt?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Or do they know the future, and they are writing it down?
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					Or are they planning a conspiracy? The conspiracy will befall the disbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					Or do they have a god besides God? God transcends what they associate.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Even if they were to see lumps of the sky falling down, they would say, "A mass
					of clouds."
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					So leave them until they meet their Day in which they will be stunned.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					The Day when their ploys will avail them nothing; and they will not be helped.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					For those who do wrong, there is a punishment besides that; but most of them do
					not know.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					So patiently await the decision of your Lord, for you are before Our Eyes; and
					proclaim the praises of your Lord when you arise.
				-
			-
				Surah 52 - The Mount: Ayah 49
			-
				-
