			Surah 53 - The Star
		-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					By the star as it goes down.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Your friend has not gone astray, nor has he erred.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Nor does he speak out of desire.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					It is but a revelation revealed.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					Taught to him by the Extremely Powerful.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					The one of vigor. He settled.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					While he was at the highest horizon.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Then he came near, and hovered around.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					He was within two bows' length, or closer.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					Then He revealed to His servant what He revealed.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					The heart did not lie about what it saw.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Will you dispute with him concerning what he saw?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					He saw him on another descent.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					At the Lotus Tree of the Extremity.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Near which is the Garden of Repose.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					As there covered the Lotus Tree what covered it.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					The sight did not waver, nor did it exceed.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					He saw some of the Great Signs of his Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					Have you considered al-Lat and al-Uzza?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And Manat, the third one, the other?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Are you to have the males, and He the females?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					What a bizarre distribution.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					These are nothing but names, which you have devised, you and your ancestors,
					for which God sent down no authority. They follow nothing but assumptions, and
					what the ego desires, even though guidance has come to them from their Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Or is the human being to have whatever he desires?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					To God belong the Last and the First.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					How many an angel is there in the heavens whose intercession avails nothing,
					except after God gives permission to whomever He wills, and approves?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Those who do not believe in the Hereafter give the angels the names of females.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					They have no knowledge of that. They only follow assumptions, and assumptions
					are no substitute for the truth.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					So avoid him who has turned away from Our remembrance, and desires nothing but
					the present life.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					That is the extent of their knowledge. Your Lord knows best who has strayed
					from His path, and He knows best who has accepted guidance.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					To God belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on earth. He will
					repay those who do evil according to their deeds, and recompense those who do
					good with the best.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Those who avoid gross sins and indecencies-except for minor lapses-your Lord is
					of Vast Forgiveness. He knows you well, ever since He created you from the
					earth, and ever since you were embryos in your mothers' wombs. So do not
					acclaim your own virtue; He is fully aware of the righteous.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					Have you considered him who turned away?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And gave a little, and held back?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					Does he possess knowledge of the unseen, and can therefore foresee?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					Or was he not informed of what is in the Scrolls of Moses?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					And of Abraham, who fulfilled?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					That no soul bears the burdens of another soul.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					And that the human being attains only what he strives for.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					And that his efforts will be witnessed.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Then he will be rewarded for it the fullest reward.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					And that to your Lord is the finality.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					And that it is He who causes laughter and weeping.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					And that it is He who gives death and life.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 45
			-
				-
					And that it is He who created the two kinds-the male and the female.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 46
			-
				-
					From a sperm drop, when emitted.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 47
			-
				-
					And that upon Him is the next existence.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 48
			-
				-
					And that it is He who enriches and impoverishes.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 49
			-
				-
					And that it is He who is the Lord of Sirius.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 50
			-
				-
					And that it is He who destroyed the first Aad.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 51
			-
				-
					And Thamood, sparing no one.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 52
			-
				-
					And the people of Noah before that; for they were most unjust and most
					oppressive.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 53
			-
				-
					And He toppled the ruined cities.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 54
			-
				-
					And covered them with whatever covered them.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 55
			-
				-
					So which of your Lord's marvels can you deny?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 56
			-
				-
					This is a warning, just like the first warnings.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 57
			-
				-
					The inevitable is imminent.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 58
			-
				-
					None besides God can unveil it.
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 59
			-
				-
					Do you marvel at this discourse?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 60
			-
				-
					And laugh, and do not weep?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 61
			-
				-
					Lost in your frivolity?
				-
			-
				Surah 53 - The Star: Ayah 62
			-
				-
					So bow down to God, and worship!
