				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Except from their spouses or those living under their control, for then they
					are free of blame.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					But whoever seeks to go beyond that-these are the transgressors.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					And those who honor their trusts and their pledges.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And those who stand by their testimonies.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And those who are dedicated to their prayers.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					These will be honored in Gardens.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					What is with those who disbelieve, stretching their necks towards you.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					From the right, and from the left, banding together?
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Is every one of them aspiring to be admitted into a Garden of Bliss?
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					No indeed! We created them from what they know.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					I swear by the Lord of the Easts and the Wests, that We are Able.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					To replace them with better than they, and We are not to be outdone.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					So leave them to blunder and play, until they meet their Day which they are
					promised.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					The Day when they will emerge from the tombs in a rush, as though they were
					hurrying towards a target.
				-
			-
				Surah 70 - The Ascending Stairways: Ayah 44
			-
				-
					Their eyes cast down; overwhelmed by humiliation. This is the Day which they
					were promised.
				-
		-
			Surah 71 - Nooh
		-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					We sent Noah to his people: "Warn your people before there comes upon them a
					painful punishment."
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					He said, "my people, I am to you a clear warner.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					Worship God and reverence Him, and obey me.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					And He will forgive you of your sins, and reprieve you until a stated term.
					God's term cannot be deferred once it has arrived, if you only knew."
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					He said, "My Lord, I have called my people night and day.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					But my call added only to their flight.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Whenever I called them to Your forgiveness, they thrust their fingers into
					their ears, and wrapped themselves in their garments, and insisted, and became
					more and more arrogant.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					Then I called them openly.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Then I appealed to them publicly, and I spoke to them privately.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					I said, 'Ask your Lord for forgiveness; He is Forgiving.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					He will let loose the sky upon you in torrents.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					And provide you with wealth and children, and allot for you gardens, and allot
					for you rivers.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					What is the matter with you, that you do not appreciate God's Greatness?
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Although He created you in stages.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Do you not realize that God created seven heavens in layers?
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					And He set the moon in their midst for light, and He made the sun a lamp.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					And God germinated you from the earth like plants.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					Then He will return you into it, and will bring you out again.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					And God made the earth a spread for you.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					That you may travel its diverse roads.'"
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Noah said, "My Lord, they have defied me, and followed him whose wealth and
					children increase him only in perdition."
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					And they schemed outrageous schemes.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					And they said, "Do not give up your gods; do not give up Wadd, nor Souwa, nor
					Yaghoos, and Yaooq, and Nassr.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					They have misled many, so do not increase the wrongdoers except in confusion."
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Because of their wrongs, they were drowned, and were hurled into a Fire. They
					did not find apart from God any helpers.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Noah said, "My Lord, do not leave of the unbelievers a single dweller on earth.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					If You leave them, they will mislead your servants, and will breed only wicked
					unbelievers.
				-
			-
				Surah 71 - Nooh: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					My Lord! Forgive me and my parents, and anyone who enters my home in faith, and
					all the believing men and believing women; and do not increase the wrongdoers
					except in perdition."
				-
		-
			Surah 72 - The Jinn
		-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					Say, "It was revealed to me that a band of jinn listened in, and said, 'We have
					heard a wondrous Quran.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					It guides to rectitude, so we have believed in it; and we will never associate
					anyone with our Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And Exalted is the Grandeur of our Lord-He never had a mate, nor a child.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					But the fools among us used to say nonsense about God.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And we thought that humans and jinn would never utter lies about God.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					Some individual humans used to seek power through some individual jinn, but
					they only increased them in confusion.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					They thought, as you thought, that God would never resurrect anyone.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					We probed the heaven, and found it filled with stern guards and projectiles.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					We used to take up positions to listen in; but whoever listens now finds a
					projectile in wait for him.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					We do not know whether ill is intended for those on earth, or if their Lord
					intends goodness for them.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Some of us are righteous, but some of us are less than that; we follow
					divergent paths.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					We realized that we cannot defeat God on earth, and that we cannot escape Him
					by fleeing.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And when we heard the guidance, we believed in it. Whoever believes in his Lord
					fears neither loss, nor burden.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Among us are those who are submitting, and among us are the compromisers. As
					for those who have submitted-it is they who pursue rectitude.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					But as for the compromisers-they will be firewood for Hell.'"
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Had they kept true to the Path, We would have given them plenty water to drink.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					To test them with it. Whoever turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He
					will direct him to torment ever mounting.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					The places of worship are for God. So do not call, besides God, upon anyone
					else.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					And when the servant of God got up calling on Him, they almost fell on him in a
					mass.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Say, "I pray only to my Lord, and I never associate anyone with Him."
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Say, "It is not in my power to harm you, nor to bring you to right conduct."
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Say, "No one can protect me from God, and I will not find any refuge except
					with Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Except for a proclamation from God and His messages. He who defies God and His
					Messenger-for him is the Fire of Hell, in which they will dwell forever."
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Until, when they see what they were promised, they will know who is weaker in
					helpers, and fewer in numbers.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Say, "I do not know whether what you are promised is near, or whether my Lord
					will extend it for a period."
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					The Knower of the Invisible; He does not disclose His Invisible to anyone.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					Except to a Messenger of His choosing. He then dispatches guards before him and
					behind him.
				-
			-
				Surah 72 - The Jinn: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					That He may know that they have conveyed the messages of their Lord. He
					encompasses what they have, and has tallied everything by number.
				-
		-
			Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One
		-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					O you Enwrapped one.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Stay up the night, except a little.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					For half of it, or reduce it a little.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Or add to it; and chant the Quran rhythmically.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					We are about to give you a heavy message.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					The vigil of night is more effective, and better suited for recitation.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					In the daytime, you have lengthy work to do.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					So remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself to Him wholeheartedly.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					Lord of the East and the West. There is no god but He, so take Him as a
					Trustee.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					And endure patiently what they say, and withdraw from them politely.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					And leave Me to those who deny the truth, those of luxury, and give them a
					brief respite.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					With Us are shackles, and a Fierce Fire.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And food that chokes, and a painful punishment.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					On the Day when the earth and the mountains tremble, and the mountains become
					heaps of sand.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					We have sent to you a messenger, a witness over you, as We sent to Pharaoh a
					messenger.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					But Pharaoh defied the Messenger, so We seized him with a terrible seizing.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					So how will you, if you persist in unbelief, save yourself from a Day which
					will turn the children gray-haired?
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					The heaven will shatter thereby. His promise is always fulfilled.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					This is a reminder. So whoever wills, let him take a path to his Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 73 - The Enshrouded One: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Your Lord knows that you stay up nearly two-thirds of the night, or half of it,
					or one-third of it, along with a group of those with you. God designed the
					night and the day. He knows that you are unable to sustain it, so He has
					pardoned you. So read of the Quran what is possible for you. He knows that some
					of you may be ill; and others travelling through the land, seeking God's
					bounty; and others fighting in God's cause. So read of it what is possible for
					you, and observe the prayers, and give regular charity, and lend God a generous
					loan. Whatever good you advance for yourselves, you will find it with God,
					better and generously rewarded. And seek God's forgiveness, for God is
					Forgiving and Merciful.
				-
		-
			Surah 74 - The Cloaked One
		-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					O you Enrobed one.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					Arise and warn.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					And magnify your Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					And purify your clothes.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					And abandon abominations.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					And show no favor seeking gain.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					And be constant for your Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					When the Trumpet is blown.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					That Day will be a difficult day.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					For the disbelievers-not easy.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Leave Me to him whom I created alone.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					And gave him vast wealth.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					And children as witnesses.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					And smoothed things for him.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					Then he wants Me to add yet more!
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					By no means! He was stubborn towards Our revelations.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					I will exhaust him increasingly.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					He thought and analyzed.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					May he perish, how he analyzed.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Again: may he perish, how he analyzed.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Then he looked.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Then he frowned and whined.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Then he turned back and was proud.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					And said, "This is nothing but magic from the past.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					This is nothing but the word of a mortal."
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					I will roast him in Saqar.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					But what will explain to you what Saqar is?
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					It neither leaves, nor spares.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					It scorches the flesh.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					Over it are Nineteen.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					We have appointed only angels to be wardens of the Fire, and caused their
					number to be a stumbling block for those who disbelieve; so that those given
					the Scripture may attain certainty; and those who believe may increase in
					faith; and those given the Scripture and the believers may not doubt; and those
					in whose hearts is sickness and the unbelievers may say, "What did God intend
					by this parable?" Thus God leads astray whom He wills, and guides whom He
					wills. None knows the soldiers of your Lord except He. This is nothing but a
					reminder for the mortals.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Nay! By the moon.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And the night as it retreats.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And the morning as it lights up.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					It is one of the greatest.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					A warning to the mortals.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					To whomever among you wishes to advance, or regress.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Every soul is hostage to what it has earned.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Except for those on the Right.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					In Gardens, inquiring.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					About the guilty.
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					"What drove you into Saqar?"
				-
			-
				Surah 74 - The Cloaked One: Ayah 43
			-
				-
					They will say, "We were not of those who prayed.
