				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					And the mountains are set in motion, and become a mirage.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Hell is lying in ambush.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					For the oppressors, a destination.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					Where they will remain for eons.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					They will taste therein neither coolness, nor drink.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					Except boiling water, and freezing hail.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					A fitting requital.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					For they were not anticipating any reckoning.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And they denied Our signs utterly.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					But We have enumerated everything in writing.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					So taste! We will increase you only in suffering.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					But for the righteous there is triumph.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Gardens and vineyards.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					And splendid spouses, well matched.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					And delicious drinks.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					They will hear therein neither gossip, nor lies.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					A reward from your Lord, a fitting gift.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Lord of the heavens and the earth, and everything between them-The Most
					Merciful-none can argue with Him.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					On the Day when the Spirit and the angels stand in row. They will not speak,
					unless it be one permitted by the Most Merciful, and he will say what is right.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					That is the Day of Reality. So whoever wills, let him take a way back to his
					Lord.
				-
			-
				Surah 78 - The Tidings: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					We have warned you of a near punishment-the Day when a person will observe what
					his hands have produced, and the faithless will say, "O, I wish I were dust."
				-
