			Surah 80 - He Frowned
		-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 0
			-
				-
					In the name of God, the Gracious, the Merciful.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 1
			-
				-
					He frowned and turned away.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 2
			-
				-
					When the blind man approached him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 3
			-
				-
					But how do you know? Perhaps he was seeking to purify himself.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 4
			-
				-
					Or be reminded, and the message would benefit him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 5
			-
				-
					But as for him who was indifferent.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 6
			-
				-
					You gave him your attention.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 7
			-
				-
					Though you are not liable if he does not purify himself.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 8
			-
				-
					But as for him who came to you seeking.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 9
			-
				-
					In awe.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 10
			-
				-
					To him you were inattentive.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 11
			-
				-
					Do not. This is a Lesson.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 12
			-
				-
					Whoever wills, shall remember it.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 13
			-
				-
					On honorable pages.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 14
			-
				-
					Exalted and purified.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 15
			-
				-
					By the hands of scribes.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 16
			-
				-
					Noble and devoted.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 17
			-
				-
					Perish man! How thankless he is!
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 18
			-
				-
					From what did He create him?
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 19
			-
				-
					From a sperm drop He created him, and enabled him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 20
			-
				-
					Then He eased the way for him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 21
			-
				-
					Then He puts him to death, and buries him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 22
			-
				-
					Then, when He wills, He will resurrect him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 23
			-
				-
					But no, he did not fulfill what He has commanded him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 24
			-
				-
					Let man consider his food.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 25
			-
				-
					We pour down water in abundance.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 26
			-
				-
					Then crack the soil open.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 27
			-
				-
					And grow in it grains.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 28
			-
				-
					And grapes and herbs.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 29
			-
				-
					And olives and dates.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 30
			-
				-
					And luscious gardens.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 31
			-
				-
					And fruits and vegetables.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 32
			-
				-
					Enjoyment for you, and for your livestock.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 33
			-
				-
					But when the Deafening Noise comes to pass.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 34
			-
				-
					The Day when a person will flee from his brother.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 35
			-
				-
					And his mother and his father.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 36
			-
				-
					And his consort and his children.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 37
			-
				-
					Every one of them, on that Day, will have enough to preoccupy him.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 38
			-
				-
					Faces on that Day will be radiant.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 39
			-
				-
					Laughing and rejoicing.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 40
			-
				-
					And Faces on that Day will be covered with misery.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 41
			-
				-
					Overwhelmed by remorse.
				-
			-
				Surah 80 - He Frowned: Ayah 42
			-
				-
					These are the faithless, the vicious.
				-
